{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LTWjXPJJBevFH9K66WMAPL","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Office Agent\n     2→\n     3→Agent in a container, built for Office scenarios.\n     4→\n     5→## Prerequisites\n     6→\n     7→- **[Node.js](https://nodejs.org/en) >= v20** — recommend using [nvm-windows](https://github.com/coreybutler/nvm-windows) (with `nvm install lts`)\n     8→- **[Python](https://www.python.org/downloads/) >= 3.8** — for evaluation framework and testing tools (Python 3.12 recommended for msal[broker] support)\n     9→- **[.NET SDK](https://dotnet.microsoft.com/download) >= 8.0.416** — required by global.json\n    10→- [**Docker Desktop**](https://docs.docker.com/desktop/setup/install/windows-install/)\n    11→- [**Visual Studio Code**](https://code.visualstudio.com/)\n    12→\n    13→## Quick Start\n    14→\n    15→> **Note**: Only Node.js and Python are required upfront. All other tools are installed automatically.\n    16→\n    17→Run the automated setup to configure your development environment:\n    18→\n    19→```bash\n    20→npm run setup\n    21→```\n    22→\n    23→This will:\n    24→- Install global tools (Yarn, vsts-npm-auth)\n    25→- Install Node.js dependencies\n    26→- Create Python virtual environment and install packages\n    27→- Install VS Code extensions (ESLint, EditorConfig, Python)\n    28→- Configure Git settings\n    29→\n    30→> **Python Note**: VS Code automatically detects the `./venv` virtual environment. For terminal Python work, activate it with `.\\venv\\Scripts\\Activate.ps1` (Windows) or `source venv/bin/activate` (Mac/Linux).\n    31→\n    32→### Build\n    33→\n    34→> **Warning**: Docker Desktop must be running before executing `yarn build`. The build will fail if Docker is stopped.\n    35→\n    36→```bash\n    37→yarn build\n    38→```\n    39→\n    40→### Test\n    41→```bash\n    42→yarn test               # Runs both Jest (TypeScript/JavaScript) and pytest (Python) tests\n    43→```\n    44→\n    45→Tests include:\n    46→- **Jest**: TypeScript/JavaScript unit tests with coverage\n    47→- **pytest**: Python unit tests with coverage (see [Python Testing](docs/PYTHON_TESTING.md))\n    48→- Coverage reports generated only in CI/CD (when `TF_BUILD` is set)\n    49→\n    50→### Run\n    51→\n    52→Start the Docker container:\n    53→\n    54→```bash\n    55→yarn start              # Start Docker container and test client (no AugLoop required)\n    56→```\n    57→\n    58→Start the Docker Compose\n    59→```bash\n    60→yarn start:compose\n    61→```\n    62→\n    63→Stop the Docker container:\n    64→\n    65→```bash\n    66→yarn stop               # Stops and removes the OfficeAgent1 container\n    67→```\n    68→\n    69→See the [Available Scripts](#available-scripts) section for the complete list of Docker operations.\n    70→\n    71→## Development\n    72→\n    73→### Hot Reload\n    74→\n    75→For faster iteration during development, use hot reload to deploy code changes without rebuilding the Docker image:\n    76→\n    77→```bash\n    78→yarn reload             # Build your code changes and copy built files to running container and restart\n    79→```\n    80→\n    81→This updates `api/dist/` and `skills/` in the running container in seconds instead of minutes.\n    82→\n    83→> **Note**: If you modify Dockerfile, package.json dependencies, or other infrastructure files, run `yarn build` to rebuild the full Docker image.\n    84→\n    85→### Smoke Tests\n    86→\n    87→```bash\n    88→# Health check\n    89→oagent ping\n    90→\n    91→# Generate a document (this will take a while)\n    92→oagent generate \"Create a simple document about cats\" -o ./myfile.docx\n    93→```\n    94→\n    95→For direct API testing, you can use curl:\n    96→\n    97→```bash\n    98→# Health check\n    99→curl http://localhost:6010/health\n   100→\n   101→# Create a document (this will take a while)\n   102→curl -X POST http://localhost:6010/generateDocument -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"userQuery\": \"Create a simple document about cats\"}'\n   103→\n   104→# Create a PowerPoint with custom image variant (use v1 for presentai, gptv for GPT-V)\n   105→curl -X POST http://localhost:6010/generateDocument -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"userQuery\": \"Create a presentation about AI\", \"customImage\": \"v1\"}'\n   106→\n   107→# Download the file (fill in path from response above)\n   108→curl --output myfile.docx http://localhost:6010/download?filePath=path/to/myfile.docx\n   109→```\n   110→\n   111→### Package Management\n   112→Buildtime package management is handled by Yarn, with a workspace setup, with a _package.json_ and _yarn.lock_ at the root, and a _package.json_ inside each workspace.\n   113→Runtime package management, inside the container, is covered by\n   114→#### NPM:\n   115→Use command like `npm install react-dom@19.2.1 --force --ignore-scripts` inside _/docker/_ to update\n   116→- _/docker/package.json_\n   117→- _/docker/package-lock.json_\n   118→#### PIP & TDNF\n   119→- _/docker/Dockerfile_\n   120→\n   121→### Debugging API Server\n   122→\n   123→After starting Docker:\n   124→1. In VS Code, 'Run and Debug' view, run 'Attach - OfficeAgent API - Docker'\n   125→2. Set breakpoints in your TS files and trigger code execution through a request\n   126→\n   127→Note, you can not currently attach to skills JS executions triggered by Claude, which are happening in different processes.\n   128→![Screenshot of VS Code debugging session showing breakpoints set in TypeScript files and active debugging controls](./docs/images/debugging.png)\n   129→\n   130→### Testing with AugLoop\n   131→\n   132→1. Start the Docker container **without** the test client\n   133→    ```bash\n   134→    yarn start:docker\n   135→    ```\n   136→1. In your `augloop-workflow` repo:\n   137→   ```bash\n   138→   set OFFICE_AGENT_LOCAL_API=true\n   139→   augloop run office-agent -rdw -d\n   140→   ```\n   141→1. Open http://localhost:8989\n   142→1. Send the request\n   143→\n   144→### Testing in Office Agent Copilot (DA)\n   145→\n   146→## Skills\n   147→\n   148→- **DOCX**: Pack/unpack, schema validation (ISO/ECMA), offline OOXML schemas\n   149→- **PPTX**: OOXML operations, slide management, template processing, thumbnails, HTML→PPTX conversion\n   150→- **PDF**: Form field detection/extraction/filling, annotations, image conversion, bounding boxes\n   151→- **XLSX**: Lightweight recalculation helper\n   152→- **Utils**: Enterprise search helper\n   153→\n   154→## Architecture\n   155→\n   156→The API server includes a modular WebSocket routing system:\n   157→- **LLM API Proxy** — route LLM API calls through WebSocket\n   158→- **MCP Support** — Model Context Protocol message routing\n   159→- **Extensible Handlers** — add new protocol handlers easily\n   160→\n   161→See [`modules/api/websocket/README.md`](modules/api/websocket/README.md) for details.\n   162→\n   163→### Test Client\n   164→\n   165→For self-contained testing, we provide a test client that fulfills WebSocket requests from the container. This is automatically launched when you run `yarn start` (or run `yarn start:test` to only launch the test client).\n   166→\n   167→See [`.devtools/test-client/README.md`](.devtools/test-client/README.md) for details.\n   168→\n   169→### CLI Tool\n   170→\n   171→The Office Agent CLI provides a polished command-line interface for interacting with the API. You must run `yarn build` and `yarn start` before using the CLI.\n   172→\n   173→```bash\n   174→# Check API health\n   175→oagent ping\n   176→oagent ping --json\n   177→\n   178→# Generate documents\n   179→oagent gen \"Create a simple document about cats\" -o ./myfile.docx\n   180→oagent gen \"10-slide presentation about AI\" --open\n   181→\n   182→# Generate with custom image variants (for PPTX)\n   183→oagent gen \"Create a simple deck about cats\" -c v1        # Use presentai variant\n   184→oagent gen \"Create a simple deck about cats\" -c gptv      # Use GPT-V variant\n   185→\n   186→# Generate with flight flags for feature testing\n   187→oagent gen \"Create a simple deck about cats\" -f flight1 flight2 flight3\n   188→\n   189→# Generate with message annotations\n   190→# ✅ RECOMMENDED: Use file-based annotations (no escaping issues!)\n   191→oagent gen \"Summarize this file\" --message-annotations-file ./examples/message-annotations.json\n   192→\n   193→# Alternative: Inline JSON (requires careful shell escaping)\n   194→oagent gen \"Summarize\" -ma '[{\"id\":\"SPO_123\",\"queryAnnotationType\":\"File\",\"text\":\"report.docx\"}]'\n   195→\n   196→# 🎯 AUTO-DETECTION: Simply paste SharePoint/OneDrive URLs directly!\n   197→oagent gen \"Summarize https://microsoft-my.sharepoint-df.com/:w:/r/personal/vishalc_microsoft_com/_layouts/15/Doc.aspx?sourcedoc={DBB290D3-436E-4954-A893-CF1A8381F057}&file=GPT-5 Strategy for WXP Agents.docx\"\n   198→oagent gen \"Compare these files: https://contoso.sharepoint.com/:x:/Q1-Sales.xlsx and https://contoso.sharepoint.com/:x:/Q2-Sales.xlsx\"\n   199→\n   200→# Return async (don't wait for completion)\n   201→oagent gen \"Large presentation\" -ra\n   202→\n   203→# Generate with automatic report generation from debug.zip\n   204→oagent gen \"Create a deck about Project Nova. Don't ask any clarification questions. Just go ahead!\" -r\n   205→\n   206→# Generate with no enterprise search grounding\n   207→oagent gen \"Create a simple document about cats\" --disable-enterprise-search\n   208→\n   209→# Generate with no web search grounding\n   210→oagent gen \"Create a simple document about cats\" --disable-web-search\n   211→\n   212→# Configuration (stored in .env at repo root)\n   213→oagent config set apiUrl http://localhost:6010\n   214→oagent config set flights flag1,flag2       # Set default flight flags\n   215→oagent config get\n   216→oagent config path                           # Show config file location\n   217→oagent config reset\n   218→\n   219→# Evaluation framework\n   220→oagent eval submit --prompt \"Create a sales report with Q4 data. Don't ask any clarification questions. Just go ahead!\" --type pptx # Submit single evaluation\n   221→oagent eval run --batch eval/datasets/official_pairwise_officeagent_societas.json # Run batch evaluations\n   222→```\n   223→\n   224→**Available Commands:**\n   225→- `ping` - Health check with optional JSON output\n   226→- `generate|gen` - Generate documents with AI (supports: document type hints, grounding content, flight flags, async mode)\n   227→- `download|dl` - Download generated files\n   228→- `config` - Manage configuration stored in .env files (get, set, reset, path)\n   229→- `eval` - Evaluation framework for testing and quality assessment\n   230→\n   231→**Configuration:**\n   232→Settings are stored in `.env` file at the repository root with `OAGENT_` prefix. Copy from `.env.example`. Output files are saved to `<repo-root>/output` by default.\n   233→\n   234→**Get Help:**\n   235→```bash\n   236→oagent -h              # Show all available commands\n   237→oagent <command> -h    # Show options for a specific command\n   238→```\n   239→\n   240→See [`.devtools/cli/README.md`](.devtools/cli/README.md) for details.\n   241→\n   242→**Testing with MSA/Custom users via OAgent**\n   243→_See [Local Testing With Token Server](https://eng.ms/docs/experiences-devices/opg/office-ai/augloop-ai-platform/augmentation-loop/documentation/authentication/local-testing-with-token-server#use-multiple-users-or-custom-users) for detailed instructions._\n   244→1. Update Token Server settings to specify your user id in 'Defaults' from _me_.\n   245→\n   246→`<repo-root>\\node_modules\\@augloop-tools\\token-server\\dist\\exe\\settings.json`\n   247→```\n   248→\"Defaults\": {\n   249→      \"UserId\": \"mstest_<user>@outlook.com\",\n   250→}\n   251→```\n   252→2. Login with token server:\n   253→`<repo_root>\\node_modules\\@augloop-tools\\token-server\\dist\\exe\\TokenServer.exe login -u \"mstest_<user>@outlook.com\"`\n   254→3. Call via _oagent_. When testing _MSA_ pass `--disable-enterprise-search` to disable enterprise search (which would otherwise fail)\n   255→\n   256→**Evaluation Framework:**\n   257→\n   258→The eval framework provides automated testing and quality assessment for OfficeAgent. See [`eval/README.md`](eval/README.md) for complete documentation.\n   259→\n   260→## Custom Image Variants\n   261→\n   262→The API supports custom skill variants for different document generation approaches.\n   263→\n   264→### Available Variants\n   265→\n   266→- **`v1`** - Uses the Archetypes variant (`pptx_archetypes`)\n   267→- **`gptv`** - Uses the GPT-V variant (`pptx_gptv`)\n   268→- **Default (no flag)** - Uses the standard variant (`pptx`)\n   269→\n   270→### Usage\n   271→\n   272→**Via API:**\n   273→```bash\n   274→curl -X POST http://localhost:6010/generateDocument \\\n   275→  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n   276→  -d '{\n   277→    \"userQuery\": \"Create a presentation about AI\",\n   278→    \"customImage\": \"v1\"\n   279→  }'\n   280→```\n   281→\n   282→**Via CLI:**\n   283→```bash\n   284→oagent gen \"AI presentation\" -c v1    # PresentAI variant\n   285→oagent gen \"AI presentation\" -c gptv  # GPT-V variant\n   286→```\n   287→\n   288→### How It Works\n   289→\n   290→When a `customImage` flag is provided:\n   291→1. The system identifies the appropriate skill variant directory\n   292→2. It replaces the default skill implementation with the custom variant\n   293→3. The document is generated using the custom variant's logic\n   294→\n   295→When no flag is provided, alternative variant directories are automatically cleaned up to use only the default implementation.\n   296→\n   297→## Extending\n   298→\n   299→Create `skills/<name>/` with:\n   300→- `SKILL.md` — skill documentation\n   301→- `scripts/` — single-purpose scripts with minimal dependencies\n   302→\n   303→## Available Scripts\n   304→\n   305→The project provides several scripts for development and deployment:\n   306→\n   307→### Setup & Authentication\n   308→- **`npm run setup`** - Complete development environment setup (installs global tools, fetches auth token, installs dependencies, configures Git, installs VS Code extensions)\n   309→- **`yarn fetch:token`** - Fetch NPM authentication token for Office npm feed (requires vsts-npm-auth)\n   310→\n   311→### Build & Clean\n   312→- **`yarn build`** - Build bare minimum packages to run `yarn start`\n   313→- **`yarn build:all`** - Build all workspaces and Docker image\n   314→- **`yarn build:no-clean`** - Build bare minimum packages to run `yarn start`, without cleaning\n   315→- **`yarn clean`** - Clean all build artifacts\n   316→\n   317→### Docker Operations\n   318→- **`yarn start`** - Start Docker container and test client (no AugLoop required)\n   319→- **`yarn start:docker`** - Start Docker container without test client (needs AugLoop enlistment)\n   320→- **`yarn start:test`** - Start test client with token server (no Docker)\n   321→- **`yarn stop`** - Stop Docker container and close all OfficeAgent terminal windows\n   322→- **`yarn reload`** - Hot reload: copy built files to running container and restart\n   323→\n   324→### Code Quality\n   325→- **`yarn lint`** - Run ESLint on all TypeScript files across workspaces\n   326→- **`yarn lint:fix`** - Auto-fix ESLint issues where possible\n   327→\n   328→## Contributing\n   329→\n   330→PRs welcome! Keep scope tight and dependencies lean.\n   331→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"98ef6066-2367-415b-b616-f95ed64be17a","uuid":"5d963ff9-aadb-4905-bbc9-8fe2a4d8b442","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"C:/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/README.md","content":"# Office Agent\n\nAgent in a container, built for Office scenarios.\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- **[Node.js](https://nodejs.org/en) >= v20** — recommend using [nvm-windows](https://github.com/coreybutler/nvm-windows) (with `nvm install lts`)\n- **[Python](https://www.python.org/downloads/) >= 3.8** — for evaluation framework and testing tools (Python 3.12 recommended for msal[broker] support)\n- **[.NET SDK](https://dotnet.microsoft.com/download) >= 8.0.416** — required by global.json\n- [**Docker Desktop**](https://docs.docker.com/desktop/setup/install/windows-install/)\n- [**Visual Studio Code**](https://code.visualstudio.com/)\n\n## Quick Start\n\n> **Note**: Only Node.js and Python are required upfront. All other tools are installed automatically.\n\nRun the automated setup to configure your development environment:\n\n```bash\nnpm run setup\n```\n\nThis will:\n- Install global tools (Yarn, vsts-npm-auth)\n- Install Node.js dependencies\n- Create Python virtual environment and install packages\n- Install VS Code extensions (ESLint, EditorConfig, Python)\n- Configure Git settings\n\n> **Python Note**: VS Code automatically detects the `./venv` virtual environment. For terminal Python work, activate it with `.\\venv\\Scripts\\Activate.ps1` (Windows) or `source venv/bin/activate` (Mac/Linux).\n\n### Build\n\n> **Warning**: Docker Desktop must be running before executing `yarn build`. The build will fail if Docker is stopped.\n\n```bash\nyarn build\n```\n\n### Test\n```bash\nyarn test               # Runs both Jest (TypeScript/JavaScript) and pytest (Python) tests\n```\n\nTests include:\n- **Jest**: TypeScript/JavaScript unit tests with coverage\n- **pytest**: Python unit tests with coverage (see [Python Testing](docs/PYTHON_TESTING.md))\n- Coverage reports generated only in CI/CD (when `TF_BUILD` is set)\n\n### Run\n\nStart the Docker container:\n\n```bash\nyarn start              # Start Docker container and test client (no AugLoop required)\n```\n\nStart the Docker Compose\n```bash\nyarn start:compose\n```\n\nStop the Docker container:\n\n```bash\nyarn stop               # Stops and removes the OfficeAgent1 container\n```\n\nSee the [Available Scripts](#available-scripts) section for the complete list of Docker operations.\n\n## Development\n\n### Hot Reload\n\nFor faster iteration during development, use hot reload to deploy code changes without rebuilding the Docker image:\n\n```bash\nyarn reload             # Build your code changes and copy built files to running container and restart\n```\n\nThis updates `api/dist/` and `skills/` in the running container in seconds instead of minutes.\n\n> **Note**: If you modify Dockerfile, package.json dependencies, or other infrastructure files, run `yarn build` to rebuild the full Docker image.\n\n### Smoke Tests\n\n```bash\n# Health check\noagent ping\n\n# Generate a document (this will take a while)\noagent generate \"Create a simple document about cats\" -o ./myfile.docx\n```\n\nFor direct API testing, you can use curl:\n\n```bash\n# Health check\ncurl http://localhost:6010/health\n\n# Create a document (this will take a while)\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:6010/generateDocument -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"userQuery\": \"Create a simple document about cats\"}'\n\n# Create a PowerPoint with custom image variant (use v1 for presentai, gptv for GPT-V)\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:6010/generateDocument -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"userQuery\": \"Create a presentation about AI\", \"customImage\": \"v1\"}'\n\n# Download the file (fill in path from response above)\ncurl --output myfile.docx http://localhost:6010/download?filePath=path/to/myfile.docx\n```\n\n### Package Management\nBuildtime package management is handled by Yarn, with a workspace setup, with a _package.json_ and _yarn.lock_ at the root, and a _package.json_ inside each workspace.\nRuntime package management, inside the container, is covered by\n#### NPM:\nUse command like `npm install react-dom@19.2.1 --force --ignore-scripts` inside _/docker/_ to update\n- _/docker/package.json_\n- _/docker/package-lock.json_\n#### PIP & TDNF\n- _/docker/Dockerfile_\n\n### Debugging API Server\n\nAfter starting Docker:\n1. In VS Code, 'Run and Debug' view, run 'Attach - OfficeAgent API - Docker'\n2. Set breakpoints in your TS files and trigger code execution through a request\n\nNote, you can not currently attach to skills JS executions triggered by Claude, which are happening in different processes.\n![Screenshot of VS Code debugging session showing breakpoints set in TypeScript files and active debugging controls](./docs/images/debugging.png)\n\n### Testing with AugLoop\n\n1. Start the Docker container **without** the test client\n    ```bash\n    yarn start:docker\n    ```\n1. In your `augloop-workflow` repo:\n   ```bash\n   set OFFICE_AGENT_LOCAL_API=true\n   augloop run office-agent -rdw -d\n   ```\n1. Open http://localhost:8989\n1. Send the request\n\n### Testing in Office Agent Copilot (DA)\n\n## Skills\n\n- **DOCX**: Pack/unpack, schema validation (ISO/ECMA), offline OOXML schemas\n- **PPTX**: OOXML operations, slide management, template processing, thumbnails, HTML→PPTX conversion\n- **PDF**: Form field detection/extraction/filling, annotations, image conversion, bounding boxes\n- **XLSX**: Lightweight recalculation helper\n- **Utils**: Enterprise search helper\n\n## Architecture\n\nThe API server includes a modular WebSocket routing system:\n- **LLM API Proxy** — route LLM API calls through WebSocket\n- **MCP Support** — Model Context Protocol message routing\n- **Extensible Handlers** — add new protocol handlers easily\n\nSee [`modules/api/websocket/README.md`](modules/api/websocket/README.md) for details.\n\n### Test Client\n\nFor self-contained testing, we provide a test client that fulfills WebSocket requests from the container. This is automatically launched when you run `yarn start` (or run `yarn start:test` to only launch the test client).\n\nSee [`.devtools/test-client/README.md`](.devtools/test-client/README.md) for details.\n\n### CLI Tool\n\nThe Office Agent CLI provides a polished command-line interface for interacting with the API. You must run `yarn build` and `yarn start` before using the CLI.\n\n```bash\n# Check API health\noagent ping\noagent ping --json\n\n# Generate documents\noagent gen \"Create a simple document about cats\" -o ./myfile.docx\noagent gen \"10-slide presentation about AI\" --open\n\n# Generate with custom image variants (for PPTX)\noagent gen \"Create a simple deck about cats\" -c v1        # Use presentai variant\noagent gen \"Create a simple deck about cats\" -c gptv      # Use GPT-V variant\n\n# Generate with flight flags for feature testing\noagent gen \"Create a simple deck about cats\" -f flight1 flight2 flight3\n\n# Generate with message annotations\n# ✅ RECOMMENDED: Use file-based annotations (no escaping issues!)\noagent gen \"Summarize this file\" --message-annotations-file ./examples/message-annotations.json\n\n# Alternative: Inline JSON (requires careful shell escaping)\noagent gen \"Summarize\" -ma '[{\"id\":\"SPO_123\",\"queryAnnotationType\":\"File\",\"text\":\"report.docx\"}]'\n\n# 🎯 AUTO-DETECTION: Simply paste SharePoint/OneDrive URLs directly!\noagent gen \"Summarize https://microsoft-my.sharepoint-df.com/:w:/r/personal/vishalc_microsoft_com/_layouts/15/Doc.aspx?sourcedoc={DBB290D3-436E-4954-A893-CF1A8381F057}&file=GPT-5 Strategy for WXP Agents.docx\"\noagent gen \"Compare these files: https://contoso.sharepoint.com/:x:/Q1-Sales.xlsx and https://contoso.sharepoint.com/:x:/Q2-Sales.xlsx\"\n\n# Return async (don't wait for completion)\noagent gen \"Large presentation\" -ra\n\n# Generate with automatic report generation from debug.zip\noagent gen \"Create a deck about Project Nova. Don't ask any clarification questions. Just go ahead!\" -r\n\n# Generate with no enterprise search grounding\noagent gen \"Create a simple document about cats\" --disable-enterprise-search\n\n# Generate with no web search grounding\noagent gen \"Create a simple document about cats\" --disable-web-search\n\n# Configuration (stored in .env at repo root)\noagent config set apiUrl http://localhost:6010\noagent config set flights flag1,flag2       # Set default flight flags\noagent config get\noagent config path                           # Show config file location\noagent config reset\n\n# Evaluation framework\noagent eval submit --prompt \"Create a sales report with Q4 data. Don't ask any clarification questions. Just go ahead!\" --type pptx # Submit single evaluation\noagent eval run --batch eval/datasets/official_pairwise_officeagent_societas.json # Run batch evaluations\n```\n\n**Available Commands:**\n- `ping` - Health check with optional JSON output\n- `generate|gen` - Generate documents with AI (supports: document type hints, grounding content, flight flags, async mode)\n- `download|dl` - Download generated files\n- `config` - Manage configuration stored in .env files (get, set, reset, path)\n- `eval` - Evaluation framework for testing and quality assessment\n\n**Configuration:**\nSettings are stored in `.env` file at the repository root with `OAGENT_` prefix. Copy from `.env.example`. Output files are saved to `<repo-root>/output` by default.\n\n**Get Help:**\n```bash\noagent -h              # Show all available commands\noagent <command> -h    # Show options for a specific command\n```\n\nSee [`.devtools/cli/README.md`](.devtools/cli/README.md) for details.\n\n**Testing with MSA/Custom users via OAgent**\n_See [Local Testing With Token Server](https://eng.ms/docs/experiences-devices/opg/office-ai/augloop-ai-platform/augmentation-loop/documentation/authentication/local-testing-with-token-server#use-multiple-users-or-custom-users) for detailed instructions._\n1. Update Token Server settings to specify your user id in 'Defaults' from _me_.\n\n`<repo-root>\\node_modules\\@augloop-tools\\token-server\\dist\\exe\\settings.json`\n```\n\"Defaults\": {\n      \"UserId\": \"mstest_<user>@outlook.com\",\n}\n```\n2. Login with token server:\n`<repo_root>\\node_modules\\@augloop-tools\\token-server\\dist\\exe\\TokenServer.exe login -u \"mstest_<user>@outlook.com\"`\n3. Call via _oagent_. When testing _MSA_ pass `--disable-enterprise-search` to disable enterprise search (which would otherwise fail)\n\n**Evaluation Framework:**\n\nThe eval framework provides automated testing and quality assessment for OfficeAgent. See [`eval/README.md`](eval/README.md) for complete documentation.\n\n## Custom Image Variants\n\nThe API supports custom skill variants for different document generation approaches.\n\n### Available Variants\n\n- **`v1`** - Uses the Archetypes variant (`pptx_archetypes`)\n- **`gptv`** - Uses the GPT-V variant (`pptx_gptv`)\n- **Default (no flag)** - Uses the standard variant (`pptx`)\n\n### Usage\n\n**Via API:**\n```bash\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:6010/generateDocument \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"userQuery\": \"Create a presentation about AI\",\n    \"customImage\": \"v1\"\n  }'\n```\n\n**Via CLI:**\n```bash\noagent gen \"AI presentation\" -c v1    # PresentAI variant\noagent gen \"AI presentation\" -c gptv  # GPT-V variant\n```\n\n### How It Works\n\nWhen a `customImage` flag is provided:\n1. The system identifies the appropriate skill variant directory\n2. It replaces the default skill implementation with the custom variant\n3. The document is generated using the custom variant's logic\n\nWhen no flag is provided, alternative variant directories are automatically cleaned up to use only the default implementation.\n\n## Extending\n\nCreate `skills/<name>/` with:\n- `SKILL.md` — skill documentation\n- `scripts/` — single-purpose scripts with minimal dependencies\n\n## Available Scripts\n\nThe project provides several scripts for development and deployment:\n\n### Setup & Authentication\n- **`npm run setup`** - Complete development environment setup (installs global tools, fetches auth token, installs dependencies, configures Git, installs VS Code extensions)\n- **`yarn fetch:token`** - Fetch NPM authentication token for Office npm feed (requires vsts-npm-auth)\n\n### Build & Clean\n- **`yarn build`** - Build bare minimum packages to run `yarn start`\n- **`yarn build:all`** - Build all workspaces and Docker image\n- **`yarn build:no-clean`** - Build bare minimum packages to run `yarn start`, without cleaning\n- **`yarn clean`** - Clean all build artifacts\n\n### Docker Operations\n- **`yarn start`** - Start Docker container and test client (no AugLoop required)\n- **`yarn start:docker`** - Start Docker container without test client (needs AugLoop enlistment)\n- **`yarn start:test`** - Start test client with token server (no Docker)\n- **`yarn stop`** - Stop Docker container and close all OfficeAgent terminal windows\n- **`yarn reload`** - Hot reload: copy built files to running container and restart\n\n### Code Quality\n- **`yarn lint`** - Run ESLint on all TypeScript files across workspaces\n- **`yarn lint:fix`** - Auto-fix ESLint issues where possible\n\n## Contributing\n\nPRs welcome! Keep scope tight and dependencies lean.\n","numLines":331,"startLine":1,"totalLines":331}}}
