{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01M7Z5o6d92Qfrx5LJXmrfxB","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Workspace Agent Design Document\n     2→\n     3→## Overview\n     4→\n     5→Design for a new **Workspace Agent** within OfficeAgent infrastructure. Handles workspace creation requests from AugLoop while maintaining complete isolation from CreateAgent document generation flow.\n     6→\n     7→The Workspace Agent generates **Office artifacts** including:\n     8→- **Reports** - Business reports, analysis summaries, executive briefings\n     9→- **Documents** - Word documents, memos, proposals\n    10→- **Presentations** - PowerPoint decks, pitch decks, training materials\n    11→- **Newsletters** - Internal communications, team updates\n    12→- **Blogs** - Blog posts, articles, thought leadership content\n    13→\n    14→The agent uses a **two-phase sub-agent architecture**:\n    15→1. **Planning Phase** (`@workspace-planner`) - Analyzes user intent, researches content, generates structured outline\n    16→2. **Generation Phase** (`@workspace-generator`) - Executes plan, generates artifact content\n    17→\n    18→## Architecture\n    19→\n    20→### Infrastructure Overview\n    21→\n    22→| Directory | Purpose |\n    23→|-----------|---------|\n    24→| `modules/api/` | Express server, WebSocket handling |\n    25→| `modules/core/` | BaseAgent, logging, WebSocket router |\n    26→| `modules/grounding/` | Enterprise search, image search, parsing |\n    27→| `modules/message-protocol/` | Message types, request/response structures |\n    28→| `agents/` | Individual agent implementations |\n    29→\n    30→### Workspace Agent Structure\n    31→\n    32→```\n    33→agents/workspace-agent/\n    34→├── src/\n    35→│   ├── index.ts\n    36→│   ├── workspace-agent.ts        # Main orchestrator (extends BaseAgent)\n    37→│   ├── registry.ts               # AgentRegistryConfig\n    38→│   ├── types.ts                  # Internal types\n    39→│   ├── utils.ts                  # Helpers (buildResponsePayload, sendWebSocketResponse)\n    40→│   │\n    41→│   ├── hooks/\n    42→│   │   ├── index.ts              # Hook exports\n    43→│   │   └── stage-hooks.ts        # PostToolUse hook for incremental responses\n    44→│   │\n    45→│   ├── skills/\n    46→│   │   └── workspace-setup/\n    47→│   │       ├── skill.md          # Main skill entry point\n    48→│   │       └── workflow_steps/\n    49→│   │           └── WORKFLOW.md   # Orchestration workflow\n    50→│   │\n    51→│   ├── subagents/\n    52→│   │   ├── workspace-planner.md  # Phase 1: Planning sub-agent\n    53→│   │   └── workspace-generator.md # Phase 2: Generation sub-agent\n    54→│   │\n    55→│   └── prompts/\n    56→│       └── system-prompt.md      # Orchestrator instructions\n    57→│\n    58→├── tests/\n    59→├── package.json\n    60→└── tsconfig.json\n    61→```\n    62→\n    63→### Existing Agents (Reference)\n    64→\n    65→| Agent ID | Message Type | Reference |\n    66→|----------|--------------|-----------|\n    67→| `create-agent` | `chat_request` | [agents/create-agent/src/create-agent.ts](../agents/create-agent/src/create-agent.ts) |\n    68→| `dw-paralegal-agent` | `paralegal_agent_request` | [agents/dw-paralegal-agent/](../agents/dw-paralegal-agent/) |\n    69→| `dw-marketer-agent` | `marketer_request` | [agents/dw-marketer-agent/](../agents/dw-marketer-agent/) |\n    70→| `dw-accountant-agent` | `accountant_request` | [agents/dw-accountant-agent/](../agents/dw-accountant-agent/) |\n    71→\n    72→## Request Flow\n    73→\n    74→```\n    75→AugLoop                          OfficeAgent Container\n    76→───────                          ─────────────────────\n    77→   │\n    78→   │  SessionInit { agentId: \"workspace-agent\" }\n    79→   ├──────────────────────────────────▶ SessionInitHandler\n    80→   │                                          │\n    81→   │                                          ▼\n    82→   │                                    AgentRegistry.getAgent(\"workspace-agent\")\n    83→   │                                          │\n    84→   │                                          ▼\n    85→   │                                    WorkspaceAgent.initialize()\n    86→   │                                    └── registers handlers for WorkspaceRequest\n    87→   │\n    88→   │  WorkspaceRequest { type: \"workspace_request\" }\n    89→   ├──────────────────────────────────▶ WorkspaceAgent.handleWorkspaceRequest()\n    90→   │                                          │\n    91→   │                                    ┌─────┴─────┐\n    92→   │                                    │  Phase 1  │\n    93→   │                                    │  Planning │\n    94→   │                                    └─────┬─────┘\n    95→   │                                          │ @workspace-planner\n    96→   │                                          │ └── writes workspace_plan.json\n    97→   │                                          │\n    98→   │◀─────────────────────────────────────────┤ PostToolUse hook fires\n    99→   │  WorkspaceResponse (partial)             │ └── sends plan with isPartial: true\n   100→   │  { state: \"generating\", isPartial: true }│\n   101→   │                                          ▼\n   102→   │                                    ┌─────────────┐\n   103→   │                                    │   Phase 2   │\n   104→   │                                    │ Generation  │\n   105→   │                                    └─────┬───────┘\n   106→   │                                          │ @workspace-generator\n   107→   │                                          │ └── reads plan, creates artifact.json\n   108→   │                                          ▼\n   109→   │◀────────────────────────────────── WorkspaceResponse (final)\n   110→   │                                    { state: \"complete\", isPartial: false }\n   111→```\n   112→\n   113→## Sub-Agent Architecture\n   114→\n   115→### Why Sub-Agents?\n   116→\n   117→| Factor | Benefit |\n   118→|--------|---------|\n   119→| **Isolation** | Planning failure doesn't affect generation; each phase can fail independently |\n   120→| **Parallelism** | Generator can spawn parallel file generation tasks |\n   121→| **Reusability** | Planner output (plan JSON) can be reviewed/modified before execution |\n   122→| **Follows Patterns** | Matches create-agent's `outline-generator` + `section-generator` approach |\n   123→\n   124→### Phase 1: Planning (`@workspace-planner`)\n   125→\n   126→**Purpose:** Analyze user query, research content via grounding, generate structured outline\n   127→\n   128→**Input:**\n   129→- User query (e.g., \"Create a quarterly sales report for Q4 2025\")\n   130→- Grounding content (enterprise search results, source documents)\n   131→\n   132→**Output:** `workspace_plan.json`\n   133→\n   134→```json\n   135→{\n   136→  \"artifactName\": \"Q4 2025 Sales Report\",\n   137→  \"artifactType\": \"report\",\n   138→  \"description\": \"Quarterly sales performance report with analysis and recommendations\",\n   139→  \"outline\": {\n   140→    \"sections\": [\n   141→      {\n   142→        \"id\": 1,\n   143→        \"title\": \"Executive Summary\",\n   144→        \"description\": \"High-level overview of Q4 performance\",\n   145→        \"contentType\": \"summary\"\n   146→      },\n   147→      {\n   148→        \"id\": 2,\n   149→        \"title\": \"Sales Performance\",\n   150→        \"description\": \"Detailed sales metrics and trends\",\n   151→        \"contentType\": \"analysis\",\n   152→        \"includeCharts\": true\n   153→      },\n   154→      {\n   155→        \"id\": 3,\n   156→        \"title\": \"Regional Breakdown\",\n   157→        \"description\": \"Performance by region\",\n   158→        \"contentType\": \"data-table\"\n   159→      },\n   160→      {\n   161→        \"id\": 4,\n   162→        \"title\": \"Recommendations\",\n   163→        \"description\": \"Strategic recommendations for Q1\",\n   164→        \"contentType\": \"recommendations\"\n   165→      }\n   166→    ]\n   167→  },\n   168→  \"style\": {\n   169→    \"tone\": \"professional\",\n   170→    \"audience\": \"executive\",\n   171→    \"length\": \"detailed\"\n   172→  },\n   173→  \"sources\": [\n   174→    { \"type\": \"grounding\", \"id\": \"sales-data-q4.xlsx\" },\n   175→    { \"type\": \"grounding\", \"id\": \"regional-summary.docx\" }\n   176→  ]\n   177→}\n   178→```\n   179→\n   180→**Tools Available:**\n   181→- `Read` - Read grounding content, source documents\n   182→- `Grep` - Search for relevant content\n   183→- `Glob` - Find source files\n   184→- `TodoWrite` - Track planning progress\n   185→- `EnterpriseSearch` - Search enterprise content\n   186→\n   187→### Phase 2: Generation (`@workspace-generator`)\n   188→\n   189→**Purpose:** Execute the plan, generate artifact content section by section\n   190→\n   191→**Input:** `workspace_plan.json`\n   192→\n   193→**Output:** Generated HTML content for web rendering\n   194→\n   195→**Process:**\n   196→1. Read `workspace_plan.json`\n   197→2. For each section in outline:\n   198→   - Generate content using Claude with grounding context\n   199→   - Apply style guidelines (tone, audience)\n   200→   - Include citations/references where applicable\n   201→3. Assemble sections into final artifact\n   202→4. Output as structured HTML for web experience\n   203→\n   204→**Tools Available:**\n   205→- `Read` - Read plan and grounding content\n   206→- `Write` - Write section content\n   207→- `Edit` / `MultiEdit` - Refine content\n   208→- `TodoWrite` - Track generation progress\n   209→\n   210→### File-Based Handoff\n   211→\n   212→```\n   213→workspace/\n   214→├── workspace_plan.json          # Written by @workspace-planner\n   215→├── section_contexts/            # Per-section context from grounding\n   216→│   ├── 01_executive_summary.json\n   217→│   ├── 02_sales_performance.json\n   218→│   └── ...\n   219→├── output/\n   220→│   ├── artifact.html            # Final rendered artifact\n   221→│   └── artifact.json            # Structured content for client\n   222→└── logs/\n   223→    └── generation_report.json   # Summary of generation\n   224→```\n   225→\n   226→## Agent Isolation\n   227→\n   228→| Factor | How it works |\n   229→|--------|--------------|\n   230→| `agentId` in SessionInit | Determines which agent's `initialize()` is called |\n   231→| `MessageType` | Each agent registers handlers for its own message types |\n   232→| Sub-agents | Spawned via `Task` tool, isolated execution per phase |\n   233→\n   234→The `wsRouter` is a **singleton**. Only the initialized agent's handlers are registered per session.\n   235→\n   236→**Key files:**\n   237→- [modules/api/src/websocket/handlers/session-init-handler.ts](../modules/api/src/websocket/handlers/session-init-handler.ts) - Agent selection\n   238→- [modules/core/src/agent/agent-manager.ts](../modules/core/src/agent/agent-manager.ts) - Single agent per session\n   239→- [modules/core/src/websocket/router.ts](../modules/core/src/websocket/router.ts) - Message routing\n   240→\n   241→## Implementation Steps\n   242→\n   243→### 1. Add Message Types ✅\n   244→\n   245→**File:** [modules/message-protocol/src/types/message-type.ts](../modules/message-protocol/src/types/message-type.ts)\n   246→\n   247→Add `WorkspaceRequest` and `WorkspaceResponse` to the `MessageType` enum.\n   248→\n   249→### 2. Create Workspace Agent Types ✅\n   250→\n   251→**File:** [modules/message-protocol/src/types/agents/workspace-agent/types.ts](../modules/message-protocol/src/types/agents/workspace-agent/types.ts)\n   252→\n   253→Types follow the same structure as CreateAgent (`types/agents/create-agent/`):\n   254→- `WorkspaceRequestPayload` - `userMessage: string` field\n   255→- `WorkspaceOptions` - configuration options\n   256→- `WorkspaceResponsePayload` - response with files list\n   257→- `WorkspaceFile` - file information\n   258→- `WorkspaceRequestMessage` / `WorkspaceResponseMessage`\n   259→\n   260→### 3. Create Agent Package ✅\n   261→\n   262→**Directory:** `agents/workspace-agent/`\n   263→\n   264→See [Workspace Agent Structure](#workspace-agent-structure) above.\n   265→\n   266→### 4. Register Agent ✅\n   267→\n   268→**File:** [modules/api/src/agents.ts](../modules/api/src/agents.ts)\n   269→\n   270→### 5. Create Sub-Agents 🔄 (In Progress)\n   271→\n   272→**Files to create:**\n   273→- `src/subagents/workspace-planner.md` - Planning sub-agent\n   274→- `src/subagents/workspace-generator.md` - Generation sub-agent\n   275→\n   276→### 6. Create Skill and Workflow 🔄 (In Progress)\n   277→\n   278→**Files to create:**\n   279→- `src/skills/workspace-setup/skill.md` - Main skill entry\n   280→- `src/skills/workspace-setup/workflow_steps/WORKFLOW.md` - Orchestration workflow\n   281→\n   282→### 7. Update Registry Configuration 🔄 (In Progress)\n   283→\n   284→Update `src/registry.ts` to include:\n   285→- Sub-agents: `['workspace-planner', 'workspace-generator']`\n   286→- Skills: `['workspace-setup']`\n   287→\n   288→## Reusable Modules\n   289→\n   290→| Module | Purpose | Exports |\n   291→|--------|---------|---------|\n   292→| `@officeagent/grounding` | Enterprise/image search | `parseGroundingContent`, `Orchestrator` |\n   293→| `@officeagent/core` | Infrastructure | `BaseAgent`, `SessionContext`, logging |\n   294→| `@officeagent/message-protocol` | Messages | `MessageType`, `Message` |\n   295→| `@officeagent/chain-of-thought` | CoT display | `initChainOfThought`, `trackChainOfThought` |\n   296→| `@officeagent/rai` | RAI validation | `validateContent` |\n   297→\n   298→**Reference:** [modules/grounding/src/index.ts](../modules/grounding/src/index.ts)\n   299→\n   300→## Supported Artifact Types\n   301→\n   302→The workspace agent generates the following artifact types, all rendered as a **web experience**:\n   303→\n   304→| Type | Description | Rendering |\n   305→|------|-------------|------------|\n   306→| `report` | Business reports, analysis summaries, executive briefings | HTML/Web |\n   307→| `document` | Memos, proposals, contracts | HTML/Web |\n   308→| `presentation` | Pitch decks, training materials | HTML/Web |\n   309→| `newsletter` | Internal communications, team updates | HTML/Web |\n   310→| `blog` | Blog posts, articles, thought leadership content | HTML/Web |\n   311→| `spreadsheet` | Data reports, financial summaries | HTML/Web |\n   312→\n   313→> **Note:** All artifacts are rendered as HTML for web-based display. The artifact type determines the content structure and styling, not the output file format.\n   314→\n   315→## AugLoop Message Format\n   316→\n   317→### SessionInit\n   318→```json\n   319→{\n   320→  \"type\": \"session_init\",\n   321→  \"payload\": {\n   322→    \"agentId\": \"workspace-agent\",\n   323→    \"conversationId\": \"...\"\n   324→  }\n   325→}\n   326→```\n   327→\n   328→### WorkspaceRequest\n   329→```json\n   330→{\n   331→  \"type\": \"workspace_request\",\n   332→  \"id\": \"request-id\",\n   333→  \"sessionId\": \"session-id\",\n   334→  \"payload\": {\n   335→    \"userMessage\": \"Create a quarterly sales report for Q4 2025 based on the attached data\",\n   336→    \"workspaceName\": \"Q4-Sales-Report\",\n   337→    \"workspaceType\": \"report\",\n   338→    \"options\": {\n   339→      \"tone\": \"professional\",\n   340→      \"audience\": \"executive\",\n   341→      \"includeCharts\": true\n   342→    },\n   343→    \"groundingContent\": [\"...\"]\n   344→  }\n   345→}\n   346→```\n   347→\n   348→### WorkspaceResponse (Partial - after planner)\n   349→```json\n   350→{\n   351→  \"type\": \"workspace_response\",\n   352→  \"id\": \"stage-generating\",\n   353→  \"sessionId\": \"session-id\",\n   354→  \"payload\": {\n   355→    \"success\": true,\n   356→    \"state\": \"generating\",\n   357→    \"isPartial\": true,\n   358→    \"artifacts\": [\n   359→      {\n   360→        \"title\": \"workspace_plan.json\",\n   361→        \"artifactType\": \"plan\",\n   362→        \"format\": \"json\",\n   363→        \"path\": \"workspace_plan.json\",\n   364→        \"size\": 2048,\n   365→        \"mimeType\": \"application/json\",\n   366→        \"content\": \"<base64-encoded JSON>\",\n   367→        \"order\": 1\n   368→      }\n   369→    ]\n   370→  }\n   371→}\n   372→```\n   373→\n   374→### WorkspaceResponse (Final - after generator)\n   375→```json\n   376→{\n   377→  \"type\": \"workspace_response\",\n   378→  \"id\": \"request-id\",\n   379→  \"sessionId\": \"session-id\",\n   380→  \"payload\": {\n   381→    \"success\": true,\n   382→    \"state\": \"complete\",\n   383→    \"isPartial\": false,\n   384→    \"workspaceName\": \"workspace-abc123\",\n   385→    \"message\": \"Artifact generated successfully with 4 sections\",\n   386→    \"artifacts\": [\n   387→      {\n   388→        \"title\": \"Q4 2025 Sales Report\",\n   389→        \"artifactType\": \"report\",\n   390→        \"format\": \"json\",\n   391→        \"path\": \"artifact.json\",\n   392→        \"size\": 15420,\n   393→        \"mimeType\": \"application/json\",\n   394→        \"content\": \"<base64-encoded JSON>\",\n   395→        \"order\": 2\n   396→      }\n   397→    ],\n   398→    \"artifact\": {\n   399→      \"type\": \"report\",\n   400→      \"title\": \"Q4 2025 Sales Report\",\n   401→      \"sections\": [\n   402→        { \"id\": 1, \"title\": \"Executive Summary\", \"content\": \"<div>...</div>\" }\n   403→      ],\n   404→      \"style\": { \"tone\": \"professional\", \"audience\": \"executive\" }\n   405→    }\n   406→  }\n   407→}\n   408→```\n   409→\n   410→> **Note:** Plan is NOT included in the final response — it was already sent as a partial response when the planner completed.\n   411→\n   412→### Incremental Response Flow\n   413→\n   414→The agent sends responses incrementally as each sub-agent completes:\n   415→\n   416→| Response | `isPartial` | `state` | Contains |\n   417→|----------|-------------|---------|----------|\n   418→| After planner | `true` | `generating` | Plan artifact (order: 1) |\n   419→| Final | `false` | `complete` | Artifact (order: 2) |\n   420→\n   421→This allows clients to display progress (e.g., show plan outline) while generation continues.\n   422→\n   423→### Artifacts Array\n   424→\n   425→Artifacts are sent across multiple responses:\n   426→\n   427→| Order | Type | Path | Sent In |\n   428→|-------|------|------|----------|\n   429→| 1 | `plan` | `workspace_plan.json` | Partial response (isPartial: true) |\n   430→| 2 | `report`/`blog`/etc. | `artifact.json` | Final response (isPartial: false) |\n   431→\n   432→**Client processing:** Handle `isPartial: true` responses as progress updates; accumulate artifacts. When `isPartial: false` arrives, the workflow is complete.\n   433→\n   434→## Local Testing\n   435→\n   436→Set in `.env`:\n   437→```\n   438→OAGENT_AGENTID=workspace-agent\n   439→```\n   440→\n   441→## Logging\n   442→\n   443→Follow [.github/copilot-instructions.md](../.github/copilot-instructions.md) - never log user content to telemetry.\n   444→\n   445→## Checklist\n   446→\n   447→### Core Implementation ✅\n   448→- [x] Add `WorkspaceRequest`/`WorkspaceResponse` to `MessageType` enum\n   449→- [x] Create `types/agents/workspace-agent/types.ts` (follows CreateAgent pattern)\n   450→- [x] Export workspace types from `message-protocol/src/index.ts`\n   451→- [x] Create `agents/workspace-agent/` package\n   452→- [x] Implement `WorkspaceAgent` extending `BaseAgent`\n   453→- [x] Register in `modules/api/src/agents.ts`\n   454→- [x] Write unit tests\n   455→\n   456→### Sub-Agent Architecture ✅\n   457→- [x] Create `@workspace-planner` sub-agent (`src/prompts/1.0.0/subagents/workspace-planner.md`)\n   458→- [x] Create `@workspace-generator` sub-agent (`src/prompts/1.0.0/subagents/workspace-generator.md`)\n   459→- [x] Claude SDK integration with Task tool delegation\n   460→- [x] System prompt with EJS templating\n   461→- [x] Wire format with `artifacts` array and `order` field\n   462→- [x] Add `plan` artifact type to `WorkspaceArtifactType` enum\n   463→- [x] CLI command (`oagent workspace`)\n   464→- [x] Incremental responses via PostToolUse hooks (`src/hooks/stage-hooks.ts`)\n   465→- [x] `isPartial` and `state` fields in WorkspaceResponsePayload\n   466→\n   467→### Future Enhancements\n   468→- [ ] Workspace plan JSON schema validation\n   469→- [ ] Enterprise grounding integration\n   470→- [ ] Multi-artifact generation (multiple files per workspace)\n   471→\n   472→## Key References\n   473→\n   474→| File | Purpose |\n   475→|------|---------|\n   476→| [agents/workspace-agent/src/workspace-agent.ts](../agents/workspace-agent/src/workspace-agent.ts) | Main orchestrator |\n   477→| [agents/workspace-agent/src/registry.ts](../agents/workspace-agent/src/registry.ts) | Agent configuration |\n   478→| [agents/workspace-agent/src/utils.ts](../agents/workspace-agent/src/utils.ts) | Helpers (buildResponsePayload, renderPrompt) |\n   479→| [agents/workspace-agent/src/prompts/1.0.0/system-prompt.md](../agents/workspace-agent/src/prompts/1.0.0/system-prompt.md) | System prompt (EJS) |\n   480→| [agents/workspace-agent/src/prompts/1.0.0/subagents/workspace-planner.md](../agents/workspace-agent/src/prompts/1.0.0/subagents/workspace-planner.md) | Planning sub-agent |\n   481→| [agents/workspace-agent/src/prompts/1.0.0/subagents/workspace-generator.md](../agents/workspace-agent/src/prompts/1.0.0/subagents/workspace-generator.md) | Generation sub-agent |\n   482→| [agents/workspace-agent/src/hooks/stage-hooks.ts](../agents/workspace-agent/src/hooks/stage-hooks.ts) | PostToolUse hook for incremental responses |\n   483→| [modules/message-protocol/src/types/agents/workspace-agent/types.ts](../modules/message-protocol/src/types/agents/workspace-agent/types.ts) | Public types (WorkspaceArtifactType, GeneratedArtifact) |\n   484→| [modules/core/src/agent/base-agent.ts](../modules/core/src/agent/base-agent.ts) | Base class to extend |\n   485→| [.devtools/cli/src/commands/workspace.ts](../.devtools/cli/src/commands/workspace.ts) | CLI command |\n   486→| [agents/create-agent/](../agents/create-agent/) | Reference implementation |\n   487→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JFxuCnY2KejKQcmVMsFzvh","session_id":"98ef6066-2367-415b-b616-f95ed64be17a","uuid":"388a1c2e-e2fc-4b25-b096-54053b4834a0"}
