{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Em4z7axwZxFpiwmz8ErXGj","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Office Agent CLI\n     2→\n     3→A polished command-line interface for interacting with the Office Agent API. Generate Office documents (DOCX, PPTX, XLSX) with AI-powered natural language commands.\n     4→\n     5→## Installation & Setup\n     6→\n     7→The CLI is part of the OfficeAgent workspace. To use it:\n     8→\n     9→1. **Build the CLI** (first time or after changes):\n    10→   ```bash\n    11→   cd .devtools/cli\n    12→   yarn build\n    13→   ```\n    14→   This will compile TypeScript and automatically register the `oagent` command globally.\n    15→\n    16→2. **Use the CLI** from anywhere:\n    17→   ```bash\n    18→   # Use directly (after build registers it globally)\n    19→   oagent [command]\n    20→\n    21→   # Or use via yarn from repo root\n    22→   yarn oagent [command]\n    23→   ```\n    24→\n    25→## Quick Start\n    26→\n    27→```bash\n    28→# Build the CLI first\n    29→cd .devtools/cli\n    30→yarn build\n    31→\n    32→# Check if the API is running\n    33→oagent ping\n    34→\n    35→# Generate a document\n    36→oagent generate \"Create a report about Q4 sales performance\"\n    37→```\n    38→\n    39→## Commands\n    40→\n    41→### `ping` - Health Check\n    42→\n    43→Check if the Office Agent API is running.\n    44→\n    45→```bash\n    46→oagent ping\n    47→oagent ping --json\n    48→```\n    49→\n    50→**Options:**\n    51→- `-j, --json` - Output raw JSON response\n    52→- `-t, --timeout <ms>` - Request timeout in milliseconds (default: \"5000\")\n    53→\n    54→### `generate` - Generate Document\n    55→\n    56→Generate an Office document using AI.\n    57→\n    58→```bash\n    59→oagent generate <query> [options]\n    60→# or use the alias\n    61→oagent gen <query> [options]\n    62→```\n    63→\n    64→**Arguments:**\n    65→- `<query>` - Natural language description of the document\n    66→\n    67→**Options:**\n    68→- `-o, --output <path>` - Output file path (default: auto-generated in configured output directory)\n    69→- `-i, --id <conversationId>` - Conversation ID for tracking\n    70→- `-c, --custom-image <flag>` - Custom image flag (e.g., v1 for presentai, gptv for GPT-V)\n    71→- `-t, --document-type <type>` - Document type hint (optional: e.g., presentation, spreadsheet, document)\n    72→- `-g, --grounding-content <content>` - Additional context or grounding content\n    73→- `-f, --flights <flights...>` - Flight flags (space-separated list). **Note:** Use `ExcelDownload` flight to enable Excel file download to output folder\n    74→- `-ra, --return-async` - Return immediately without waiting for completion\n    75→- `--open` - Automatically open the file after download\n    76→- `--no-download` - Skip downloading files (both document and debug.zip)\n    77→- `-r, --report` - Extract debug.zip and automatically run report generation scripts from `reports/*/scripts/generate_report.py`\n    78→- `--verbose` - Show detailed output\n    79→- `-ma, --message-annotations <string>` - Message annotations as JSON string (⚠️ requires careful shell escaping)\n    80→- `-maf, --message-annotations-file <path>` - Path to JSON file containing message annotations (✅ **recommended** - avoids escaping issues)\n    81→\n    82→**Examples:**\n    83→```bash\n    84→# Generate a Word document\n    85→oagent generate \"Create a business proposal for a software project\"\n    86→\n    87→# Generate and open PowerPoint\n    88→oagent gen \"10-slide presentation about climate change\" --open\n    89→\n    90→# Generate without downloading\n    91→oagent gen \"Financial spreadsheet with Q1-Q4 data\" --no-download\n    92→\n    93→# Generate with custom image variant\n    94→oagent gen \"AI presentation\" --custom-image v1 --open\n    95→\n    96→# Specify output path\n    97→oagent gen \"Summary of project milestones\" -o ./reports/milestones.docx\n    98→\n    99→# With document type hint\n   100→oagent gen \"Sales report for Q4\" -t spreadsheet\n   101→\n   102→# Generate Excel file with download enabled (requires ExcelDownload flight)\n   103→oagent gen \"Financial model with projections\" -t spreadsheet -f ExcelDownload\n   104→\n   105→# With grounding content for additional context\n   106→oagent gen \"Summary report\" -g \"Based on the attached financial data from fiscal year 2024\"\n   107→\n   108→# With flight flags for feature testing\n   109→oagent gen \"Create a simple deck about cats\" -f flag1 flag2 flag3\n   110→\n   111→# Generate with automatic report generation from debug.zip\n   112→oagent gen \"Create a simple deck about cats\" --report\n   113→\n   114→# Short form for report generation\n   115→oagent gen \"Create a simple deck about cats\" -r\n   116→\n   117→# Return async (don't wait for completion)\n   118→oagent gen \"Create a large presentation with 50 slides about dogs\" -ra\n   119→\n   120→# Combined options\n   121→oagent gen \"Create a simple deck about cats\" -t document -g \"Include latest GPT-4 findings\" -f experimental-feature --open\n   122→\n   123→# ✅ RECOMMENDED: Use file-based message annotations (no escaping issues!)\n   124→oagent gen \"Summarize this file\" --message-annotations-file ./examples/message-annotations.json\n   125→\n   126→# Alternative: Inline JSON (requires careful shell escaping)\n   127→# PowerShell: Use single quotes and escape inner quotes\n   128→oagent gen \"Summarize\" -ma '[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"SPO_123\\\",\\\"queryAnnotationType\\\":\\\"File\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"report.docx\\\"}]'\n   129→\n   130→# 🎯 AUTO-DETECTION: Simply paste SharePoint/OneDrive URLs directly in the query!\n   131→oagent gen \"Summarize this file https://microsoft-my.sharepoint-df.com/:w:/r/personal/vishalc_microsoft_com/_layouts/15/Doc.aspx?sourcedoc={DBB290D3-436E-4954-A893-CF1A8381F057}&file=GPT-5 Strategy for WXP Agents.docx\"\n   132→\n   133→# URLs are automatically detected and converted to message annotations\n   134→oagent gen \"Compare these files: https://contoso.sharepoint.com/:x:/file1.xlsx and https://contoso.sharepoint.com/:w:/file2.docx\"\n   135→```\n   136→\n   137→#### URL Auto-Detection (New! 🎉)\n   138→\n   139→The CLI now **automatically detects URLs** in your query and converts them to message annotations. Simply paste SharePoint or OneDrive URLs directly in your command - no JSON formatting needed!\n   140→\n   141→**How it works:**\n   142→1. Detects URLs in the query (SharePoint, OneDrive, or any HTTP/HTTPS link)\n   143→2. Extracts file name and type from the URL\n   144→3. Automatically creates message annotations\n   145→4. Merges with any explicitly provided annotations\n   146→\n   147→**Supported URL patterns:**\n   148→- SharePoint: `https://company.sharepoint.com/:w:/...` (Word)\n   149→- SharePoint: `https://company.sharepoint.com/:x:/...` (Excel)\n   150→- SharePoint: `https://company.sharepoint.com/:p:/...` (PowerPoint)\n   151→- OneDrive: `https://onedrive.live.com/...`\n   152→- Generic file URLs: `https://example.com/document.pdf`\n   153→\n   154→**Examples:**\n   155→\n   156→```bash\n   157→# Single file URL\n   158→oagent gen \"Summarize this document https://contoso.sharepoint.com/:w:/file.docx\"\n   159→\n   160→# Multiple URLs - both files will be auto-detected\n   161→oagent gen \"Compare these spreadsheets: https://contoso.sharepoint.com/:x:/sales.xlsx and https://contoso.sharepoint.com/:x:/forecast.xlsx\"\n   162→\n   163→# Full SharePoint URL from browser (just copy-paste!)\n   164→oagent gen \"Create a summary based on https://microsoft-my.sharepoint-df.com/:w:/r/personal/user_microsoft_com/_layouts/15/Doc.aspx?sourcedoc={ABC123}&file=Project%20Report.docx&action=default\"\n   165→\n   166→# Mix URLs with other content\n   167→oagent gen \"Create a presentation about the findings in https://sharepoint.com/research.docx and include charts\"\n   168→```\n   169→\n   170→**What gets auto-detected:**\n   171→- **File name**: Extracted from URL (e.g., \"GPT-5 Strategy for WXP Agents.docx\")\n   172→- **File type**: Detected from extension (docx, xlsx, pptx, pdf, etc.)\n   173→- **Annotation type**: \"File\" for documents, \"External\" for web links\n   174→\n   175→**Priority:** Auto-detected URLs are merged with explicit annotations. If you provide the same file in both the URL and via `--message-annotations-file`, the explicit annotation takes priority.\n   176→\n   177→#### Message Annotations\n   178→\n   179→Message annotations provide context about user-attached entities (files, emails, meetings) for enterprise search and document generation.\n   180→\n   181→**File Format (`message-annotations.json`):**\n   182→```json\n   183→[\n   184→  {\n   185→    \"id\": \"SPO_MDhmNDE4NDctNmNm\",\n   186→    \"queryAnnotationType\": \"File\",\n   187→    \"text\": \"Q4 Financial Report.xlsx\"\n   188→  },\n   189→  {\n   190→    \"id\": \"user@microsoft.com\",\n   191→    \"queryAnnotationType\": \"Email\",\n   192→    \"text\": \"Meeting notes from John\"\n   193→  },\n   194→  {\n   195→    \"id\": \"MTG_abc123def456\",\n   196→    \"queryAnnotationType\": \"Meeting\",\n   197→    \"text\": \"Q4 Planning Meeting\"\n   198→  }\n   199→]\n   200→```\n   201→\n   202→**Supported Annotation Types:**\n   203→- `File` - SharePoint/OneDrive files\n   204→- `Email` - Email messages\n   205→- `Meeting` - Calendar meetings\n   206→- `Chat` - Teams chat messages\n   207→- `Transcript` - Meeting transcripts\n   208→- `People` - User profiles\n   209→\n   210→**💡 Best Practice:** Use `--message-annotations-file` instead of `-ma` to avoid complex shell escaping issues with JSON strings.\n   211→\n   212→**Note:** When downloading is enabled (default), both the document and a `*.debug.zip` file containing logs and workspace files are automatically downloaded. Use `--no-download` to skip both files.\n   213→\n   214→**Report Generation:** When using the `--report` flag, the CLI will:\n   215→1. Download and extract the `debug.zip` file to a folder named `<filename>_extracted`\n   216→2. Automatically discover all `generate_report.py` scripts in `reports/*/scripts/` directories\n   217→3. Run each report script with the extracted folder as input\n   218→4. Generate comprehensive analysis reports (e.g., enterprise grounding analysis)\n   219→\n   220→This is useful for automatically generating diagnostic and performance reports after document generation.\n   221→\n   222→### `download` - Download Document\n   223→\n   224→Download a previously generated document.\n   225→\n   226→```bash\n   227→oagent download <filePath> [options]\n   228→# or use the alias\n   229→oagent dl <filePath> [options]\n   230→```\n   231→\n   232→**Arguments:**\n   233→- `<filePath>` - Server file path (returned from generate command)\n   234→\n   235→**Options:**\n   236→- `-o, --output <path>` - Output file path (default: current directory)\n   237→- `--open` - Automatically open the file after download\n   238→- `--no-debug-zip` - Skip downloading the debug.zip file\n   239→- `--verbose` - Show detailed output\n   240→\n   241→**Examples:**\n   242→```bash\n   243→oagent download \"abc123/def456/report.docx\"\n   244→oagent dl \"abc123/def456/report.docx\" --open -o ./my-report.docx\n   245→\n   246→# Skip downloading debug.zip\n   247→oagent dl \"abc123/def456/presentation.pptx\" --no-debug-zip\n   248→```\n   249→\n   250→**Note:** The download command automatically downloads both the document and a `*.debug.zip` file containing logs and workspace files. Use `--no-debug-zip` to skip the debug file.\n   251→\n   252→### `new-agent` - Scaffold a New Agent\n   253→\n   254→Scaffold a new agent package with all the boilerplate wired up and ready to build.\n   255→\n   256→```bash\n   257→oagent new-agent <name> [options]\n   258→```\n   259→\n   260→**Arguments:**\n   261→- `<name>` - Agent name in kebab-case (e.g. `my-new-agent`)\n   262→\n   263→**Options:**\n   264→- `--preset <preset>` - Capability preset (default: `DOCUMENT_GENERATION_ENTERPRISE_GROUNDING`)\n   265→\n   266→**Available presets:**\n   267→| Preset | Description |\n   268→|--------|-------------|\n   269→| `DOCUMENT_GENERATION` | Filesystem + shell + task/skill tools |\n   270→| `DOCUMENT_GENERATION_GROUNDING` | Above + web search |\n   271→| `DOCUMENT_GENERATION_ENTERPRISE` | Above + enterprise feature access |\n   272→| `DOCUMENT_GENERATION_ENTERPRISE_GROUNDING` | All of the above (default) |\n   273→| `ENTERPRISE` | Enterprise access only |\n   274→| `GROUNDING` | Web search only |\n   275→\n   276→**Examples:**\n   277→```bash\n   278→# Scaffold with the default preset\n   279→oagent new-agent my-new-agent\n   280→\n   281→# Scaffold with a specific preset\n   282→oagent new-agent my-new-agent --preset DOCUMENT_GENERATION\n   283→```\n   284→\n   285→This creates `agents/my-new-agent/` with a full agent skeleton: registry, main agent class, constants, system prompt, and build config. See [docs/ONBOARDING.md](../../docs/ONBOARDING.md) for next steps after scaffolding.\n   286→\n   287→### `config` - Configuration Management\n   288→\n   289→Manage CLI configuration settings. Configuration is stored in `.env` files using environment variables with the `OAGENT_` prefix.\n   290→\n   291→```bash\n   292→# View all configuration\n   293→oagent config get\n   294→\n   295→# Get specific value\n   296→oagent config get apiUrl\n   297→\n   298→# Set a value (saves to .env file)\n   299→oagent config set apiUrl http://localhost:6010\n   300→oagent config set timeout 1800000\n   301→oagent config set autoOpen true\n   302→oagent config set flights flag1,flag2,flag3\n   303→\n   304→# Show config file path\n   305→oagent config path\n   306→\n   307→# Reset to defaults\n   308→oagent config reset\n   309→```\n   310→\n   311→**Configuration Keys:**\n   312→- `apiUrl` - API server URL (default: `http://localhost:6010`)\n   313→- `timeout` - Request timeout in milliseconds (default: `1800000` - 30 minutes)\n   314→- `outputDir` - Default download directory (default: `<repo-root>/output`)\n   315→- `autoOpen` - Auto-open files after download (default: `false`)\n   316→- `flights` - Default flight flags (comma-separated, e.g., `flag1,flag2`)\n   317→\n   318→**Configuration File Location:**\n   319→- `.env` in the repository root (OfficeAgent directory)\n   320→- The CLI automatically finds the repo root and uses `.env` there\n   321→\n   322→**Environment Variables:**\n   323→You can also set configuration via environment variables:\n   324→```bash\n   325→OAGENT_API_URL=http://localhost:6010\n   326→OAGENT_TIMEOUT=1800000\n   327→OAGENT_OUTPUT_DIR=/path/to/output\n   328→OAGENT_AUTO_OPEN=true\n   329→OAGENT_FLIGHTS=flag1,flag2,flag3\n   330→```\n   331→\n   332→## Usage Examples\n   333→\n   334→### Basic Workflow\n   335→\n   336→```bash\n   337→## Examples\n   338→\n   339→## Usage Examples\n   340→\n   341→### Basic Workflow\n   342→\n   343→```bash\n   344→# 1. Check API health\n   345→oagent ping\n   346→\n   347→# 2. Generate a document\n   348→oagent generate \"Create a project proposal\"\n   349→\n   350→# 3. The file path is returned, download it\n   351→oagent download \"path/from/response.docx\" --open\n   352→```\n   353→\n   354→### Advanced Usage\n   355→\n   356→```bash\n   357→# Generate with custom conversation ID\n   358→oagent gen \"Quarterly business review\" -i \"Q4-2024-review\"\n   359→\n   360→# Generate without downloading\n   361→oagent gen \"Sales data analysis\" --no-download\n   362→\n   363→# Configure for auto-open\n   364→oagent config set autoOpen true\n   365→\n   366→# Now all downloads open automatically\n   367→oagent gen \"Product roadmap 2025\"\n   368→```\n   369→\n   370→## Command Aliases\n   371→\n   372→The CLI supports short aliases for convenience:\n   373→\n   374→- `generate` → `gen`\n   375→- `download` → `dl`\n   376→\n   377→## Configuration\n   378→\n   379→Configuration is stored in `~/.oagent/config.json` and persists across sessions.\n   380→\n   381→### Default Configuration\n   382→\n   383→```json\n   384→{\n   385→  \"apiUrl\": \"http://localhost:6010\",\n   386→  \"timeout\": 1800000,\n   387→  \"outputDir\": \"~/Documents/OfficeAgent\",\n   388→  \"autoOpen\": false\n   389→}\n   390→```\n   391→\n   392→## Features\n   393→\n   394→- **Fast and efficient** - Configurable timeouts and progress indicators\n   395→- **User-friendly** - Colorful output with helpful error messages\n   396→- **Flexible** - Multiple output options and configurable defaults\n   397→- **Reliable** - Proper error handling and exit code support for scripting\n   398→\n   399→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JFxuCnY2KejKQcmVMsFzvh","session_id":"98ef6066-2367-415b-b616-f95ed64be17a","uuid":"459b1fa4-31d0-4cf9-8410-ddfc527fc3b8"}
