{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_0152Kke9cttug1iqDcFSVbPY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_011yE4qmLYtecYxAVh6biFqZ","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/.devtools/e2e-tests/README.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":397,"cache_read_input_tokens":46804,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":397,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JFxuCnY2KejKQcmVMsFzvh","session_id":"98ef6066-2367-415b-b616-f95ed64be17a","uuid":"987e2fe3-99f5-44e6-9986-618c8b42ae1d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01N8k8rjrUFEt8aYnY9HaXN3","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# LLM Test Client for WebSocket Relay\n     2→\n     3→This test client connects to the WebSocket server and acts as an external LLM client that can handle requests and forward them to the actual Anthropic API.\n     4→\n     5→⚠️ **Note**: This is a temporary test client for development and testing purposes. In production, this functionality will be handled by **augloop**.\n     6→\n     7→## Setup\n     8→\n     9→### 1. Build the Project\n    10→\n    11→First, build the project to ensure all dependencies are compiled:\n    12→\n    13→```bash\n    14→cd ../../\n    15→yarn build\n    16→```\n    17→\n    18→### 2. Authentication\n    19→\n    20→Authentication tokens are now automatically managed by the **Token Server**. The token server:\n    21→- Automatically fetches authentication tokens\n    22→- Refreshes tokens before they expire\n    23→- Handles token rotation seamlessly in the background\n    24→\n    25→No manual token management is required. The token server will be started automatically when you run the test client.\n    26→\n    27→### 3. Run the Test Client\n    28→\n    29→From the compiled dist directory:\n    30→\n    31→```bash\n    32→cd .devtools/test-client/dist/.devtools/test-client/src\n    33→node test-llm-client-for-relay.js\n    34→```\n    35→\n    36→Or use the convenient script from the root:\n    37→\n    38→```bash\n    39→yarn start:test\n    40→```\n    41→\n    42→## Configuration\n    43→\n    44→The test client can be configured using environment variables:\n    45→\n    46→- `LLM_WS_URL` - WebSocket server URL (default: `ws://localhost:6010/ws`)\n    47→- `LLM_API_HOST` - Anthropic API host (default: `fe-26.qas.bing.net`)\n    48→- `LLM_API_PATH` - API path (default: `/sdf/messages`)\n    49→\n    50→## Usage\n    51→\n    52→### Prerequisites\n    53→\n    54→The API server must be running and accessible. The server can be running in various environments:\n    55→- **Local development**: Running locally on your machine\n    56→- **Container**: Running in a Docker container\n    57→- **Cloud**: Running behind OfficePy service in the cloud\n    58→- **Remote**: Running on a remote server\n    59→\n    60→The test client will connect to the WebSocket endpoint (default: `ws://localhost:6010/ws`).\n    61→\n    62→### Running the Test Client\n    63→\n    64→1. **Start the test client**:\n    65→   ```bash\n    66→   yarn start:test\n    67→   ```\n    68→\n    69→   Or manually from the compiled directory:\n    70→   ```bash\n    71→   cd .devtools/test-client/dist/.devtools/test-client/src\n    72→   node test-llm-client-for-relay.js\n    73→   ```\n    74→\n    75→2. **Send requests** to the API server:\n    76→   ```bash\n    77→   curl -v -X POST http://localhost:6010/generateDocument \\\n    78→     -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n    79→     -d '{\n    80→       \"userQuery\": \"Create a simple one-page document about dog breeds with minimal information and maybe tabular data if possible.\",\n    81→       \"documentType\": \"docx\",\n    82→       \"conversationId\": \"XYZ-ABC-TEST\"\n    83→     }'\n    84→   ```\n    85→\n    86→## How It Works\n    87→\n    88→1. The test client connects to the WebSocket server at `/ws`\n    89→2. When the API server receives HTTP requests at `/v1/messages`, it forwards them as WebSocket messages to the test client\n    90→3. The test client receives these messages, forwards them to the real Anthropic API, and sends responses back through WebSocket\n    91→4. The API server receives the WebSocket responses and returns them to the original HTTP client\n    92→\n    93→## Message Protocol\n    94→\n    95→The client now uses the standardized message protocol contracts defined in `modules/message-protocol`:\n    96→\n    97→- **Request Messages**: `MessageType.LLMRequest` with structured payload\n    98→- **Response Messages**: `MessageType.LLMResponse`, `MessageType.LLMResponseChunk`, etc.\n    99→- **Message Structure**: Each message includes `id`, `sessionId`, `requestId`, and `payload`\n   100→\n   101→## Troubleshooting\n   102→\n   103→### Connection Issues\n   104→- Ensure the main API server is running on port 6010\n   105→- Check that the WebSocket path `/ws` is accessible\n   106→- Verify no firewall is blocking the connection\n   107→- Ensure the Token Server is running on port 12000\n   108→\n   109→### Protocol Errors\n   110→- Ensure both the API server and test client are using the latest compiled versions\n   111→- Check that message types match the protocol contracts\n   112→- Verify the message structure includes all required fields (`id`, `sessionId`, `requestId`, `payload`)\n   113→\n   114→### Token Server Issues\n   115→- If you encounter authentication errors, verify the Token Server is running\n   116→- Check the Token Server logs for any authentication failures\n   117→- The Token Server should automatically handle token refresh - no manual intervention needed\n   118→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JFxuCnY2KejKQcmVMsFzvh","session_id":"98ef6066-2367-415b-b616-f95ed64be17a","uuid":"e358c406-4319-44e7-9eb4-3e88b02c4485"}
