{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KidWEgsGBZ7YcurtWEDAvh","type":"tool_result","content":"/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/create-agent/src/prompts/1.0.0/skills\n/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/create-agent/src/prompts/1.0.0/skills/docx\n/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/create-agent/src/prompts/1.0.0/skills/enterprise-research\n/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/create-agent/src/prompts/1.0.0/skills/enterprise-search-sydney\n/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/create-agent/src/prompts/1.0.0/skills/image-search\n/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/create-agent/src/prompts/1.0.0/skills/pdf\n/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/create-agent/src/prompts/1.0.0/skills/pptx\n/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/create-agent/src/prompts/1.0.0/skills/web-fetch\n/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/create-agent/src/prompts/1.0.0/skills/web-search\n/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/create-agent/src/prompts/1.0.0/skills/xlsx","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01VbaCZT2x5MAVT4SegakNyh","session_id":"98ef6066-2367-415b-b616-f95ed64be17a","uuid":"0bae478d-b54a-43ef-93eb-f1b030c99cb1"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PWGb5sKGnk5AAM855FfdBa","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Excel Headless Module\n     2→\n     3→## Overview\n     4→\n     5→The Excel Headless system enables server-side Excel automation through Office.js script execution in a sandboxed environment. It provides a secure, isolated runtime for executing Excel operations without requiring a full Excel client, communicating with Excel Online via WebSocket-based message passing.\n     6→\n     7→The system consists of two main components:\n     8→- **`@officeagent/excel-headless`** - Container-side module (OfficePy) that handles script execution in a VM sandbox\n     9→- **Office Agent Client** - Trusted client-side handlers that manage WOPI tokens and communicate with SharePoint/Excel Online\n    10→\n    11→---\n    12→\n    13→## Table of Contents\n    14→\n    15→1. [System Architecture](#system-architecture)\n    16→2. [Document Generation Flow](#document-generation-flow)\n    17→3. [Module Structure](#module-structure)\n    18→4. [Core Components](#core-components)\n    19→5. [Office Agent Client Integration](#office-agent-client-integration)\n    20→6. [Security Model](#security-model)\n    21→7. [Message Protocol](#message-protocol)\n    22→8. [API Reference](#api-reference)\n    23→9. [Usage Examples](#usage-examples)\n    24→10. [Troubleshooting](#troubleshooting)\n    25→\n    26→---\n    27→\n    28→## System Architecture\n    29→\n    30→### High-Level System Overview\n    31→\n    32→:::mermaid\n    33→graph TB\n    34→    subgraph AugLoop[\"Augmentation Loop\"]\n    35→        subgraph OffAgent[\"OfficeAgent\"]\n    36→            AgentClient[\"Agent Client\"]\n    37→        end\n    38→    end\n    39→\n    40→    subgraph OfficePy[\"OfficePy Container (Linux)\"]\n    41→        Filesystem[\"SKILL.md files, CLI tools\"]\n    42→\n    43→        subgraph HostApp[\"Office Agent Host App\"]\n    44→            AgentHarness[\"Agent Harness (Claude SDK)\"]\n    45→            InternalHTTP[\"Internal HTTP Server\"]\n    46→            ExcelModule[\"@officeagent/excel-headless\"]\n    47→        end\n    48→    end\n    49→\n    50→    subgraph External[\"External Services\"]\n    51→        Excel[\"Excel Online\"]\n    52→        SharePoint[\"SharePoint/OneDrive\"]\n    53→    end\n    54→\n    55→    AgentClient -.->|WebSocket| ExcelModule\n    56→    ExcelModule -->|Office.js scripts| AgentHarness\n    57→    AgentClient -->|Graph API + WOPI| SharePoint\n    58→    AgentClient -->|Office.js API| Excel\n    59→\n    60→    classDef highlight fill:#e3f2fd,stroke:#2196f3,stroke-width:3px\n    61→    class OfficePy highlight\n    62→:::\n    63→\n    64→### Component Architecture\n    65→\n    66→:::mermaid\n    67→graph TB\n    68→    subgraph Container[\"OfficePy Container\"]\n    69→        CLI[\"excel-headless-cli\"]\n    70→        Handler[\"Excel Headless Handler\"]\n    71→        Sandbox[\"VM Sandbox\"]\n    72→        Tracker[\"Request Tracker\"]\n    73→\n    74→        CLI -->|HTTP POST| Handler\n    75→        Handler -->|Execute| Sandbox\n    76→        Handler --> Tracker\n    77→    end\n    78→\n    79→    subgraph WSLayer[\"WebSocket Layer\"]\n    80→        Router[\"WebSocket Router\"]\n    81→    end\n    82→\n    83→    subgraph Client[\"Office Agent Client\"]\n    84→        MsgHandler[\"ExcelMessageHandler\"]\n    85→        FileHandler[\"ExcelFileHandler\"]\n    86→        JSHandler[\"ExcelOfficeJsHandler\"]\n    87→        Cache[\"ExcelMetadataCache\"]\n    88→\n    89→        MsgHandler --> FileHandler\n    90→        MsgHandler --> JSHandler\n    91→        FileHandler --> Cache\n    92→        JSHandler --> Cache\n    93→    end\n    94→\n    95→    subgraph External[\"External Services\"]\n    96→        SP[\"SharePoint/Excel Online\"]\n    97→    end\n    98→\n    99→    Handler <-->|WebSocket| Router\n   100→    Router <-->|WebSocket| MsgHandler"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JFxuCnY2KejKQcmVMsFzvh","session_id":"98ef6066-2367-415b-b616-f95ed64be17a","uuid":"2c47ace3-93f1-483a-8fb6-e99e01f9ecd9"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GkUu9YFqgsW87MA9SaiZpV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Azure OpenAI Integration - Corrected Design\n     2→\n     3→## Requirements\n     4→\n     5→1. **New Server Route:** `/v1/openai` (generic for all OpenAI APIs)\n     6→2. **Request Format:** Actual LLM request + metadata (api, backend, headers) - server doesn't parse LLM request\n     7→3. **Routing:** Server → TestClient OR AugLoop Client (whoever is connected)\n     8→4. **TestClient Paths:**\n     9→   - 4a.1: Direct API (env var controlled) → Azure or Substrate\n    10→   - 4a.2: AugLoop REST API (forward all metadata)\n    11→5. **AugLoop Client Path:** Forward all details for backend + api routing\n    12→6. **Response Handling:** Standard flow, NO rate limit delays (429 handled by agent)\n    13→\n    14→---\n    15→\n    16→## Inspiration: Claude Pattern\n    17→\n    18→```\n    19→Claude:\n    20→  POST /v1/messages → Server → WebSocket → TestClient/AugLoop\n    21→  - Server: Dumb pipe, forwards opaque body\n    22→  - TestClient: USE_DIRECT_SUBSTRATE_LLM_API env var controls routing\n    23→  - Response: Standard SSE streaming\n    24→```\n    25→\n    26→---\n    27→\n    28→## Proposed Design\n    29→\n    30→### 1. Server Route\n    31→\n    32→**Endpoint:** `POST /v1/openai`\n    33→\n    34→**Request Headers:**\n    35→```\n    36→Content-Type: application/json\n    37→X-OpenAI-Api: chat/completions | responses | images/generations | ...\n    38→X-OpenAI-Backend: azure | substrate\n    39→X-Custom-Header-*: ...  (any custom headers prefixed with X-Custom-)\n    40→```\n    41→\n    42→**Request Body:**\n    43→```typescript\n    44→{\n    45→  // Opaque LLM request (Server DOES NOT parse)\n    46→  \"model\": \"gpt-5.1\",\n    47→  \"messages\": [...],\n    48→  \"stream\": false,\n    49→  // ... any OpenAI API fields\n    50→}\n    51→```\n    52→\n    53→**Alternative (if prefer body over headers):**\n    54→```typescript\n    55→{\n    56→  // Metadata\n    57→  \"api\": \"chat/completions\",\n    58→  \"backend\": \"azure\",\n    59→\n    60→  // Opaque LLM request\n    61→  \"request\": {\n    62→    \"model\": \"gpt-5.1\",\n    63→    \"messages\": [...]\n    64→  }\n    65→}\n    66→```\n    67→\n    68→**My recommendation:** Use **headers** for metadata (api, backend) since:\n    69→- Cleaner separation of routing metadata vs request data\n    70→- Easier to pass through extra headers\n    71→- Request body is pure OpenAI API format\n    72→\n    73→---\n    74→\n    75→### 2. Server Handler (modules/api)\n    76→\n    77→**File:** `modules/api/src/websocket/handlers/openai-proxy-handler.ts`\n    78→\n    79→```typescript\n    80→// Copy structure from llm-proxy-handler.ts\n    81→export function registerOpenAIProxyHandlers(\n    82→  app: Application,\n    83→  getConversationId: () => string | null,\n    84→  getLogsDir: () => string | null\n    85→) {\n    86→  // Register WebSocket response handler\n    87→  wsRouter.registerHandler(MessageType.OpenAIResponse, handleOpenAIResponse);\n    88→\n    89→  // HTTP endpoint\n    90→  app.post('/v1/openai', async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n    91→    const requestId = uuidv4();\n    92→    const sessionId = getConversationId() || `http-session-${Date.now()}`;\n    93→\n    94→    // Extract metadata from headers\n    95→    const api = req.headers['x-openai-api'] as string;\n    96→    const backend = req.headers['x-openai-backend'] as string;\n    97→\n    98→    // Extract custom headers (X-Custom-*)\n    99→    const customHeaders: Record<string, string> = {};\n   100→    Object.keys(req.headers).forEach(key => {"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JFxuCnY2KejKQcmVMsFzvh","session_id":"98ef6066-2367-415b-b616-f95ed64be17a","uuid":"923b6d85-7552-43eb-bf24-914c7f244fbd"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01T6JfJvi26WvKjWcUTsW4gp","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Claude Code Launcher for OfficeAgent\n     2→\n     3→A convenient desktop launcher for Claude Code with Anthropic logo.\n     4→\n     5→## 🚀 Quick Start (New & Improved!)\n     6→\n     7→### ONE-TIME SETUP - Just Double-Click:\n     8→\n     9→```\n    10→📁 .devtools/launcher/\n    11→   └── 🎯 SETUP.cmd  ← DOUBLE-CLICK THIS!\n    12→```\n    13→\n    14→**That's it!** The setup will:\n    15→- ✅ Remove any old broken shortcuts\n    16→- ✅ Download Anthropic Claude logo\n    17→- ✅ Create a pinnable desktop shortcut\n    18→- ✅ Auto-load .env file\n    19→- ✅ Launch from correct directory\n    20→\n    21→**Then:**\n    22→- Right-click shortcut → **Pin to Start** 📌\n    23→- Or drag to **Taskbar** for quick access\n    24→\n    25→### Alternative: Run Directly Without Shortcut\n    26→\n    27→If you don't want a shortcut, just double-click:\n    28→- `launch-claude.cmd` in this folder\n    29→\n    30→## Features\n    31→\n    32→- **Auto-detects project directory** - Finds OfficeAgent root automatically from launcher location\n    33→- **Sets working directory** - Changes to OfficeAgent directory BEFORE launching Claude Code\n    34→- **Loads .env file** - Automatically loads environment variables from project root (`OfficeAgent/.env`)\n    35→- **Validates API key** - Checks for `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` before launching\n    36→- **Version checking** - Displays Claude Code version and checks for updates\n    37→- **Age warning** - Warns if your Claude executable is over 30 days old\n    38→- **Detailed logging** - Shows exactly what directory and .env file are being used\n    39→\n    40→## Setup Requirements\n    41→\n    42→### 1. Install Claude Code\n    43→\n    44→```bash\n    45→npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code\n    46→```\n    47→\n    48→Or let the launcher use `npx` as a fallback (slower).\n    49→\n    50→### 2. Set API Key\n    51→\n    52→Create a `.env` file in the project root (OfficeAgent/) with:\n    53→```\n    54→ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-your-key-here\n    55→```\n    56→\n    57→Or set it as a system environment variable.\n    58→\n    59→## Usage Options\n    60→\n    61→### Skip API Key Check\n    62→If you want to launch without API key validation:\n    63→```powershell\n    64→.\\launch-claude.ps1 -SkipApiKeyCheck\n    65→```\n    66→\n    67→### Specify Custom Project Directory\n    68→```powershell\n    69→.\\launch-claude.ps1 -ProjectDir \"C:\\custom\\path\\to\\OfficeAgent\"\n    70→```\n    71→\n    72→## Troubleshooting\n    73→\n    74→### \"Execution Policy\" Error\n    75→**Solution: Use the .cmd file instead!**\n    76→\n    77→The `.cmd` file has NO execution policy issues. If you're getting this error:\n    78→- Double-click `launch-claude.cmd` instead of the `.ps1` file\n    79→- Or use the desktop shortcut created by `create-shortcut.ps1` (it uses the .cmd file)\n    80→\n    81→If you really need to run the `.ps1` directly:\n    82→```powershell\n    83→Set-ExecutionPolicy -Scope Process -ExecutionPolicy Bypass\n    84→.\\launch-claude.ps1\n    85→```\n    86→\n    87→### \"Claude not found\" Error\n    88→The launcher will automatically try:\n    89→1. `~\\.local\\bin\\claude.exe` (user installation)\n    90→2. `claude` command in PATH (global installation)\n    91→3. `npx @anthropic-ai/claude-code` (fallback, slower)\n    92→\n    93→If all fail, install Claude Code globally:\n    94→```bash\n    95→npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code\n    96→```\n    97→\n    98→### \"API Key not found\" Error\n    99→1. Check that `.env` file exists in project root\n   100→2. Verify `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` is set correctly\n   101→3. Make sure there are no extra spaces or quotes\n   102→4. Or use `-SkipApiKeyCheck` flag if you want to proceed anyway\n   103→\n   104→## Team Distribution\n   105→\n   106→To share this launcher with your team:\n   107→\n   108→1. Commit the `.devtools/launcher/` folder to git (except `icons/` - auto-ignored)\n   109→2. Team members clone the repo\n   110→3. Each person double-clicks `SETUP.cmd`\n   111→4. Everyone has a pinnable launcher with Claude logo!\n   112→\n   113→**Zero configuration needed!** Everything auto-detects paths and downloads the logo automatically.\n   114→\n   115→## Files\n   116→\n   117→**Main Files:**\n   118→- `SETUP.cmd` - 🎯 **ONE-TIME SETUP** - Double-click to create launcher with Claude logo!\n   119→- `setup-claude-launcher.ps1` - Setup script (called by SETUP.cmd)\n   120→- `launch-claude.cmd` - Direct launcher (no shortcut needed)\n   121→- `launch-claude.ps1` - PowerShell launcher\n   122→- `README.md` - This file\n   123→\n   124→**Legacy Files (kept for compatibility):**\n   125→- `create-shortcut.cmd` - Old shortcut creator (use SETUP.cmd instead)\n   126→- `create-shortcut.ps1` - Old setup script\n   127→\n   128→**Auto-Generated (gitignored):**\n   129→- `icons/` - Downloaded Claude logo\n   130→\n   131→**All files can be checked into git!** The setup downloads the Claude logo automatically.\n   132→\n   133→## How It Works\n   134→\n   135→### Directory & Environment Setup\n   136→\n   137→When you launch Claude Code via this launcher, here's what happens:\n   138→\n   139→1. **Auto-detect project directory**\n   140→   - Launcher is at: `.devtools/launcher/`\n   141→   - Goes up 2 levels to find: `OfficeAgent/` (project root)\n   142→   - Works regardless of where you cloned the repo\n   143→\n   144→2. **Load .env file**\n   145→   - Looks for: `OfficeAgent/.env`\n   146→   - Loads all environment variables into the session\n   147→   - Shows count of variables loaded\n   148→\n   149→3. **Change working directory**\n   150→   - `cd` to: `OfficeAgent/` directory\n   151→   - Verifies directory change was successful\n   152→   - Claude Code launches FROM this directory\n   153→\n   154→4. **Launch Claude Code**\n   155→   - Runs `claude` command\n   156→   - Already in correct directory with env vars loaded\n   157→   - Can access `.claude/`, `package.json`, etc.\n   158→\n   159→**Result:** Claude Code starts in `OfficeAgent/` with all your `.env` variables available!\n   160→\n   161→## Developer Notes\n   162→\n   163→The launcher:\n   164→- Automatically detects the project root from its location\n   165→- Works from any OfficeAgent clone location\n   166→- No hardcoded paths (portable across machines and clone locations)\n   167→- Changes to project directory BEFORE launching Claude (not after)\n   168→- Loads environment variables from `.env` if present\n   169→- Shows detailed output of what it's doing for debugging\n   170→\n   171→---\n   172→\n   173→**Version:** 1.0\n   174→**Last Updated:** 2025-10-22\n   175→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JFxuCnY2KejKQcmVMsFzvh","session_id":"98ef6066-2367-415b-b616-f95ed64be17a","uuid":"fd48daa9-6181-46c2-aa98-8b5112180755"}
