{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Aqb9dzxewNpX6M5Sumkfki","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Word OCV Feedback Report Generator\n     2→\n     3→This tool generates comprehensive reports from OCV (Office Customer Voice) feedback by combining data from:\n     4→- **OCV** - Customer feedback (thumbs up/down, comments)\n     5→- **Claude LLM** - AI-powered categorization of feedback\n     6→- **Kusto** - Telemetry logs (failures, latencies, session data)\n     7→- **ADO** - Bug tracking (existing bugs related to failures)\n     8→\n     9→## Prerequisites\n    10→\n    11→### 1. Python Environment\n    12→```bash\n    13→# Python 3.10+ required\n    14→python --version\n    15→\n    16→# Install dependencies\n    17→pip install playwright azure-kusto-data mcp\n    18→playwright install chromium\n    19→```\n    20→\n    21→### 2. Claude Code CLI (for LLM Categorization)\n    22→The tool uses Claude CLI to automatically categorize feedback based on comments and tags.\n    23→**It uses your existing Claude Code sign-in - no API key needed!**\n    24→\n    25→Make sure you have Claude Code installed and signed in:\n    26→```bash\n    27→# Check if Claude CLI is available\n    28→claude --version\n    29→\n    30→# If not installed, download from:\n    31→# https://claude.ai/download\n    32→\n    33→# Sign in (if not already)\n    34→claude\n    35→```\n    36→\n    37→**Note:** If Claude CLI is not available, categorization will be skipped and all items will be marked as \"Uncategorized\".\n    38→\n    39→### 3. Kusto Configuration\n    40→Create `kusto_mcp/kusto_config.json`:\n    41→```json\n    42→{\n    43→  \"clusters\": {\n    44→    \"odxaugloop\": {\n    45→      \"cluster\": \"https://odxaugloop.eastus.kusto.windows.net\",\n    46→      \"database\": \"ODX AugLoop Service\"\n    47→    }\n    48→  }\n    49→}\n    50→```\n    51→\n    52→### 4. ADO Configuration\n    53→Create `ado_mcp/ado_config.json`:\n    54→```json\n    55→{\n    56→  \"org_url\": \"https://office.visualstudio.com\",\n    57→  \"project\": \"OC\",\n    58→  \"pat\": \"YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN\",\n    59→  \"area_path\": \"OC\",\n    60→  \"iteration_path\": \"OC\"\n    61→}\n    62→```\n    63→\n    64→To get a PAT:\n    65→1. Go to https://office.visualstudio.com/_usersSettings/tokens\n    66→2. Create a new token with **Work Items (Read)** scope\n    67→3. Copy the token to the config file\n    68→\n    69→### 5. OCV Authentication\n    70→OCV uses Microsoft SSO. On first run:\n    71→1. A browser window will open\n    72→2. Complete Microsoft login\n    73→3. Auth is cached for future runs\n    74→\n    75→## Usage\n    76→\n    77→### Run Full Workflow\n    78→```bash\n    79→# Default: Last 7 days with AI Agents query\n    80→python run_full_workflow.py\n    81→\n    82→# Custom date range: Last 14 days\n    83→python run_full_workflow.py --days 14\n    84→\n    85→# Last 30 days with max 1000 items\n    86→python run_full_workflow.py --days 30 --max 1000\n    87→\n    88→# Custom OCV URL (copy from browser after setting up filters)\n    89→python run_full_workflow.py --url \"https://ocv.microsoft.com/#/discover/?q=YourQuery...\"\n    90→\n    91→# Custom report title\n    92→python run_full_workflow.py --title \"Excel Copilot Feedback\"\n    93→\n    94→# Combine options\n    95→python run_full_workflow.py --days 14 --title \"PowerPoint Feedback\" --url \"https://ocv.microsoft.com/#/...\"\n    96→```\n    97→\n    98→**Command-line options:**\n    99→| Option | Default | Description |\n   100→|--------|---------|-------------|\n   101→| `--days`, `-d` | 7 | Number of days to look back (used for both OCV and Kusto) |\n   102→| `--max`, `-m` | 500 | Maximum OCV feedback items to scrape |\n   103→| `--url`, `-u` | (AI Agents) | Custom OCV URL - copy from browser after setting up your filters |\n   104→| `--title`, `-t` | \"OCV Feedback Analysis\" | Title for the HTML report |\n   105→\n   106→This will:\n   107→1. Scrape OCV feedback for the specified date range\n   108→2. Categorize feedback using Claude LLM (based on comments, tags, theme)\n   109→3. Query Kusto for telemetry data (same date range)\n   110→4. Search ADO for related bugs\n   111→5. Generate HTML report with categories\n   112→\n   113→### Output Structure\n   114→Each run creates a timestamped folder:\n   115→```\n   116→~/.ocv_mcp_data/\n   117→├── run_20260122_143052/              # Timestamped run folder\n   118→│   ├── step1_all_feedback.json       # All OCV feedback\n   119→│   ├── step1_all_feedback.csv\n   120→│   ├── step1_thumbs_down.json        # Thumbs down only\n   121→│   ├── step1_thumbs_down.csv\n   122→│   ├── step2_llm_categories.json     # LLM categorization results\n   123→│   ├── step3_kusto_data.json         # Kusto telemetry\n   124→│   ├── step3_kusto_data.csv\n   125→│   ├── step4_ado_bugs.json           # ADO bug matches\n   126→│   ├── step5_detailed_items.json     # Final merged data\n   127→│   ├── step5_detailed_items.csv\n   128→│   ├── report.json                   # Full report data\n   129→│   └── report.html                   # HTML report\n   130→├── thumbs_down_report_latest.html    # Latest HTML (always updated)\n   131→└── thumbs_down_detailed_report_latest.json\n   132→```\n   133→\n   134→### View Report\n   135→Open the HTML report in a browser:\n   136→```bash\n   137→# Windows\n   138→start ~/.ocv_mcp_data/thumbs_down_report_latest.html\n   139→\n   140→# Or open specific run\n   141→start ~/.ocv_mcp_data/run_20260122_143052/report.html\n   142→```\n   143→\n   144→## MCP Servers\n   145→\n   146→Individual MCP servers can be used independently:\n   147→\n   148→### OCV MCP\n   149→```bash\n   150→cd ocv_mcp\n   151→python server.py\n   152→```\n   153→\n   154→Tools:\n   155→- `ocv_scrape_feedback` - Scrape feedback from OCV\n   156→- `ocv_analyze_feedback` - Analyze feedback statistics\n   157→- `ocv_read_latest_feedback` - Read previously scraped data\n   158→\n   159→### Kusto MCP\n   160→```bash\n   161→cd kusto_mcp\n   162→python server.py\n   163→```\n   164→\n   165→Tools:\n   166→- `kusto_query` - Run Kusto queries\n   167→- `kusto_list_clusters` - List configured clusters\n   168→\n   169→### ADO MCP\n   170→```bash\n   171→cd ado_mcp\n   172→python server.py\n   173→```\n   174→\n   175→Tools:\n   176→- `ado_find_bugs` - Search for bugs by keyword\n   177→- `ado_get_bug` - Get bug details by ID\n   178→\n   179→## Issue Categories\n   180→\n   181→Feedback is automatically categorized by Claude LLM based on:\n   182→- User comments\n   183→- Tags\n   184→- Theme\n   185→- Issue description\n   186→- Area\n   187→\n   188→| Category | Description |\n   189→|----------|-------------|\n   190→| Reliability | No response / Blank output / Stopped working / Crash or hang |\n   191→| Performance | Very slow / Long-running / High CPU / Timeout |\n   192→| Accuracy | Hallucination / Fiction / Wrong or inaccurate answers |\n   193→| Grounding & Relevance | Didn't use provided data / Lost context / Wrong source |\n   194→| Instruction Following | Missed requirements / Missing content / Wrong format |\n   195→| File & Data Handling | File not found / Upload issues / Document errors |\n   196→| UI & Formatting | Display issues / Formatting problems / Visual bugs |\n   197→| Other | General dissatisfaction / Unclear issue |\n   198→\n   199→To customize categories, edit `ISSUE_CATEGORIES` dict in `run_full_workflow.py`.\n   200→\n   201→## Troubleshooting\n   202→\n   203→### LLM Categorization Not Working\n   204→- Verify Claude CLI is installed: `claude --version`\n   205→- Ensure you're signed in to Claude Code: run `claude` and complete sign-in\n   206→- Check that Claude CLI is in your PATH\n   207→- If timeouts occur, the tool will retry and continue with remaining batches\n   208→\n   209→### OCV Authentication Issues\n   210→- Delete browser cache: `rm -rf ~/.ocv_mcp_browser`\n   211→- Re-run workflow to trigger fresh login\n   212→\n   213→### Kusto Connection Issues\n   214→- Ensure you're on corp network or VPN\n   215→- Check cluster URL in config\n   216→- Verify Azure AD authentication\n   217→\n   218→### ADO PAT Expired\n   219→- Generate new PAT at https://office.visualstudio.com/_usersSettings/tokens\n   220→- Update `ado_mcp/ado_config.json`\n   221→\n   222→### No Kusto Data Found\n   223→- Kusto only keeps data for 14 days\n   224→- Check if conversation IDs are in the correct format\n   225→- Verify the Kusto query filters match your data\n   226→\n   227→## File Structure\n   228→\n   229→```\n   230→dev-tools/\n   231→├── run_full_workflow.py      # Main workflow script\n   232→├── README.md                 # This file\n   233→├── ocv_mcp/\n   234→│   └── server.py            # OCV scraper MCP server\n   235→├── kusto_mcp/\n   236→│   ├── server.py            # Kusto query MCP server\n   237→│   └── kusto_config.json    # Kusto cluster configuration\n   238→└── ado_mcp/\n   239→    ├── server.py            # ADO bug search MCP server\n   240→    └── ado_config.json      # ADO configuration (PAT)\n   241→```\n   242→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JFxuCnY2KejKQcmVMsFzvh","session_id":"98ef6066-2367-415b-b616-f95ed64be17a","uuid":"333a7678-dd7d-402f-ab39-134ff5e0ea4c"}
