{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DoWPqYgZb6dv7X3Ny6qo6a","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Eval Output Browser\n     2→\n     3→A web-based tool to browse and analyze OfficeAgent pairwise evaluation outputs. Built with Python/Flask.\n     4→\n     5→## Features\n     6→\n     7→- 📁 Browse eval output directories from `eval/outputs/`\n     8→- 🔄 **A vs B Comparison**: Side-by-side view of page images from both sides\n     9→- 📝 **OfficeAgent Detail**: View page images alongside HTML sections\n    10→- 📊 **Eval Scores**: See Aesthetics, Fidelity, and Consistency scores with winner highlighted\n    11→  - 🟢 Green = OfficeAgent wins\n    12→  - 🔴 Red = Other side wins\n    13→- 🔍 Click on any score to see the full analysis/reasoning\n    14→- ⌨️ Keyboard navigation: Use Arrow Up/Down to browse through documents\n    15→- 🖼️ Click images to view full-size preview\n    16→\n    17→## Requirements\n    18→\n    19→- Python 3.8+\n    20→- Flask (will be installed from workspace venv)\n    21→\n    22→The workspace virtual environment (`venv`) already has Flask installed.\n    23→\n    24→## Quick Start\n    25→\n    26→### Option 1: Using workspace venv (Recommended)\n    27→\n    28→```powershell\n    29→# From the OfficeAgent repository root\n    30→c:\\src\\OfficeAgent\\venv\\Scripts\\python.exe c:\\src\\OfficeAgent\\.devtools\\eval-browser\\server.py\n    31→```\n    32→\n    33→### Option 2: Using system Python\n    34→\n    35→```bash\n    36→# Install Flask if not already installed\n    37→pip install flask\n    38→\n    39→# Run the server\n    40→cd .devtools/eval-browser\n    41→python server.py\n    42→```\n    43→\n    44→### Open in Browser\n    45→\n    46→Navigate to: **http://localhost:3050**\n    47→\n    48→## Usage\n    49→\n    50→1. **Select an output directory** from the dropdown (e.g., `official_word_pairwise_vs_wordagentmode`)\n    51→2. **Click on a document** (e.g., `doc_1`) from the list\n    52→3. **View scores and query** at the top panel\n    53→4. **Switch tabs** between \"A vs B Comparison\" and \"OfficeAgent Detail\"\n    54→5. **Navigate with keyboard**: Arrow Up/Down to move through documents\n    55→6. **Click on scores** to see detailed analysis reasoning\n    56→\n    57→## Eval Output Location\n    58→\n    59→Evaluation outputs are read from:\n    60→```\n    61→<repo_root>/eval/outputs/\n    62→```\n    63→\n    64→## Running Evaluations\n    65→\n    66→To generate new eval outputs, run evaluations using the `oagent` CLI:\n    67→\n    68→```bash\n    69→# Example: Run word pairwise evaluation\n    70→oagent eval run word.pairwise.ungrounded.official\n    71→\n    72→# With custom batch file\n    73→oagent eval run word.pairwise.ungrounded.official --batch eval/datasets/word_datasets/your_dataset.json\n    74→```\n    75→\n    76→See `eval/aliases.json` for available evaluation aliases and their configurations.\n    77→\n    78→## Expected Directory Structure\n    79→\n    80→The browser expects eval outputs in this format:\n    81→```\n    82→eval/outputs/\n    83→  <output_dir>/                           # e.g., official_word_pairwise_vs_wordagentmode\n    84→    doc_1/\n    85→      OfficeAgent v1.1.0/                 # Side A\n    86→        doc/\n    87→          *.docx                          # Generated document\n    88→          slide_*.png                     # Page preview images\n    89→          debug/turn1/workspace/output/\n    90→            html_sections/*.html          # HTML sections\n    91→        eval/\n    92→          pairwise_result_run1.json       # Contains query, app names\n    93→          run1/\n    94→            sbsleov3_scores_cache.json    # Contains scores & analysis\n    95→      Word Agent Mode/                    # Side B\n    96→        doc/\n    97→          ...\n    98→    doc_2/\n    99→      ...\n   100→```\n   101→\n   102→## Troubleshooting\n   103→\n   104→### Server won't start\n   105→- Make sure no other process is using port 3050\n   106→- Check that Flask is installed: `pip show flask`\n   107→\n   108→### No outputs showing\n   109→- Verify `eval/outputs/` contains evaluation directories\n   110→- Run an evaluation first using `oagent eval run`\n   111→\n   112→### Scores not showing\n   113→- Scores are read from `eval/run1/sbsleov3_scores_cache.json`\n   114→- This file is generated after the evaluation scoring phase completes\n   115→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JFxuCnY2KejKQcmVMsFzvh","session_id":"98ef6066-2367-415b-b616-f95ed64be17a","uuid":"8a66a675-3af0-4efe-9302-fc9d42a36dd8"}
