{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01EgR9MXzpWiLpetX4uWZKT1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01T5LXurZXmxf4wBaW8g6LYx","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"ls -la /c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/ppt-creation-agent/src/prompts/ 2>/dev/null || echo \"No prompts directory\"","description":"Check if ppt-creation-agent has prompts"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2354,"cache_read_input_tokens":49668,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2354,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01VbaCZT2x5MAVT4SegakNyh","session_id":"98ef6066-2367-415b-b616-f95ed64be17a","uuid":"5904307b-512b-401d-b55e-73439cd72bc1"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015AywHePLKxrKqeFSdm4AfL","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# AgentRequestMessage WebSocket Handling - End-to-End Flow\n     2→\n     3→This document explains how `AgentRequestMessage` is handled by created agents when received over WebSocket, from the initial connection through to Claude agent execution and response delivery.\n     4→\n     5→## Table of Contents\n     6→- [Overview](#overview)ture)\n     7→- [End-to-End Flow](#end-to-end-flow)\n     8→- [Detailed Component Breakdown](#detailed-component-breakdown)\n     9→- [Key Features](#key-features)\n    10→- [Error Handling](#error-handling)\n    11→\n    12→---\n    13→\n    14→## Overview\n    15→\n    16→The WebSocket-based agent request flow enables real-time, bidirectional communication between clients and Office Agent. When a client sends an `AgentRequestMessage` over WebSocket, it triggers a sophisticated pipeline involving message routing, preprocessing, validation, and ultimately Claude-based document generation.\n    17→\n    18→**Key Components:**\n    19→- **WebSocket Router** - Routes incoming messages to appropriate handlers\n    20→- **WebSocket Chat Request Handler** - Preprocesses and validates requests\n    21→- **Create Agent** - Main agent orchestrating document generation\n    22→- **Claude Agent SDK** - Executes document generation logic\n    23→\n    24→\n    25→---\n    26→\n    27→## End-to-End Flow\n    28→\n    29→```\n    30→┌──────────────┐\n    31→│   Client     │\n    32→└──────┬───────┘\n    33→       │ 1. Send AgentRequestMessage\n    34→       │    over WebSocket\n    35→       ▼\n    36→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n    37→│  WebSocket Server                           │\n    38→│  (modules/core/src/websocket/router.ts)    │\n    39→│                                             │\n    40→│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n    41→│  │  WebSocketRouter.routeMessage()      │  │\n    42→│  │  - Parse JSON message                │  │\n    43→│  │  - Extract message.type              │  │\n    44→│  │  - Find registered handler           │  │\n    45→│  └──────────┬───────────────────────────┘  │\n    46→└─────────────┼───────────────────────────────┘\n    47→              │ 2. Route to handler\n    48→              ▼\n    49→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n    50→│  CreateAgent.handleChatRequest()            │\n    51→│  (agents/create-agent/src/create-agent.ts)  │\n    52→│                                             │\n    53→│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n    54→│  │  PHASE 1: Preprocessing               │  │\n    55→│  │  ──────────────────────────────────   │  │\n    56→│  │  WebSocketChatRequestHandler          │  │\n    57→│  │  .preprocess(message)                 │  │\n    58→│  │  - Wait for session init              │  │\n    59→│  │  - Extract conversationId/requestId   │  │\n    60→│  │  - Check conversation busy state      │  │\n    61→│  │  - Validate query not empty           │  │\n    62→│  │  - Store query annotations            │  │\n    63→│  └──────────┬───────────────────────────┘  │\n    64→│             │ 3. Preprocessing result       │\n    65→│             ▼                               │\n    66→│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n    67→│  │  PHASE 2: Send Acknowledgment         │  │\n    68→│  │  ──────────────────────────────────   │  │\n    69→│  │  Send ChatResponseMessage:            │  │\n    70→│  │  {                                    │  │\n    71→│  │    type: ChatResponse,                │  │\n    72→│  │    success: true/false,               │  │\n    73→│  │    requestId: \"...\",                  │  │\n    74→│  │    conversationId: \"...\",             │  │\n    75→│  │    error?: \"...\",                     │  │\n    76→│  │    errorMessage?: \"...\"               │  │\n    77→│  │  }                                    │  │\n    78→│  └──────────┬───────────────────────────┘  │\n    79→└─────────────┼───────────────────────────────┘\n    80→              │ 4. Continue if success\n    81→              ▼\n    82→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n    83→│  PHASE 3: Parse Grounding Content           │\n    84→│  (grounding-content-parser.ts)              │\n    85→│  - Extract clarification questions          │\n    86→│  - Parse message annotations                │\n    87→│  - Append to user query if present          │\n    88→└──────────┬──────────────────────────────────┘\n    89→           │ 5. Enhanced query\n    90→           ▼\n    91→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n    92→│  PHASE 4: Initialize Services               │\n    93→│  ──────────────────────────────────────     │\n    94→│  - FileWatcherService (monitor output)      │\n    95→│  - ClaudeMessageLoggerService               │\n    96→│  - WebSocketMessengerService                │\n    97→│  - DebugZipCreatorService                   │\n    98→│  - Performance tracking                     │\n    99→│  - Chain of thought tracking                │\n   100→│  - Query classifier                         │\n   101→└──────────┬──────────────────────────────────┘\n   102→           │ 6. Services ready\n   103→           ▼\n   104→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n   105→│  PHASE 5: Create Turn & Execute Hooks       │\n   106→│  ──────────────────────────────────────     │\n   107→│  - workspaceManager.createNewTurn()         │\n   108→│  - Execute base startTurn hooks             │\n   109→│  - Execute agent-specific startTurn hooks   │\n   110→│  - Store grounding sources metadata         │\n   111→│  - Store query annotations metadata         │\n   112→└──────────┬──────────────────────────────────┘\n   113→           │ 7. Workspace ready\n   114→           ▼\n   115→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n   116→│  PHASE 6: Build System Prompt               │\n   117→│  ──────────────────────────────────────     │\n   118→│  - Load agent capabilities                  │\n   119→│  - Load RAI guidelines                      │\n   120→│  - Load skill documentation (XLSX/DOCX/PPTX)│\n   121→│  - Build timestamp metadata                 │\n   122→│  - Render EJS template                      │\n   123→└──────────┬──────────────────────────────────┘\n   124→           │ 8. System prompt ready\n   125→           ▼\n   126→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n   127→│  PHASE 7: Execute Claude Query              │\n   128→│  ──────────────────────────────────────     │\n   129→│  claude.query({                             │\n   130→│    prompt: userQuery + metadata,            │\n   131→│    options: {                               │\n   132→│      model: 'claude-sonnet-4-5',            │\n   133→│      maxTurns: 2000,                        │\n   134→│      systemPrompt: systemPrompt,            │\n   135→│      hooks: combinedHooks,                  │\n   136→│      env: { WORKSPACE_DIR, ... }            │\n   137→│    }                                        │\n   138→│  })                                         │\n   139→└──────────┬──────────────────────────────────┘\n   140→           │ 9. Stream Claude messages\n   141→           ▼\n   142→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n   143→│  PHASE 8: Process Claude Messages           │\n   144→│  ──────────────────────────────────────     │\n   145→│  for await (message of queryIterator) {     │\n   146→│    - Log message to disk                    │\n   147→│    - Track performance metrics              │\n   148→│    - Track chain of thought                 │\n   149→│                                             │\n   150→│    if (message.type === 'result') {         │"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JFxuCnY2KejKQcmVMsFzvh","session_id":"98ef6066-2367-415b-b616-f95ed64be17a","uuid":"0ddd8b6f-5efa-4504-b25b-83d81edc050c"}
