{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Cps4zsW7QEqKxsLA8uS5LP","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# OfficeAgent Evaluation Framework - Developer Guide\n     2→\n     3→A comprehensive framework for evaluating OfficeAgent requests and responses with support for parallel batch evaluations across multiple containers.\n     4→\n     5→## Table of Contents\n     6→\n     7→1. [When to Run Evaluations](#when-to-run-evaluations)\n     8→2. [Setup and Installation](#setup-and-installation)\n     9→3. [Running Evaluations](#running-evaluations)\n    10→4. [Understanding Results](#understanding-results)\n    11→5. [What to Do With Results](#what-to-do-with-results)\n    12→6. [Advanced Usage](#advanced-usage)\n    13→7. [Troubleshooting](#troubleshooting)\n    14→\n    15→---\n    16→\n    17→## When to Run Evaluations\n    18→\n    19→### 🔄 Regular Development Cycles\n    20→\n    21→Run evaluations in these scenarios:\n    22→\n    23→1. **Before Merging PRs** (Required)\n    24→\n    25→   - Run full evaluation suite on your feature branch\n    26→   - Compare results against main branch baseline\n    27→   - Ensure no regression in quality scores\n    28→\n    29→2. **After Major Changes** (Recommended)\n    30→\n    31→   - Modified prompt templates or skill logic\n    32→   - Updated document generation code\n    33→   - Changed AI model versions or parameters\n    34→   - Modified theme/styling systems\n    35→\n    36→3. **Weekly Quality Checks** (Best Practice)\n    37→\n    38→   - Run against production-like data\n    39→   - Track quality trends over time\n    40→   - Catch drift or degradation early\n    41→\n    42→4. **Before Releases** (Critical)\n    43→   - Full regression suite\n    44→   - Performance benchmarking\n    45→   - Cross-document-type validation\n    46→\n    47→---\n    48→\n    49→## Setup and Installation\n    50→\n    51→### Prerequisites\n    52→\n    53→- Node.js >= 20\n    54→- Docker Desktop (running)\n    55→- Python 3.8+ (automatically configured)\n    56→- Finish setting up the local Office Agent: [README.md](../README.md)\n    57→\n    58→### Initial Setup\n    59→\n    60→The evaluation framework is automatically installed during OfficeAgent setup:\n    61→\n    62→```bash\n    63→# One-time setup (if not done already)\n    64→npm run setup\n    65→```\n    66→\n    67→This installs:\n    68→\n    69→- All Node.js dependencies\n    70→- Python virtual environment and packages\n    71→- The `oagent-eval` Python package\n    72→- The `oagent` CLI tool\n    73→\n    74→> **Important**: You must run `npm run setup` before using `yarn start:compose` for the first time. This builds the test client that connects to the Docker containers.\n    75→\n    76→### Verify Installation\n    77→\n    78→```bash\n    79→# Check that the CLI is available\n    80→oagent eval --help\n    81→```\n    82→\n    83→---\n    84→\n    85→## Running Evaluations\n    86→\n    87→### Run Your Evaluations\n    88→\n    89→#### Option A: Quick Single Test\n    90→\n    91→Test a single prompt quickly (without grounding evaluation):\n    92→\n    93→```bash\n    94→oagent eval ppt.example\n    95→```\n    96→Test a single prompt quickly (grounding evaluation, runs only the first example from the larger dataset):\n    97→\n    98→```bash\n    99→oagent eval ppt.groundingeval -n 1\n   100→```\n   101→```bash\n   102→oagent eval word.groundingeval -n 1\n   103→```\n   104→\n   105→\n   106→**Note**: You may change the query by updating the batch files `./eval/datasets/official_ppt_example.json`, `.eval/datasets/official_ppt_implicit_grounding_inputs.json`, `.eval/datasets/official_word_implicit_grounding_inputs.json`\n   107→\n   108→Output:\n   109→\n   110→```\n   111→[INFO] Phase 2 complete: 1/1 evaluations completed\n   112→[INFO] Loaded societas results from: C:\\src\\OfficeAgent\\eval\\outputs\\ppt1\\officeagent\\societas_result.json\n   113→[INFO] Total evaluation results collected: 1 across 1 evaluators\n   114→Report saved to: eval\\outputs\\eval_report_official_ppt_example_20251114_160335.json\n   115→```\n   116→\n   117→#### Option B: Run Full Evaluation Suite (Recommended)\n   118→\n   119→Run the complete test dataset with a specified document type in json (without grounding eval):\n   120→\n   121→```bash\n   122→oagent eval ppt.ungrounded\n   123→```\n   124→\n   125→Run the complete test dataset with a specified document type in json (with grounding eval):\n   126→\n   127→```bash\n   128→oagent eval ppt.groundingeval\n   129→```\n   130→change to word.groundingeval to run for word.\n   131→\n   132→**Note**: You may run `oagent eval alias` to see all available aliases.\n   133→\n   134→This will:\n   135→\n   136→- Run all prompts in the dataset (distributed across containers)\n   137→- Generate detailed results per test\n   138→- Create aggregate metrics\n   139→- Produce JSON and HTML reports.\n   140→\n   141→**Expected output:**\n   142→\n   143→```\n   144→Using Python executable: C:\\src\\OfficeAgent\\venv\\Scripts\\python.exe\n   145→Running alias \"ppt.ungrounded\"\n   146→  Batch file: ./eval/datasets/official_ppt_officeagent_societas_taste.json\n   147→  Config file: ./eval/configs/dev_ppt_config.json\n   148→[INFO] No existing compose stack 'officeagent-eval' found, starting clean\n   149→[INFO] Starting token server on port 12000...\n   150→[INFO] Token server started successfully (PID: 37552)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JFxuCnY2KejKQcmVMsFzvh","session_id":"98ef6066-2367-415b-b616-f95ed64be17a","uuid":"3215111e-f7df-48b6-a049-111d277a795e"}
