{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AU7kaGXRrmfPoh4L8qumog","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me compile the findings into a clear report.\n\n## Module Structure & Architecture Overview\n\nBased on my deep exploration of the OfficeAgent modules directory, here's a comprehensive analysis of how these modules connect and what each provides:\n\n### 1. **Core Module** (`@officeagent/core`)\n**Location:** `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/core/`\n\n**Purpose:** Foundation infrastructure for the entire system.\n\n**Key Components:**\n- **Agent System:** \n  - `AgentRegistry` - In-memory registry for agent discovery\n  - `BaseAgent` - Abstract base class for all agents\n  - `AgentManager` - Management of agent lifecycle\n  - `AgentWorkspaceManager` - File/directory management for agent output\n  \n- **WebSocket Infrastructure:**\n  - `WebSocketManager` - Singleton managing client connections and message transmission with payload size validation\n  - `WebSocketRouter` - Routes incoming messages to handlers by type\n  - `JsonRpcRouter` - Routes JSON-RPC 2.0 compliant messages with request/response correlation\n  - `OfficeAgentSettingsManager` - Settings storage with change gates and flights\n\n- **Logging:** Structured logging with telemetry-safe logging functions (never logs PII in logInfo/logWarn/logError)\n\n- **Exports:** All agent, logging, websocket, and utility exports\n\n### 2. **API Module** (`@officeagent/api`)\n**Location:** `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/api/`\n\n**Purpose:** HTTP/WebSocket API server serving as the main entry point for document generation requests.\n\n**Key Files:**\n- **`app.ts`** - Main server setup:\n  - Initializes external HTTP server (port 6010) + WebSocket at `/ws`\n  - Initializes internal HTTP server (port 6011) for internal handlers\n  - Loads environment configuration\n  - Registers session handlers and agent initialization\n  - Implements `/generateDocument` endpoint that:\n    - Accepts user queries, grounding content, web/enterprise search toggles\n    - Manages conversation state and prevents concurrent requests\n    - Supports flight flags for A/B testing (e.g., `-enableEnterpriseSearchV2`)\n    - Calls agent's `run()` method and returns generated file info\n\n- **Handler Registry System** (`internal/registry/handler-registry.ts`):\n  - `InternalMessageHandler<TRequest, TResponse>` interface\n  - `HandlerRegistry` - Central registry for message handlers\n  - Supports streaming and non-streaming handlers\n  - Request validation, execution, error handling with typed payloads\n  - Timeout management (default 30s)\n\n- **WebSocket Handlers** (`websocket/handlers/`):\n  - `mcp.ts` - MCP (Model Context Protocol) request/response forwarding\n  - `llm-proxy-handler.ts` - LLM message handling\n  - `enterprise-search-sydney-handler.ts` - Sydney search integration\n  - `excel-headless-handler.ts` - Excel computation\n  - `image-search-handler.ts` - Image grounding\n  - `llm-logger.ts` - Message logging\n\n- **Internal Handlers** (`internal/handlers/`):\n  - Citation injection, Excel parsing, PPTX slide counting\n  - Enterprise/web search, image search, user context\n  - File creation tracking\n\n- **Routes:**\n  - `routes-external.ts` - Public HTTP endpoints (/ping, /health, /download, /upload, /generateDocument)\n  - `routes-internal.ts` - Internal endpoints (6011 port)\n\n### 3. **Message Protocol Module** (`@officeagent/message-protocol`)\n**Location:** `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/message-protocol/`\n\n**Purpose:** WebSocket message contract and type definitions.\n\n**Key Types:**\n- **Core Types:**\n  - `Message<T>` - Base message with type, id, sessionId, payload\n  - `ResponseMessage<T>` - Message with requestId for correlation\n  - `ClientMetadata` - Client app info (appName, appPlatform, agentName)\n  - `RequestContext` - Grounding toggles, annotations, scenario type\n\n- **MessageType Enum:** 100+ message types including:\n  - LLM types: `llm_request`, `llm_response`, `openai_request`, `openai_response`\n  - Enterprise search: file, email, chat, transcript, meeting, people, calendar search\n  - Citations, Excel, PowerPoint, sensitivity labels, web search, image search\n  - MCP, user context, session init\n\n- **JSON-RPC 2.0 Protocol:**\n  - `JsonRpcRequest` - Request with id (expects response)\n  - `JsonRpcNotification` - No id (fire-and-forget)\n  - `JsonRpcResponse` - Response with id matching request\n  - Type guards: `isJsonRpcRequest()`, `isJsonRpcNotification()`, etc.\n\n- **Grounding Types:**\n  - Enterprise search results (enterprise.ts)\n  - Image grounding (image.ts)\n  - Web search (web.ts)\n  - Citations for clickable links (citations.ts)\n\n### 4. **Chain-of-Thought Module** (`@officeagent/chain-of-thought`)\n**Location:** `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/chain-of-thought/`\n\n**Purpose:** Track and display agent reasoning steps to users.\n\n**Architecture:**\n- **State Management:** Centralized `ChainOfThoughtState` with:\n  - File descriptors for writing COT content\n  - Message queue for processing\n  - Message processor for handling different message types\n  - Queue manager for task coordination\n\n- **Key Functions:**\n  - `initChainOfThought()` - Initialize with output/log directories\n  - `trackChainOfThought()` - Add message to COT chain\n  - `closeChainOfThought()` - Flush and finalize\n  - `messageProcessor` - Processes messages and writes to files/output\n\n- **Components:**\n  - `FileHandler` - Write COT to files\n  - `MessageProcessor` - Process and transform messages\n  - `QueueManager` - Handle async queue coordination\n  - `ChainOfThoughtContentNotifier` - Notify of updates\n\n### 5. **MCP-Proxy Module** (`@officeagent/mcp-proxy`)\n**Location:** `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/mcp-proxy/`\n\n**Purpose:** Bridge between OfficeAgent and Model Context Protocol (MCP) servers.\n\n**Key File:** `src/mcp-proxy/local-mcp.ts`\n- Creates McpServer wrapping around local tools\n- **File Path Transformation:** Converts `directAttachmentFilePaths` to base64-encoded `directAttachments`\n  - Supported tools: `SendEmailWithAttachmentsAsync`, `ReplyToMessageAsync`\n  - Reads files, encodes as base64, includes MIME type\n- Loads tools from JSON file at runtime\n- HTTP endpoint proxy to MCP at http://localhost:6011/mcp\n\n### 6. **Orchestrator Module** (`@officeagent/orchestrator`)\n**Location:** `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/orchestrator/`\n\n**Purpose:** Provider-agnostic abstraction layer for multi-provider agent execution (Claude, GitHub Copilot, Azure OpenAI).\n\n**Core Interface - `IOrchestrator`:**\n```typescript\ninterface IOrchestrator {\n  run(request: OrchestratorRequest): Promise<OrchestratorResult>  // Batch mode\n  runStream(request: OrchestratorRequest): AsyncIterable<OrchestratorMessage>  // Streaming\n  interrupt(): Promise<void>  // Cancel execution\n}\n```\n\n**Key Types:**\n- **OrchestratorRequest:** Prompt, system prompt, model, reasoning effort, tools, environment, hooks\n- **OrchestratorMessage:** Normalized message (system, assistant, tool_use, tool_result, result)\n- **OrchestratorResult:** Content, status, usage (tokens, cost, duration, turns)\n- **OrchestratorHooks:** Observe activity (on message, tool use)\n- **GenericToolHooks:** Pre/post tool use interception\n\n**Providers:**\n- `ClaudeOrchestrator` - Claude SDK wrapper\n- `GhcpOrchestrator` - GitHub Copilot wrapper\n- `BaseOrchestrator` - Abstract base with common logic\n\n**Factory Pattern:**\n- `createOrchestrator()` - Provider selection at runtime\n- `HarnessBuilder` - Build orchestrator with all dependencies\n- `ChainOfThoughtAdapter` - Adapt orchestrator messages to COT format\n\n### 7. **Grounding Module** (`@officeagent/grounding`)\n**Location:** `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/grounding/`\n\n**Purpose:** RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) pipeline for enterprise data sources and citations.\n\n**Pipeline Architecture - 4-Stage Design:**\n\n1. **Preprocessor** (`BasePreprocessor`):\n   - Validates input requests\n   - Enriches with metadata\n   - Builds substrate search requests\n   - Abstract with subclasses for specific operations\n\n2. **Retriever** (`BaseRetriever`):\n   - Fetches data from enterprise sources\n   - Handles timeouts and retries\n   - Converts external responses to internal format\n   - Tracks timing metrics\n\n3. **Postprocessor** (`BasePostprocessor`):\n   - Transforms raw responses\n   - Extracts structured data\n   - Subclasses handle specific entity types:\n     - `EmailExtractor` - Email content\n     - `FileExtractor` - File metadata\n     - `ChatExtractor` - Chat/Teams messages\n     - `MeetingExtractor` - Meeting info\n     - `PeopleExtractor` - User profiles\n     - `CalendarExtractor` - Calendar events\n     - `TranscriptExtractor` - Meeting transcripts\n\n4. **Storage** (`BaseStorage`):\n   - Persists processed results\n   - Subclasses implement different backends\n\n**Orchestrator** (`orchestrator.ts`):\n- Chains pipeline stages together\n- Manages context and timings\n- Handles parallel stage execution\n- Error propagation\n\n**Enterprise Search Types:**\n- Search orchestrators (fetch, search, user-context)\n- Specific entity type searches (file, email, chat, etc.)\n\n**A2A Communication:**\n- HTTP server/client for Agent-to-Agent communication\n- Service types define request/response contracts\n\n**Key Exports:**\n- Pipeline abstractions\n- Enterprise/image/web/citation grounding types\n- Shared utilities and helpers\n\n---\n\n## How They Connect\n\n**Message Flow:**\n```\nClient (WebSocket) \n  ↓\nAPI Module (app.ts) → WebSocket on port 6010\n  ↓\nCore WebSocketManager/Router\n  ↓\nHandler (via registry or wsRouter)\n  ↓\nMessage-Protocol types (validate structure)\n  ↓\nOrchestrator (execute via Claude/GHCP)\n  ↓\nGrounding Pipeline (if needed):\n  Preprocessor → Retriever → Postprocessor → Storage\n  ↓\nAgent execution (create-agent, ppt-agent, etc.)\n  ↓\nChain-of-Thought (track reasoning)\n  ↓\nResponse back to client\n```\n\n**Configuration & State:**\n- Settings flow through `OfficeAgentSettingsManager` (in core)\n- Flights/experiments controlled via changeGates\n- Agent registry in core serves agents registered during startup\n- Session context maintains conversation state\n\n---\n\n**Absolute Paths to Key Files:**\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/core/src/websocket/websocket-manager.ts`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/core/src/websocket/router.ts`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/core/src/agent/agent-registry.ts`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/api/src/app.ts`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/api/src/internal/registry/handler-registry.ts`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/message-protocol/src/types/core.ts`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/message-protocol/src/types/message-type.ts`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/chain-of-thought/src/manager.ts`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/mcp-proxy/src/mcp-proxy/local-mcp.ts`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/orchestrator/src/types.ts`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/grounding/src/orchestrator.ts`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/grounding/src/base-preprocessor.ts`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/grounding/src/base-retriever.ts`"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ab25c3c7736211383 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 76310\ntool_uses: 48\nduration_ms: 80043</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"98ef6066-2367-415b-b616-f95ed64be17a","uuid":"5374021e-5d9e-4f3a-8f82-0834780267f4","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the OfficeAgent modules directory at C:/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/. I need to understand:\n\n1. Read the core module structure (modules/core/) - look at package.json and key expo