{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VbaCZT2x5MAVT4SegakNyh","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have enough information. Let me compile a comprehensive report of my findings.\n\n## Comprehensive Report: OfficeAgent Agents Architecture & Patterns\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the OfficeAgent agents directory, here are my findings:\n\n### 1. CLAUDE.md Files Analysis\n\nI examined CLAUDE.md files for 4 key agents, revealing distinct purposes and architectures:\n\n**create-agent** (`/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/create-agent/CLAUDE.md`)\n- Full-featured document creation agent using Claude SDK directly\n- Supports Word, PowerPoint, and Excel generation with enterprise search\n- Multiple prompt versions (1.0.0, 1.1.0, 1.2.0, 1.2.1) with feature progression\n- Complex sub-agent pipelines (outline generators, content extractors, section generators)\n- Skills-based architecture with flight-controlled overrides\n- Key file: `src/create-agent.ts` (~84KB of orchestration logic)\n\n**office-agent** (`/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/office-agent/CLAUDE.md`)\n- Simplified variant using GhcpOrchestrator (GitHub Copilot SDK wrapper)\n- Single version (1.2.0), no sub-agents\n- Shares services and hooks from create-agent via `@officeagent/create-agent` exports\n- Includes request interceptors but no versioned prompts beyond 1.2.0\n- Smaller attack surface, optimized for simplicity\n\n**ppt-creation-agent** (`/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/ppt-creation-agent/CLAUDE.md`)\n- Minimal, specialized HTML parser agent\n- No versions, flights, or filters\n- Direct HTML → PPTX conversion (no LLM orchestration)\n- Very simple registry with only id, name, description\n\n**excel-agent** (`/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/excel-agent/CLAUDE.md`)\n- Copilot SDK-based Excel editing agent\n- Local Office.js execution via proxy pattern (augloop integration)\n- Uses GitHub Copilot SDK, not Claude SDK\n- Custom message protocol (ScriptRequest/ScriptResponse for Excel operations)\n- Single version (1.0.0)\n\n---\n\n### 2. Registry.ts Pattern Analysis\n\nAll agents follow a common `AgentRegistryConfig` interface from `@officeagent/core`:\n\n**create-agent registry** (26KB file):\n```typescript\n{\n    id, name, packageName, description,\n    defaultVersion: '1.0.0',\n    versions: [\n        {\n            version, model, maxThinkingTokens, maxTurns,\n            systemPrompt, raiGuidelines,\n            allowedTools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep, Task, Skill, ...],\n            disallowedTools: [WebSearch, WebFetch],\n            skills: ['docx', 'pptx', 'xlsx', 'image-search'],\n            subagents: [docx-page-subagent, pptx-*, xlsx-*],\n            scripts: [send-clarification-config.js, ...],\n            intentDetectionDir: [CLARIFICATION.md, ...]\n        }\n    ],\n    flights: [\n        {\n            flightKey: 'OfficeAgent.EnableCreateAgent@1.1.0',\n            config: { version: '1.1.0' }\n        },\n        // Complex overwrites for flight-based prompt replacements\n        {\n            flightKey: 'OfficeAgent.CreateAgent.NewDesign',\n            applicableVersions: ['1.2.0'],\n            config: {\n                overwrites: [\n                    { src: 'pptx/newDesign/SKILL.md', dst: 'skills/pptx/SKILL.md' },\n                    // ... many more\n                ]\n            }\n        }\n    ],\n    filters: []\n}\n```\n\n**office-agent registry** (67 lines):\n- Single version (1.2.0)\n- Uses `harness: 'ghcp'` (GitHub Copilot harness)\n- Minimal flights (only model override for GPT-5)\n- Skills: ['docx', 'pptx', 'xlsx', 'research']\n- No subagents\n\n**ppt-creation-agent registry** (14 lines):\n- Bare minimum: only id, name, packageName, description\n- No versions, skills, subagents, or flights\n\n**excel-agent registry** (30 lines):\n- Imports system prompt as TypeScript constant: `import { SYSTEM_PROMPT as SYSTEM_PROMPT_v_1_0_0 } from './prompts/1.0.0/system-prompt'`\n- Uses `templateSettings` instead of standard model config\n- Copilot model: 'gpt-52-reasoning'\n\n---\n\n### 3. Main Agent Implementation: create-agent.ts\n\n**Key Architecture** (lines 1-100):\n```typescript\nexport class CreateAgent extends BaseAgent {\n    // Core dependencies\n    private queryInterruptManager = new QueryInterruptManager();\n    private externalDocTracker = new ExternalDocumentTracker();\n    private context?: SessionContext;\n    private hookRegistry: HookRegistry;\n    \n    // Services\n    private chatHistoryService = new ChatHistoryService();\n    private agentStateService = new AgentStateService();\n    private requestInterceptors: RequestInterceptors | undefined;\n    \n    public constructor() {\n        super(agentRegistry);\n        \n        // Hook registry with agent-type specific providers\n        this.hookRegistry = new HookRegistry();\n        this.hookRegistry.register('base', new BaseHooksProvider());\n        this.hookRegistry.register(AgentType.WordAgent, new WordHooksProvider());\n        this.hookRegistry.register(AgentType.ExcelAgent, new ExcelHooksProvider());\n        this.hookRegistry.register(AgentType.PowerPointAgent, new PowerPointHooksProvider());\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Implementation Pattern**:\n- Extends `BaseAgent` from `@officeagent/core`\n- Registers hooks by AgentType enum (word, excel, powerpoint)\n- Manages multi-turn conversation with chat history service\n- Handles Excel headless API registration during initialize()\n- Uses Claude SDK directly via `claude` function calls\n- Supports request interceptors (clarification, intent detection, language detection)\n\n---\n\n### 4. Prompt Directory Structure\n\n**create-agent versioned structure** (`src/prompts/<version>/`):\n```\n1.0.0/\n├── system-prompt.md          (EJS template)\n├── rai.md                     (Responsible AI)\n├── agent-capabilities/        (word.md, excel.md, ppt.md)\n├── intent-detection/          (CLARIFICATION.md, INTENT_DETECTION_PROMPT.md, etc.)\n├── skills/                    (Named skill directories)\n│   ├── docx/                  (Word skill)\n│   │   ├── SKILL.md           (Main skill definition)\n│   │   ├── content/\n│   │   ├── conversion/        (json_to_docx, json_to_html pipelines)\n│   │   ├── core/\n│   │   ├── themes/\n│   │   ├── validation/\n│   │   └── scripts/\n│   ├── pptx/                  (PowerPoint skill)\n│   ├── xlsx/                  (Excel skill)\n│   ├── image-search/\n│   └── web-search/\n├── subagents/                 (Named subagent definitions)\n│   ├── docx-page-subagent.md\n│   ├── pptx-html-creator-validator.md\n│   ├── enterprise-search.md\n│   └── ...\n└── scripts/                   (Runtime scripts deployed to agent)\n    ├── send-clarification-config.js\n    ├── web-search.js\n    └── ...\n\n1.1.0/                         (Same structure, evolved workflows)\n├── overwrites/                (Flight-conditional replacements)\n│   ├── docx/\n│   ├── pptx/\n│   ├── xlsx/\n│   └── researcher/\n\n1.2.0/                         (Latest evolution)\n```\n\n**office-agent structure** (simpler):\n```\nsrc/prompts/1.2.0/\n├── system-prompt.md\n├── rai.md\n├── skills/\n│   ├── docx/                  (Complete docx implementation)\n│   ├── pptx/                  (Complete pptx implementation)\n│   ├── xlsx/                  (Complete xlsx implementation)\n│   └── research/              (Research skill)\n└── intent-detection/          (Copied from create-agent)\n```\n\n**ppt-creation-agent**:\n- No prompts directory (HTML-only processing agent)\n- Direct HTML rendering implementation in TypeScript\n\n---\n\n### 5. Skill Organization Pattern\n\nEach skill lives at `src/prompts/<version>/skills/<name>/SKILL.md` with YAML frontmatter:\n\n```markdown\n---\nname: Word Document Suite\ndescription: Creates .docx files with professional formatting...\n---\n\n# Skill Implementation Details\n```\n\n**Skill Structure** (example: docx in 1.0.0):\n- `SKILL.md` - Main skill entry point (17KB for Word)\n- `CLARIFICATION.md` - Clarification prompts for user preferences\n- `clarification.py` - Interactive clarification script\n- `content/` - Content generation workflows\n- `conversion/` - File format converters (json_to_docx.py, json_to_html)\n- `core/` - Core generation logic\n- `themes/` - Theme definitions (Python files with color/font specs)\n- `validation/` - Post-generation validators\n- `web-search/`, `sydney-outline/` - Search and outline workflows\n- `scripts/` - Runtime utilities\n\n**Skills by agent**:\n- create-agent 1.0.0: docx, pptx, xlsx, image-search, enterprise-research, enterprise-search-sydney, pdf, web-fetch, web-search\n- create-agent 1.1.0+: docx, pptx, xlsx, image-search (removed enterprise-specific skills)\n- office-agent 1.2.0: docx, pptx, xlsx, research (all bundled locally)\n\n---\n\n### 6. Sub-Agents & Orchestration\n\n**Sub-agents are defined in `subagents/<name>.md`** with YAML frontmatter:\n\n```markdown\n---\nname: docx-outline-generator\ndescription: [Word Document Outline Generation] Conducts strategic search, \nanalyzes results, generates outline ready for section generation.\ntools: Write, Read, Bash, TodoWrite, TodoRead\n---\n```\n\n**create-agent 1.0.0 sub-agents** (11 total):\n- `docx-page-subagent` - Per-page generation with parallel processing\n- `pptx-html-creator-validator` - Creates HTML from outline, validates structure\n- `pptx-outline-validator` - Validates presentation outline completeness\n- `enterprise-search` - Enterprise data search orchestrator\n- `enterprise-*-analyst` (6 types: chat, email, file, meeting, people, transcript)\n- `enterprise-curator` - Synthesizes multi-source insights\n\n**create-agent 1.1.0+ sub-agents** (9 total, new pipeline):\n- `docx-outline-generator` → `docx-section-generator`\n- `pptx-outline-generator` → `pptx-html-creator-validator` → `pptx-html-updater`\n- `xlsx-resource-discovery` → `xlsx-content-extractor` → `xlsx-outline-generator` → `xlsx-office-js-generator`\n\n**office-agent**:\n- No sub-agents (all work done in main agent)\n\n---\n\n### 7. Hooks Organization\n\n**Hooks files** in `src/hooks/`:\n- `base-hooks.ts` - Performance tracking, chain-of-thought (shared by all agents)\n- `word-hooks.ts` - Word-specific hooks (docx validation, themes)\n- `excel-hooks.ts` - Excel-specific hooks (blocks direct .xlsx creation, enforces headless API)\n- `ppt-hooks.ts` - PowerPoint-specific hooks (HTML validation, slide counting)\n- `terminal-hooks.ts` - Dev-only terminal output hooks\n- `config.ts` - Hook configuration constants\n- `hooks-utils.ts` - Utility functions\n- `file-observer-hooks.ts` - File system observation hooks\n- `ppt-outline-sanitization-hooks.ts` - PPT-specific outline sanitization\n\n**Hook Registration Pattern** (from base-hooks.ts excerpt):\n```typescript\nexport class BaseHooksProvider implements HookProvider {\n    createHooks(context: SessionContext): AgentHooks {\n        // Create performance tracking hooks\n        const perfHooks = createPerfTrackingHooks(...);\n        \n        // Combine hooks using Claude SDK format\n        const claudeHooks: Options['hooks'] = {\n            PreToolUse: [{ hooks: [perfHooks.PreToolUse] }],\n            PostToolUse: [{ hooks: [perfHooks.PostToolUse] }],\n            SessionStart: [{ hooks: [perfHooks.SessionStart] }],\n            SessionEnd: [{ hooks: [perfHooks.SessionEnd] }],\n        };\n        \n        return { claude: claudeHooks, startTurn: createBaseStartTurnHook(context) };\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. Services Architecture\n\n**create-agent services** in `src/services/`:\n- `performance-tracker-service.ts` - Timing/metrics tracking\n- `chat-history-service.ts` - Multi-turn conversation state\n- `agent-state-service.ts` - Document generation state tracking\n- `websocket-messenger-service.ts` - WebSocket message routing\n- `claude-message-logger-service.ts` - LLM interaction logging\n- `file-watcher-service.ts` - Workspace file monitoring\n- `query-interrupt-manager.ts` - Request cancellation\n- `external-document-tracker.ts` - Excel/cloud file creation tracking\n- `excel/` subdirectory - Excel-specific services (headless API, metadata)\n- `request-interceptors/` - Intent detection, clarification, language detection\n- `image-processor-service.ts` - Image handling\n\n**office-agent**:\n- Imports most services from create-agent via shared exports in `create-agent/src/shared.ts`\n\n**excel-agent services** in `src/protocol/` and `src/copilot/`:\n- `script-executor.ts` - Promise-based Office.js script execution\n- `copilot-bridge.ts` - Copilot SDK session management\n- `event-adapter.ts` - SDK events → QueryStatus message transformation\n\n---\n\n### 9. Core Differences Between Agents\n\n| Feature | create-agent | office-agent | ppt-creation-agent | excel-agent |\n|---------|-------------|-------------|-------------------|------------|\n| **Orchestrator** | Claude SDK direct | GhcpOrchestrator (Copilot SDK) | None (HTML-only) | Copilot SDK (GitHub) |\n| **Versions** | 4 (1.0.0, 1.1.0, 1.2.0, 1.2.1) | 1 (1.2.0) | None | 1 (1.0.0) |\n| **Sub-agents** | 11 (1.0.0), 9 (1.1.0+) | 0 | 0 | 0 |\n| **Skills** | 9 total | 4 local | 0 | 0 |\n| **Flights** | 20+ | 1 | 0 | 1 |\n| **Prompts** | Versioned, EJS templates | Single version | None | Single TypeScript constant |\n| **Request Interceptors** | Yes (clarification, intent, language) | Yes (shared) | No | No |\n| **Chain of Thought** | Full streaming | Via hooks | No | No |\n| **Hooks** | 9 files, type-specific | 2 files, simpler | No custom hooks | Tools-based |\n\n---\n\n### 10. Type System\n\n**Core types** in `src/types.ts`:\n```typescript\nenum AgentType {\n    WordAgent = 'word',\n    ExcelAgent = 'excel',\n    PowerPointAgent = 'powerpoint',\n}\n\ninterface GeneratedFileInfo {\n    filename: string;\n    filePath: string;\n    size: number;\n}\n\ninterface ExternalDocumentInfo {\n    fileName?, webUrl?, documentUrl?, isEdit?, fileId?, driveId?, driveItemId?, error?\n}\n\ninterface DocumentGenerationCallbacks {\n    onDocumentGenerationAttempted?(...): void;\n    onDocumentGenerationCompleted?(...): void;\n    onDocumentGenerationFailed?(...): void;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Summary of Common Agent Pattern\n\n1. **Registry-driven configuration**: All agents register via `AgentRegistryConfig` with versions, flights, and filters\n2. **Extensible hooks**: HookRegistry allows per-agent-type customization\n3. **Service architecture**: Shared services from core + agent-specific services\n4. **Skill-based prompting**: Skills live in `src/prompts/<version>/skills/<name>/SKILL.md`\n5. **Sub-agent definitions**: Optional, defined as `.md` files with YAML frontmatter\n6. **Flight-based overrides**: Complex prompt/config changes via flight system with overwrites\n7. **WebSocket messaging**: All agents communicate via message protocol types\n8. **Chain-of-thought tracking**: Performance and progress tracking via hooks\n\nThe architecture supports ranging complexity from minimal (ppt-creation-agent) to enterprise-scale (create-agent) while maintaining a consistent structural pattern."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: acd9cf5cfb285b40c (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 67818\ntool_uses: 36\nduration_ms: 88048</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"98ef6066-2367-415b-b616-f95ed64be17a","uuid":"d7b32f71-59f1-4524-8504-c3649d04f993","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the OfficeAgent agents directory at C:/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/. I need to understand:\n\n1. Read CLAUDE.md files for at least 3-4 agents (create-agent, office-agent, ppt-creation-agent, excel-agent)\n2. Look at registry.ts files for 3-4 agents to understand the registration pattern\n3. Look at the main agent implementation file for create-agent\n4. Look at prompt directory structure for create-agent and ppt-creation-agent\n5. Identify how skills are organized within agents\n\nBe thorough - read actual file contents, not just list directories. Focus on understanding the common agent pattern and how they differ.","agentId":"acd9cf5cfb285b40c","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have enough information. Let me compile a comprehensive report of my findings.\n\n## Comprehensive Report: OfficeAgent Agents Architecture & Patterns\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the OfficeAgent agents directory, here are my findings:\n\n### 1. CLAUDE.md Files Analysis\n\nI examined CLAUDE.md files for 4 key agents, revealing distinct purposes and architectures:\n\n**create-agent** (`/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/create-agent/CLAUDE.md`)\n- Full-featured document creation agent using Claude SDK directly\n- Supports Word, PowerPoint, and Excel generation with enterprise search\n- Multiple prompt versions (1.0.0, 1.1.0, 1.2.0, 1.2.1) with feature progression\n- Complex sub-agent pipelines (outline generators, content extractors, section generators)\n- Skills-based architecture with flight-controlled overrides\n- Key file: `src/create-agent.ts` (~84KB of orchestration logic)\n\n**office-agent** (`/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/office-agent/CLAUDE.md`)\n- Simplified variant using GhcpOrchestrator (GitHub Copilot SDK wrapper)\n- Single version (1.2.0), no sub-agents\n- Shares services and hooks from create-agent via `@officeagent/create-agent` exports\n- Includes request interceptors but no versioned prompts beyond 1.2.0\n- Smaller attack surface, optimized for simplicity\n\n**ppt-creation-agent** (`/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/ppt-creation-agent/CLAUDE.md`)\n- Minimal, specialized HTML parser agent\n- No versions, flights, or filters\n- Direct HTML → PPTX conversion (no LLM orchestration)\n- Very simple registry with only id, name, description\n\n**excel-agent** (`/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/excel-agent/CLAUDE.md`)\n- Copilot SDK-based Excel editing agent\n- Local Office.js execution via proxy pattern (augloop integration)\n- Uses GitHub Copilot SDK, not Claude SDK\n- Custom message protocol (ScriptRequest/ScriptResponse for Excel operations)\n- Single version (1.0.0)\n\n---\n\n### 2. Registry.ts Pattern Analysis\n\nAll agents follow a common `AgentRegistryConfig` interface from `@officeagent/core`:\n\n**create-agent registry** (26KB file):\n```typescript\n{\n    id, name, packageName, description,\n    defaultVersion: '1.0.0',\n    versions: [\n        {\n            version, model, maxThinkingTokens, maxTurns,\n            systemPrompt, raiGuidelines,\n            allowedTools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep, Task, Skill, ...],\n            disallowedTools: [WebSearch, WebFetch],\n            skills: ['docx', 'pptx', 'xlsx', 'image-search'],\n            subagents: [docx-page-subagent, pptx-*, xlsx-*],\n            scripts: [send-clarification-config.js, ...],\n            intentDetectionDir: [CLARIFICATION.md, ...]\n        }\n    ],\n    flights: [\n        {\n            flightKey: 'OfficeAgent.EnableCreateAgent@1.1.0',\n            config: { version: '1.1.0' }\n        },\n        // Complex overwrites for flight-based prompt replacements\n        {\n            flightKey: 'OfficeAgent.CreateAgent.NewDesign',\n            applicableVersions: ['1.2.0'],\n            config: {\n                overwrites: [\n                    { src: 'pptx/newDesign/SKILL.md', dst: 'skills/pptx/SKILL.md' },\n                    // ... many more\n                ]\n            }\n        }\n    ],\n    filters: []\n}\n```\n\n**office-agent registry** (67 lines):\n- Single version (1.2.0)\n- Uses `harness: 'ghcp'` (GitHub Copilot harness)\n- Minimal flights (only model override for GPT-5)\n- Skills: ['docx', 'pptx', 'xlsx', 'research']\n- No subagents\n\n**ppt-creation-agent registry** (14 lines):\n- Bare minimum: only id, name, packageName, description\n- No versions, skills, subagents, or flights\n\n**excel-agent registry** (30 lines):\n- Imports system prompt as TypeScript constant: `import { SYSTEM_PROMPT as SYSTEM_PROMPT_v_1_0_0 } from './prompts/1.0.0/system-prompt'`\n- Uses `templateSettings` instead of standard model config\n- Copilot model: 'gpt-52-reasoning'\n\n---\n\n### 3. Main Agent Implementation: create-agent.ts\n\n**Key Architecture** (lines 1-100):\n```typescript\nexport class CreateAgent extends BaseAgent {\n    // Core dependencies\n    private queryInterruptManager = new QueryInterruptManager();\n    private externalDocTracker = new ExternalDocumentTracker();\n    private context?: SessionContext;\n    private hookRegistry: HookRegistry;\n    \n    // Services\n    private chatHistoryService = new ChatHistoryService();\n    private agentStateService = new AgentStateService();\n    private requestInterceptors: RequestInterceptors | undefined;\n    \n    public constructor() {\n        super(agentRegistry);\n        \n        // Hook registry with agent-type specific providers\n        this.hookRegistry = new HookRegistry();\n        this.hookRegistry.register('base', new BaseHooksProvider());\n        this.hookRegistry.register(AgentType.WordAgent, new WordHooksProvider());\n        this.hookRegistry.register(AgentType.ExcelAgent, new ExcelHooksProvider());\n        this.hookRegistry.register(AgentType.PowerPointAgent, new PowerPointHooksProvider());\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Implementation Pattern**:\n- Extends `BaseAgent` from `@officeagent/core`\n- Registers hooks by AgentType enum (word, excel, powerpoint)\n- Manages multi-turn conversation with chat history service\n- Handles Excel headless API registration during initialize()\n- Uses Claude SDK directly via `claude` function calls\n- Supports request interceptors (clarification, intent detection, language detection)\n\n---\n\n### 4. Prompt Directory Structure\n\n**create-agent versioned structure** (`src/prompts/<version>/`):\n```\n1.0.0/\n├── system-prompt.md          (EJS template)\n├── rai.md                     (Responsible AI)\n├── agent-capabilities/        (word.md, excel.md, ppt.md)\n├── intent-detection/          (CLARIFICATION.md, INTENT_DETECTION_PROMPT.md, etc.)\n├── skills/                    (Named skill directories)\n│   ├── docx/                  (Word skill)\n│   │   ├── SKILL.md           (Main skill definition)\n│   │   ├── content/\n│   │   ├── conversion/        (json_to_docx, json_to_html pipelines)\n│   │   ├── core/\n│   │   ├── themes/\n│   │   ├── validation/\n│   │   └── scripts/\n│   ├── pptx/                  (PowerPoint skill)\n│   ├── xlsx/                  (Excel skill)\n│   ├── image-search/\n│   └── web-search/\n├── subagents/                 (Named subagent definitions)\n│   ├── docx-page-subagent.md\n│   ├── pptx-html-creator-validator.md\n│   ├── enterprise-search.md\n│   └── ...\n└── scripts/                   (Runtime scripts deployed to agent)\n    ├── send-clarification-config.js\n    ├── web-search.js\n    └── ...\n\n1.1.0/                         (Same structure, evolved workflows)\n├── overwrites/                (Flight-conditional replacements)\n│   ├── docx/\n│   ├── pptx/\n│   ├── xlsx/\n│   └── researcher/\n\n1.2.0/                         (Latest evolution)\n```\n\n**office-agent structure** (simpler):\n```\nsrc/prompts/1.2.0/\n├── system-prompt.md\n├── rai.md\n├── skills/\n│   ├── docx/                  (Complete docx implementation)\n│   ├── pptx/                  (Complete pptx implementation)\n│   ├── xlsx/                  (Complete xlsx implementation)\n│   └── research/              (Research skill)\n└── intent-detection/          (Copied from create-agent)\n```\n\n**ppt-creation-agent**:\n- No prompts directory (HTML-only processing agent)\n- Direct HTML rendering implementation in TypeScript\n\n---\n\n### 5. Skill Organization Pattern\n\nEach skill lives at `src/prompts/<version>/skills/<name>/SKILL.md` with YAML frontmatter:\n\n```markdown\n---\nname: Word Document Suite\ndescription: Creates .docx files with professional formatting...\n---\n\n# Skill Implementation Details\n```\n\n**Skill Structure** (example: docx in 1.0.0):\n- `SKILL.md` - Main skill entry point (17KB for Word)\n- `CLARIFICATION.md` - Clarification prompts for user preferences\n- `clarification.py` - Interactive clarification script\n- `content/` - Content generation workflows\n- `conversion/` - File format converters (json_to_docx.py, json_to_html)\n- `core/` - Core generation logic\n- `themes/` - Theme definitions (Python files with color/font specs)\n- `validation/` - Post-generation validators\n- `web-search/`, `sydney-outline/` - Search and outline workflows\n- `scripts/` - Runtime utilities\n\n**Skills by agent**:\n- create-agent 1.0.0: docx, pptx, xlsx, image-search, enterprise-research, enterprise-search-sydney, pdf, web-fetch, web-search\n- create-agent 1.1.0+: docx, pptx, xlsx, image-search (removed enterprise-specific skills)\n- office-agent 1.2.0: docx, pptx, xlsx, research (all bundled locally)\n\n---\n\n### 6. Sub-Agents & Orchestration\n\n**Sub-agents are defined in `subagents/<name>.md`** with YAML frontmatter:\n\n```markdown\n---\nname: docx-outline-generator\ndescription: [Word Document Outline Generation] Conducts strategic search, \nanalyzes results, generates outline ready for section generation.\ntools: Write, Read, Bash, TodoWrite, TodoRead\n---\n```\n\n**create-agent 1.0.0 sub-agents** (11 total):\n- `docx-page-subagent` - Per-page generation with parallel processing\n- `pptx-html-creator-validator` - Creates HTML from outline, validates structure\n- `pptx-outline-validator` - Validates presentation outline completeness\n- `enterprise-search` - Enterprise data search orchestrator\n- `enterprise-*-analyst` (6 types: chat, email, file, meeting, people, transcript)\n- `enterprise-curator` - Synthesizes multi-source insights\n\n**create-agent 1.1.0+ sub-agents** (9 total, new pipeline):\n- `docx-outline-generator` → `docx-section-generator`\n- `pptx-outline-generator` → `pptx-html-creator-validator` → `pptx-html-updater`\n- `xlsx-resource-discovery` → `xlsx-content-extractor` → `xlsx-outline-generator` → `xlsx-office-js-generator`\n\n**office-agent**:\n- No sub-agents (all work done in main agent)\n\n---\n\n### 7. Hooks Organization\n\n**Hooks files** in `src/hooks/`:\n- `base-hooks.ts` - Performance tracking, chain-of-thought (shared by all agents)\n- `word-hooks.ts` - Word-specific hooks (docx validation, themes)\n- `excel-hooks.ts` - Excel-specific hooks (blocks direct .xlsx creation, enforces headless API)\n- `ppt-hooks.ts` - PowerPoint-specific hooks (HTML validation, slide counting)\n- `terminal-hooks.ts` - Dev-only terminal output hooks\n- `config.ts` - Hook configuration constants\n- `hooks-utils.ts` - Utility functions\n- `file-observer-hooks.ts` - File system observation hooks\n- `ppt-outline-sanitization-hooks.ts` - PPT-specific outline sanitization\n\n**Hook Registration Pattern** (from base-hooks.ts excerpt):\n```typescript\nexport class BaseHooksProvider implements HookProvider {\n    createHooks(context: SessionContext): AgentHooks {\n        // Create performance tracking hooks\n        const perfHooks = createPerfTrackingHooks(...);\n        \n        // Combine hooks using Claude SDK format\n        const claudeHooks: Options['hooks'] = {\n            PreToolUse: [{ hooks: [perfHooks.PreToolUse] }],\n            PostToolUse: [{ hooks: [perfHooks.PostToolUse] }],\n            SessionStart: [{ hooks: [perfHooks.SessionStart] }],\n            SessionEnd: [{ hooks: [perfHooks.SessionEnd] }],\n        };\n        \n        return { claude: claudeHooks, startTurn: createBaseStartTurnHook(context) };\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. Services Architecture\n\n**create-agent services** in `src/services/`:\n- `performance-tracker-service.ts` - Timing/metrics tracking\n- `chat-history-service.ts` - Multi-turn conversation state\n- `agent-state-service.ts` - Document generation state tracking\n- `websocket-messenger-service.ts` - WebSocket message routing\n- `claude-message-logger-service.ts` - LLM interaction logging\n- `file-watcher-service.ts` - Workspace file monitoring\n- `query-interrupt-manager.ts` - Request cancellation\n- `external-document-tracker.ts` - Excel/cloud file creation tracking\n- `excel/` subdirectory - Excel-specific services (headless API, metadata)\n- `request-interceptors/` - Intent detection, clarification, language detection\n- `image-processor-service.ts` - Image handling\n\n**office-agent**:\n- Imports most services from create-agent via shared exports in `create-agent/src/shared.ts`\n\n**excel-agent services** in `src/protocol/` and `src/copilot/`:\n- `script-executor.ts` - Promise-based Office.js script execution\n- `copilot-bridge.ts` - Copilot SDK session management\n- `event-adapter.ts` - SDK events → QueryStatus message transformation\n\n---\n\n### 9. Core Differences Between Agents\n\n| Feature | create-agent | office-agent | ppt-creation-agent | excel-agent |\n|---------|-------------|-------------|-------------------|------------|\n| **Orchestrator** | Claude SDK direct | GhcpOrchestrator (Copilot SDK) | None (HTML-only) | Copilot SDK (GitHub) |\n| **Versions** | 4 (1.0.0, 1.1.0, 1.2.0, 1.2.1) | 1 (1.2.0) | None | 1 (1.0.0) |\n| **Sub-agents** | 11 (1.0.0), 9 (1.1.0+) | 0 | 0 | 0 |\n| **Skills** | 9 total | 4 local | 0 | 0 |\n| **Flights** | 20+ | 1 | 0 | 1 |\n| **Prompts** | Versioned, EJS templates | Single version | None | Single TypeScript constant |\n| **Request Interceptors** | Yes (clarification, intent, language) | Yes (shared) | No | No |\n| **Chain of Thought** | Full streaming | Via hooks | No | No |\n| **Hooks** | 9 files, type-specific | 2 files, simpler | No custom hooks | Tools-based |\n\n---\n\n### 10. Type System\n\n**Core types** in `src/types.ts`:\n```typescript\nenum AgentType {\n    WordAgent = 'word',\n    ExcelAgent = 'excel',\n    PowerPointAgent = 'powerpoint',\n}\n\ninterface GeneratedFileInfo {\n    filename: string;\n    filePath: string;\n    size: number;\n}\n\ninterface ExternalDocumentInfo {\n    fileName?, webUrl?, documentUrl?, isEdit?, fileId?, driveId?, driveItemId?, error?\n}\n\ninterface DocumentGenerationCallbacks {\n    onDocumentGenerationAttempted?(...): void;\n    onDocumentGenerationCompleted?(...): void;\n    onDocumentGenerationFailed?(...): void;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Summary of Common Agent Pattern\n\n1. **Registry-driven configuration**: All agents register via `AgentRegistryConfig` with versions, flights, and filters\n2. **Extensible hooks**: HookRegistry allows per-agent-type customization\n3. **Service architecture**: Shared services from core + agent-specific services\n4. **Skill-based prompting**: Skills live in `src/prompts/<version>/skills/<name>/SKILL.md`\n5. **Sub-agent definitions**: Optional, defined as `.md` files with YAML frontmatter\n6. **Flight-based overrides**: Complex prompt/config changes via flight system with overwrites\n7. **WebSocket messaging**: All agents communicate via message protocol types\n8. **Chain-of-thought tracking**: Performance and progress tracking via hooks\n\nThe architecture supports ranging complexity from minimal (ppt-creation-agent) to enterprise-scale (create-agent) while maintaining a consistent structural pattern."}],"totalDurationMs":88048,"totalTokens":67818,"totalToolUseCount":36,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2718,"cache_read_input_tokens":60681,"output_tokens":4412,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2718},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JFxuCnY2KejKQcmVMsFzvh","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the OfficeAgent codebase. Let me compile my findings:\n\n## Comprehensive Exploration Report: OfficeAgent Monorepo\n\n### Overview\nOfficeAgent is a sophisticated AI-powered platform for Office document creation (DOCX, PPTX, XLSX, PDF) built on the Claude Agent SDK and Azure OpenAI infrastructure. It's containerized in Docker and runs as a distributed system with multiple agents, shared modules, and development tools.\n\n---\n\n## 1. DOCUMENTATION STRUCTURE\n\n### Root Level Documentation (`docs/`)\nKey files discovered:\n\n- **`BEST_PRACTICES.md`** - Universal guidelines covering:\n  - Repo layout (agents/, modules/, .devtools/, eval/, docker/)\n  - Package naming conventions (@officeagent/* scope)\n  - File & directory conventions (src → dist/src/)\n  - Import rules (scoped imports, no relative cross-package imports)\n  - Agent development patterns (registry-first approach)\n  - Prompt organization with versioning and skills/subagents\n  - Flights (feature flags) vs Filters (runtime rules)\n  - Logging rules (no user data in telemetry)\n  - Testing structure (Jest for TS, pytest for Python)\n  - Build pipeline (lage orchestration, Docker)\n  - Common pitfalls (PowerShell requirement, Docker Desktop, Node.js >= 22, Yarn 4.10.3)\n\n- **`WORKSPACE_AGENT_DESIGN.md`** - Detailed architecture for workspace agent (Reports, Documents, Presentations, Newsletters, Blogs):\n  - Two-phase sub-agent architecture (Planning + Generation)\n  - File-based handoff between phases\n  - WebSocket flow with incremental responses\n  - Message protocol specifications\n  - Artifact types and rendering formats\n\n- **`AZURE_OPENAI_DESIGN.md`** - Azure OpenAI integration strategy with `/v1/openai` endpoint, request/response routing patterns\n\n- **`EXCEL_HEADLESS.md`** - Server-side Excel automation via Office.js in sandboxed environments\n\n- **`AgentRequestMessage-WebSocket-Flow.md`** - End-to-end WebSocket handling flow for agent requests through 8 phases (preprocessing → Claude execution → response delivery)\n\nAdditional docs for image search, teams channel fetching, OCE, Python testing, and pptx architecture documentation.\n\n---\n\n## 2. BUILD SYSTEM & CONFIGURATION\n\n### Root `package.json`\n- **Workspaces**: `.devtools/*`, `modules/*`, `agents/*` (Yarn 4.10.3)\n- **Key Scripts**:\n  - `yarn build` - Full build (lage + Docker)\n  - `yarn compile` - lage only (no Docker)\n  - `yarn start` - Start Docker + test client\n  - `yarn start:compose` - Docker Compose with scaling\n  - `yarn test` - Jest + pytest via lage\n  - `yarn lint` - ESLint across workspaces\n  - `oagent` - CLI entry point\n- **Engines**: Node >= 24, Yarn 4.10.3\n- **Dependencies**: @anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk 0.2.39\n- **DevDependencies**: TypeScript 5.9.3, Jest 30.2.0, lage 2.14.15, various build tools\n\n### `lage.config.js`\n- Orchestrates build task dependencies\n- `build` depends on `^build` (upstream packages first)\n- Caching enabled with environment glob invalidation\n- Inputs: `src/**`, `tsconfig.json`, `package.json`, `pyproject.toml`\n- Outputs: `dist/**`, `.build/.pyproject-hash`\n\n### `tsconfig.json`\n- Target: ES2020\n- Module: commonjs\n- Strict mode enabled\n- Declaration maps and source maps\n- Resolves JSON modules\n- Excludes node_modules and dist\n\n---\n\n## 3. DOCKER & RUNTIME\n\n### `docker-compose.yml`\n- Single service: `officeagent` (scalable with `--scale`)\n- Image: `officeagent:devlatest`\n- Ports exposed: 6010 (API), 6011 (internal), 6020 (debug), 7010 (grounding HTTP)\n- Environment:\n  - `OfficePy__Deployment__LocalhostOfficeAgentDevelopment: \"True\"`\n  - `OAGENT_AGENTID` (default: create-agent)\n  - `OAGENT_FLIGHTS` for feature gates\n  - `GITHUB_TOKEN` for CLI auth\n- Health check: `/health` endpoint on port 6010\n- Network: `officeagent-net` bridge\n- Secrets: pip index URL, npm credentials\n\n### `docker/Dockerfile` (first 100 lines analyzed)\n- Multi-stage build with BuildKit parallelization\n- **Poppler builder stage** - Compiles poppler from source (26.02.0) with cmake\n- **LibreOffice installer stage** - Extracts and installs LibreOffice 26.2.0 RPMs\n- **Node deps stage** - Node.js 24 + npm, installs from `docker/package.json`\n- **Final runtime stage** - Inherits from OfficePy base image (mcr.microsoft.com/officepy/codeexecutionjupyter4)\n- Environment: `CLAUDE_CODE_MAX_OUTPUT_TOKENS=64000`, `NODE_PATH` includes app modules\n\n---\n\n## 4. MONOREPO STRUCTURE\n\n### Agents (`agents/`)\n15 agent packages discovered:\n- **`create-agent`** - Core document creation (DOCX, PPTX, XLSX) using Claude SDK\n- **`gpt-create-agent`** - Azure OpenAI variant\n- **`ppt-creation-agent`** - PowerPoint-specific\n- **`ppt-edit-agent`** - PowerPoint editing\n- **`dw-accountant-agent`** - DataWorks accountant\n- **`dw-paralegal-agent`** - DataWorks paralegal\n- **`dw-marketer-agent`** - DataWorks marketer\n- **`odsp-agent`** - OneDrive/SharePoint integration\n- **`workspace-agent`** - Two-phase planner/generator for reports, documents, presentations\n- **`grounding-agent`** - Enterprise search & content retrieval\n- **`excel-agent`** - Excel-specific operations\n- **`excel-js-runner-agent`** - Office.js execution sandbox\n- **`office-agent`** - Generic office operations\n- **`ppt-agent`** - PowerPoint operations\n- Plus others\n\n### Modules (`modules/`)\n19 shared library packages:\n- **`api`** - Express server, WebSocket handling, session init\n- **`core`** - BaseAgent, logging, WebSocket router, session context\n- **`message-protocol`** - Message types (MessageType enum, Request/Response structures)\n- **`grounding`** - Enterprise search, image search, content parsing\n- **`rai`** - Responsible AI validation\n- **`excel-headless`** - Server-side Excel automation via Office.js\n- **`chain-of-thought`** - CoT display and tracking\n- **`html2pptx`** - HTML to PowerPoint conversion\n- **`json-to-docx-ooxml`** - JSON to Word OOXML conversion\n- **`mcp-proxy`** - Model Context Protocol proxy\n- **`gpt-agent`** - Azure OpenAI agent wrapper\n- **`git-remote-spo`** - SharePoint/OneDrive Git integration\n- **`excel-parser`** - Excel file parsing\n- **`pptx-assets`** - PowerPoint asset management\n- **`verify-slide-html`** - HTML validation for slides\n- **`orchestrator`** - Orchestration logic\n- **`example-cs`** - C# examples\n\n---\n\n## 5. DEVELOPMENT TOOLS (`.devtools/`)\n\n### CLI (`cli/` - @officeagent-tools/cli 1.1.1130)\nTypeScript-based command-line interface for document generation:\n- **Commands**:\n  - `ping` - Health check\n  - `generate` (alias: `gen`) - Create documents with flights, grounding content, message annotations\n  - `download` (alias: `dl`) - Download previously generated documents\n  - `new-agent` - Scaffold new agents with presets\n  - `config` - Manage CLI configuration (.env)\n  - `eval` - Run evaluations\n  - `workspace` - Workspace operations\n- **Features**:\n  - URL auto-detection (SharePoint/OneDrive links converted to annotations)\n  - Message annotations support (File, Email, Meeting, Chat, Transcript, People)\n  - Flight flag support for feature testing\n  - Report generation with debug.zip extraction\n  - Configuration via `.env` with `OAGENT_` prefix\n- **Dependencies**: chalk, commander, dotenv, execa, inquirer, node-fetch, open, ora, table\n\n### Test Client (`test-client/` - @officeagent-tools/test-client 1.1.1130)\nExternal LLM client for WebSocket relay testing:\n- Connects to WebSocket server at `/ws`\n- Forwards requests to Anthropic API\n- Uses Token Server for automatic authentication\n- Configuration: `LLM_WS_URL`, `LLM_API_HOST`, `LLM_API_PATH`\n- Dependencies: @augloop packages, @officeagent packages, chalk, dotenv, exceljs\n\n### E2E Tests (`e2e-tests/` - @officeagent/e2e-tests 1.1.1130)\nEnd-to-end testing framework:\n- Configured via JSON files (e.g., `ppt-example-config.json`)\n- Can test against local, container, cloud, or remote servers\n- Dependencies: chalk, commander, execa, fs-extra, node-fetch, ora\n\n### Eval Browser (`eval-browser/`)\nPython/Flask web UI for browsing evaluation results:\n- Runs on port 3050\n- Displays eval outputs from `eval/outputs/`\n- A/B comparison views\n- Side-by-side page images\n- Aesthetics/Fidelity/Consistency scores\n- Keyboard navigation\n\n### OCV Feedback Tool (`ocv/`)\nComprehensive feedback analysis system:\n- Scrapes OCV feedback\n- Categorizes via Claude LLM\n- Queries Kusto for telemetry\n- Searches ADO for related bugs\n- Generates HTML reports\n- MCP servers: ocv_mcp, kusto_mcp, ado_mcp\n\n### Launcher (`launcher/`)\nClaude Code desktop launcher:\n- One-time setup via `SETUP.cmd`\n- Auto-detects project directory\n- Loads `.env` automatically\n- Validates API key\n- Creates pinnable desktop shortcut\n\n---\n\n## 6. EVALUATION FRAMEWORK (`eval/`)\n\n### Structure\n- **`aliases.json`** - Aliases for common eval configurations\n- **`configs/`** - Evaluation configuration JSON files\n- **`datasets/`** - Test batch JSON files\n- **`src/cli.py`** - CLI entry point (`oagent eval`)\n- **`src/framework.py`** - Main orchestrator\n- **`src/types.py`** - Data models (EvalRequest, EvalConfig, EvalResult)\n- **`src/evaluators/`** - Modular evaluator implementations (excel, pairwise, societas, content, rule_based, intent)\n- **`src/preprocessors/`** - Data extraction before evaluation\n- **`src/scrapers/`** - Document generation via API\n- **`scripts/`** - Batch processing and A/B testing scripts\n- **`experiments/`** - Experimental evaluations\n\n### Key Features\n- **Evaluators**: excel (1-5 scale), pairwise (A/B comparison), societas (visual quality), content, rule_based, intent\n- **Batch Format**: JSON with prompts, document_type, metadata, flights, timeout\n- **Output Structure**: Timestamped run folders with JSON + CSV results, HTML reports, debug logs\n- **Excel Eval**: 5 dimensions (Accuracy, Completeness, Usefulness, Reliability, Aesthetics)\n- **Key Log Patterns**: Detects NO_SUMMARIZE blocks, data mismatches, sampling/fabrication indicators\n- **Parallel Execution**: Supports docker-compose scaling with auto-discovery\n- **Performance Analysis**: Excel A/B testing scripts with outlier detection\n\n---\n\n## 7. AGENT ARCHITECTURE PATTERNS\n\n### Registry-First Design\nEach agent must export `agentRegistry: AgentRegistryConfig` from `src/registry.ts`:\n- Agent identity: `id`, `name`, `packageName`, `description`\n- Versions array with default version\n- Tools list\n- Skills & subagents\n- RAI guidelines file\n- Flights (feature flags with `OfficeAgent.<AgentName>.<Feature>` pattern)\n- Filters (runtime conditionals)\n\n### Prompt Organization (Versioned Agents)\n```\nsrc/prompts/<version>/\n├── system-prompt.md (EJS templating with <%- variable %>)\n├── rai.md\n├── skills/<name>/SKILL.md\n├── subagents/<name>.md\n├── scripts/\n├── agent-capabilities/\n├── intent-detection/\n└── overwrites/\n```\n\n### Skills vs Sub-Agents\n- **Skill**: Instructions + scripts agent follows directly (shared context window)\n- **Sub-agent**: Isolated Claude instance with own system prompt (parallel, focused context)\n- Decision: Well-scoped pipeline steps → sub-agent; general capabilities → skill\n\n---\n\n## 8. KEY TECHNICAL PATTERNS\n\n### Logging Rules\n- **CRITICAL**: Never log user data (filenames, content, queries) to telemetry in `logInfo`, `logWarn`, `logError`\n- `logDebug` is local-only, safe for user data\n- Use numeric tag IDs for telemetry functions\n- Never use `console.*` in production code (ESLint enforced)\n\n### Imports & Dependencies\n- **Scoped imports only**: `@officeagent/core`, `@officeagent/message-protocol`\n- **No relative cross-package imports**: ESLint rule `import/no-relative-packages`\n- **Workspace dependency format**: `\"workspace:^\"` in package.json (never hardcoded versions)\n\n### Testing\n- **TypeScript**: Jest with ts-jest preset, `tests/**/*.test.ts`, 10s timeout\n- **Python**: pytest with coverage collection in CI only (`TF_BUILD` env var)\n- **Placement**: `<package>/tests/` for tests, `<package>/tests/**/mocks/` for mocks, `<package>/local-tests/` for local-only tests\n\n### Environment Configuration\n- **CLI & container**: `OAGENT_` prefix (e.g., `OAGENT_AGENTID`, `OAGENT_FLIGHTS`)\n- **OfficePy container**: `OfficePy__` prefix (e.g., `OfficePy__Deployment__LocalhostOfficeAgentDevelopment`)\n- **Config file**: `.env` at repo root (loaded by launcher and CLI)\n\n### WebSocket Flow (High-Level)\n1. Client sends `AgentRequestMessage` over WebSocket\n2. Router dispatches to agent handler (e.g., CreateAgent)\n3. Preprocessing: validate session, extract conversationId, check busy state\n4. Acknowledgment sent back\n5. Grounding content parsed\n6. Services initialized (FileWatcher, Logger, WebSocketMessenger, DebugZipCreator)\n7. Workspace turn created\n8. System prompt built (capabilities + RAI + skills)\n9. Claude query executed with hooks\n10. Messages streamed, logged, tracked (performance, CoT)\n11. Final response sent with files/artifacts\n\n---\n\n## 9. BUILD & DEPLOYMENT WORKFLOW\n\n### Local Development\n```powershell\n# PowerShell ONLY (bash will fail)\nnpm run setup              # First-time setup\nyarn build                 # Build all + Docker image (Docker Desktop required)\nyarn start                 # Start container + test client\nyarn start:compose         # Start via docker-compose (supports scaling)\nyarn reload               # Hot-reload code into running container\nyarn test                 # Run all tests\nyarn lint                 # ESLint check\noagent gen \"prompt\"       # Generate document via CLI\noagent eval ppt.example   # Run single evaluation\n```\n\n### Build Pipeline\n- `lage` coordinates build order across monorepo\n- Each package: clean → copy files → compile TS → dependency check\n- Python modules: editable install + syntax validation\n- Docker build includes node_modules from `docker/package.json` (separate from yarn workspaces)\n\n### Debug Links Setup\n- `gulp setupDebugLinks` creates Node.js debug port mappings\n- Supports remote debugging from IDE\n\n---\n\n## 10. FILE PATHS SUMMARY\n\n| Category | Path |\n|----------|------|\n| Documentation | `/docs/*.md`, `/docs/pptx/`, `/docs/eng_ms/` |\n| Agents | `/agents/create-agent`, `/agents/workspace-agent`, etc. |\n| Modules | `/modules/core`, `/modules/api`, `/modules/grounding`, etc. |\n| CLI | `/.devtools/cli/` |\n| Test Client | `/.devtools/test-client/` |\n| E2E Tests | `/.devtools/e2e-tests/` |\n| Eval Browser | `/.devtools/eval-browser/` |\n| OCV Tool | `/.devtools/ocv/` |\n| Launcher | `/.devtools/launcher/` |\n| Eval Framework | `/eval/` |\n| Docker | `/docker/` |\n| Build Scripts | `/gulp-tasks/` |\n| Root Config | `/package.json`, `/lage.config.js`, `/tsconfig.json`, `/docker-compose.yml` |\n\n---\n\n## 11. KEY INSIGHTS FOR NEW DEVELOPERS\n\n1. **PowerShell requirement**: All build/run commands must use PowerShell on Windows, not bash\n2. **Docker Desktop must be running** for `yarn build` to succeed\n3. **Yarn Berry (v4)** - not v1 commands\n4. **Node >= 24** required\n5. **Workspace linking**: All monorepo dependencies use `workspace:^`, never hardcoded versions\n6. **Flights are static** (override on init); **Filters are dynamic** (depend on request context)\n7. **Registry-first**: Every agent exports a registry configuration controlling its identity, capabilities, and behavior\n8. **Two-phase sub-agents**: Complex agents use Planning (outline/research) + Generation (execution) phases with file-based handoff\n9. **WebSocket-first**: All agent communication is message-routed over WebSocket for streaming and real-time updates\n10. **Evaluation before merge**: PRs require baseline eval comparisons to catch regressions\n11. **No user data in telemetry**: Use `logDebug` for user content, never `logInfo`/`logWarn`/`logError`\n\nThis is a mature, production-grade platform with comprehensive tooling for development, evaluation, debugging, and deployment."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: af5a46f4fde8b5b0d (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 75612\ntool_uses: 29\nduration_ms: 80232</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"98ef6066-2367-415b-b616-f95ed64be17a","uuid":"fa936538-eb70-4e85-8170-6f9a73e0b08d","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore these areas of C:/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/:\n\n1. Read docs/BEST_PRACTICES.md if it exists\n2. List and read key files in the docs/ directory\n3. Explore .devtools/ directory structure - what's in cli/, test-client/, e2e-tests/\n4. Read the eval/CLAUDE.md and understand the eval framework structure\n5. Read docker-compose.yml and docker/Dockerfile (first 100 lines) to understand the runtime\n6. Read the root package.json and lage.config.js to understand the build system\n7. Read the root tsconfig.json\n\nBe thorough in reading the actual content of these files.","agentId":"af5a46f4fde8b5b0d","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the OfficeAgent codebase. Let me compile my findings:\n\n## Comprehensive Exploration Report: OfficeAgent Monorepo\n\n### Overview\nOfficeAgent is a sophisticated AI-powered platform for Office document creation (DOCX, PPTX, XLSX, PDF) built on the Claude Agent SDK and Azure OpenAI infrastructure. It's containerized in Docker and runs as a distributed system with multiple agents, shared modules, and development tools.\n\n---\n\n## 1. DOCUMENTATION STRUCTURE\n\n### Root Level Documentation (`docs/`)\nKey files discovered:\n\n- **`BEST_PRACTICES.md`** - Universal guidelines covering:\n  - Repo layout (agents/, modules/, .devtools/, eval/, docker/)\n  - Package naming conventions (@officeagent/* scope)\n  - File & directory conventions (src → dist/src/)\n  - Import rules (scoped imports, no relative cross-package imports)\n  - Agent development patterns (registry-first approach)\n  - Prompt organization with versioning and skills/subagents\n  - Flights (feature flags) vs Filters (runtime rules)\n  - Logging rules (no user data in telemetry)\n  - Testing structure (Jest for TS, pytest for Python)\n  - Build pipeline (lage orchestration, Docker)\n  - Common pitfalls (PowerShell requirement, Docker Desktop, Node.js >= 22, Yarn 4.10.3)\n\n- **`WORKSPACE_AGENT_DESIGN.md`** - Detailed architecture for workspace agent (Reports, Documents, Presentations, Newsletters, Blogs):\n  - Two-phase sub-agent architecture (Planning + Generation)\n  - File-based handoff between phases\n  - WebSocket flow with incremental responses\n  - Message protocol specifications\n  - Artifact types and rendering formats\n\n- **`AZURE_OPENAI_DESIGN.md`** - Azure OpenAI integration strategy with `/v1/openai` endpoint, request/response routing patterns\n\n- **`EXCEL_HEADLESS.md`** - Server-side Excel automation via Office.js in sandboxed environments\n\n- **`AgentRequestMessage-WebSocket-Flow.md`** - End-to-end WebSocket handling flow for agent requests through 8 phases (preprocessing → Claude execution → response delivery)\n\nAdditional docs for image search, teams channel fetching, OCE, Python testing, and pptx architecture documentation.\n\n---\n\n## 2. BUILD SYSTEM & CONFIGURATION\n\n### Root `package.json`\n- **Workspaces**: `.devtools/*`, `modules/*`, `agents/*` (Yarn 4.10.3)\n- **Key Scripts**:\n  - `yarn build` - Full build (lage + Docker)\n  - `yarn compile` - lage only (no Docker)\n  - `yarn start` - Start Docker + test client\n  - `yarn start:compose` - Docker Compose with scaling\n  - `yarn test` - Jest + pytest via lage\n  - `yarn lint` - ESLint across workspaces\n  - `oagent` - CLI entry point\n- **Engines**: Node >= 24, Yarn 4.10.3\n- **Dependencies**: @anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk 0.2.39\n- **DevDependencies**: TypeScript 5.9.3, Jest 30.2.0, lage 2.14.15, various build tools\n\n### `lage.config.js`\n- Orchestrates build task dependencies\n- `build` depends on `^build` (upstream packages first)\n- Caching enabled with environment glob invalidation\n- Inputs: `src/**`, `tsconfig.json`, `package.json`, `pyproject.toml`\n- Outputs: `dist/**`, `.build/.pyproject-hash`\n\n### `tsconfig.json`\n- Target: ES2020\n- Module: commonjs\n- Strict mode enabled\n- Declaration maps and source maps\n- Resolves JSON modules\n- Excludes node_modules and dist\n\n---\n\n## 3. DOCKER & RUNTIME\n\n### `docker-compose.yml`\n- Single service: `officeagent` (scalable with `--scale`)\n- Image: `officeagent:devlatest`\n- Ports exposed: 6010 (API), 6011 (internal), 6020 (debug), 7010 (grounding HTTP)\n- Environment:\n  - `OfficePy__Deployment__LocalhostOfficeAgentDevelopment: \"True\"`\n  - `OAGENT_AGENTID` (default: create-agent)\n  - `OAGENT_FLIGHTS` for feature gates\n  - `GITHUB_TOKEN` for CLI auth\n- Health check: `/health` endpoint on port 6010\n- Network: `officeagent-net` bridge\n- Secrets: pip index URL, npm credentials\n\n### `docker/Dockerfile` (first 100 lines analyzed)\n- Multi-stage build with BuildKit parallelization\n- **Poppler builder stage** - Compiles poppler from source (26.02.0) with cmake\n- **LibreOffice installer stage** - Extracts and installs LibreOffice 26.2.0 RPMs\n- **Node deps stage** - Node.js 24 + npm, installs from `docker/package.json`\n- **Final runtime stage** - Inherits from OfficePy base image (mcr.microsoft.com/officepy/codeexecutionjupyter4)\n- Environment: `CLAUDE_CODE_MAX_OUTPUT_TOKENS=64000`, `NODE_PATH` includes app modules\n\n---\n\n## 4. MONOREPO STRUCTURE\n\n### Agents (`agents/`)\n15 agent packages discovered:\n- **`create-agent`** - Core document creation (DOCX, PPTX, XLSX) using Claude SDK\n- **`gpt-create-agent`** - Azure OpenAI variant\n- **`ppt-creation-agent`** - PowerPoint-specific\n- **`ppt-edit-agent`** - PowerPoint editing\n- **`dw-accountant-agent`** - DataWorks accountant\n- **`dw-paralegal-agent`** - DataWorks paralegal\n- **`dw-marketer-agent`** - DataWorks marketer\n- **`odsp-agent`** - OneDrive/SharePoint integration\n- **`workspace-agent`** - Two-phase planner/generator for reports, documents, presentations\n- **`grounding-agent`** - Enterprise search & content retrieval\n- **`excel-agent`** - Excel-specific operations\n- **`excel-js-runner-agent`** - Office.js execution sandbox\n- **`office-agent`** - Generic office operations\n- **`ppt-agent`** - PowerPoint operations\n- Plus others\n\n### Modules (`modules/`)\n19 shared library packages:\n- **`api`** - Express server, WebSocket handling, session init\n- **`core`** - BaseAgent, logging, WebSocket router, session context\n- **`message-protocol`** - Message types (MessageType enum, Request/Response structures)\n- **`grounding`** - Enterprise search, image search, content parsing\n- **`rai`** - Responsible AI validation\n- **`excel-headless`** - Server-side Excel automation via Office.js\n- **`chain-of-thought`** - CoT display and tracking\n- **`html2pptx`** - HTML to PowerPoint conversion\n- **`json-to-docx-ooxml`** - JSON to Word OOXML conversion\n- **`mcp-proxy`** - Model Context Protocol proxy\n- **`gpt-agent`** - Azure OpenAI agent wrapper\n- **`git-remote-spo`** - SharePoint/OneDrive Git integration\n- **`excel-parser`** - Excel file parsing\n- **`pptx-assets`** - PowerPoint asset management\n- **`verify-slide-html`** - HTML validation for slides\n- **`orchestrator`** - Orchestration logic\n- **`example-cs`** - C# examples\n\n---\n\n## 5. DEVELOPMENT TOOLS (`.devtools/`)\n\n### CLI (`cli/` - @officeagent-tools/cli 1.1.1130)\nTypeScript-based command-line interface for document generation:\n- **Commands**:\n  - `ping` - Health check\n  - `generate` (alias: `gen`) - Create documents with flights, grounding content, message annotations\n  - `download` (alias: `dl`) - Download previously generated documents\n  - `new-agent` - Scaffold new agents with presets\n  - `config` - Manage CLI configuration (.env)\n  - `eval` - Run evaluations\n  - `workspace` - Workspace operations\n- **Features**:\n  - URL auto-detection (SharePoint/OneDrive links converted to annotations)\n  - Message annotations support (File, Email, Meeting, Chat, Transcript, People)\n  - Flight flag support for feature testing\n  - Report generation with debug.zip extraction\n  - Configuration via `.env` with `OAGENT_` prefix\n- **Dependencies**: chalk, commander, dotenv, execa, inquirer, node-fetch, open, ora, table\n\n### Test Client (`test-client/` - @officeagent-tools/test-client 1.1.1130)\nExternal LLM client for WebSocket relay testing:\n- Connects to WebSocket server at `/ws`\n- Forwards requests to Anthropic API\n- Uses Token Server for automatic authentication\n- Configuration: `LLM_WS_URL`, `LLM_API_HOST`, `LLM_API_PATH`\n- Dependencies: @augloop packages, @officeagent packages, chalk, dotenv, exceljs\n\n### E2E Tests (`e2e-tests/` - @officeagent/e2e-tests 1.1.1130)\nEnd-to-end testing framework:\n- Configured via JSON files (e.g., `ppt-example-config.json`)\n- Can test against local, container, cloud, or remote servers\n- Dependencies: chalk, commander, execa, fs-extra, node-fetch, ora\n\n### Eval Browser (`eval-browser/`)\nPython/Flask web UI for browsing evaluation results:\n- Runs on port 3050\n- Displays eval outputs from `eval/outputs/`\n- A/B comparison views\n- Side-by-side page images\n- Aesthetics/Fidelity/Consistency scores\n- Keyboard navigation\n\n### OCV Feedback Tool (`ocv/`)\nComprehensive feedback analysis system:\n- Scrapes OCV feedback\n- Categorizes via Claude LLM\n- Queries Kusto for telemetry\n- Searches ADO for related bugs\n- Generates HTML reports\n- MCP servers: ocv_mcp, kusto_mcp, ado_mcp\n\n### Launcher (`launcher/`)\nClaude Code desktop launcher:\n- One-time setup via `SETUP.cmd`\n- Auto-detects project directory\n- Loads `.env` automatically\n- Validates API key\n- Creates pinnable desktop shortcut\n\n---\n\n## 6. EVALUATION FRAMEWORK (`eval/`)\n\n### Structure\n- **`aliases.json`** - Aliases for common eval configurations\n- **`configs/`** - Evaluation configuration JSON files\n- **`datasets/`** - Test batch JSON files\n- **`src/cli.py`** - CLI entry point (`oagent eval`)\n- **`src/framework.py`** - Main orchestrator\n- **`src/types.py`** - Data models (EvalRequest, EvalConfig, EvalResult)\n- **`src/evaluators/`** - Modular evaluator implementations (excel, pairwise, societas, content, rule_based, intent)\n- **`src/preprocessors/`** - Data extraction before evaluation\n- **`src/scrapers/`** - Document generation via API\n- **`scripts/`** - Batch processing and A/B testing scripts\n- **`experiments/`** - Experimental evaluations\n\n### Key Features\n- **Evaluators**: excel (1-5 scale), pairwise (A/B comparison), societas (visual quality), content, rule_based, intent\n- **Batch Format**: JSON with prompts, document_type, metadata, flights, timeout\n- **Output Structure**: Timestamped run folders with JSON + CSV results, HTML reports, debug logs\n- **Excel Eval**: 5 dimensions (Accuracy, Completeness, Usefulness, Reliability, Aesthetics)\n- **Key Log Patterns**: Detects NO_SUMMARIZE blocks, data mismatches, sampling/fabrication indicators\n- **Parallel Execution**: Supports docker-compose scaling with auto-discovery\n- **Performance Analysis**: Excel A/B testing scripts with outlier detection\n\n---\n\n## 7. AGENT ARCHITECTURE PATTERNS\n\n### Registry-First Design\nEach agent must export `agentRegistry: AgentRegistryConfig` from `src/registry.ts`:\n- Agent identity: `id`, `name`, `packageName`, `description`\n- Versions array with default version\n- Tools list\n- Skills & subagents\n- RAI guidelines file\n- Flights (feature flags with `OfficeAgent.<AgentName>.<Feature>` pattern)\n- Filters (runtime conditionals)\n\n### Prompt Organization (Versioned Agents)\n```\nsrc/prompts/<version>/\n├── system-prompt.md (EJS templating with <%- variable %>)\n├── rai.md\n├── skills/<name>/SKILL.md\n├── subagents/<name>.md\n├── scripts/\n├── agent-capabilities/\n├── intent-detection/\n└── overwrites/\n```\n\n### Skills vs Sub-Agents\n- **Skill**: Instructions + scripts agent follows directly (shared context window)\n- **Sub-agent**: Isolated Claude instance with own system prompt (parallel, focused context)\n- Decision: Well-scoped pipeline steps → sub-agent; general capabilities → skill\n\n---\n\n## 8. KEY TECHNICAL PATTERNS\n\n### Logging Rules\n- **CRITICAL**: Never log user data (filenames, content, queries) to telemetry in `logInfo`, `logWarn`, `logError`\n- `logDebug` is local-only, safe for user data\n- Use numeric tag IDs for telemetry functions\n- Never use `console.*` in production code (ESLint enforced)\n\n### Imports & Dependencies\n- **Scoped imports only**: `@officeagent/core`, `@officeagent/message-protocol`\n- **No relative cross-package imports**: ESLint rule `import/no-relative-packages`\n- **Workspace dependency format**: `\"workspace:^\"` in package.json (never hardcoded versions)\n\n### Testing\n- **TypeScript**: Jest with ts-jest preset, `tests/**/*.test.ts`, 10s timeout\n- **Python**: pytest with coverage collection in CI only (`TF_BUILD` env var)\n- **Placement**: `<package>/tests/` for tests, `<package>/tests/**/mocks/` for mocks, `<package>/local-tests/` for local-only tests\n\n### Environment Configuration\n- **CLI & container**: `OAGENT_` prefix (e.g., `OAGENT_AGENTID`, `OAGENT_FLIGHTS`)\n- **OfficePy container**: `OfficePy__` prefix (e.g., `OfficePy__Deployment__LocalhostOfficeAgentDevelopment`)\n- **Config file**: `.env` at repo root (loaded by launcher and CLI)\n\n### WebSocket Flow (High-Level)\n1. Client sends `AgentRequestMessage` over WebSocket\n2. Router dispatches to agent handler (e.g., CreateAgent)\n3. Preprocessing: validate session, extract conversationId, check busy state\n4. Acknowledgment sent back\n5. Grounding content parsed\n6. Services initialized (FileWatcher, Logger, WebSocketMessenger, DebugZipCreator)\n7. Workspace turn created\n8. System prompt built (capabilities + RAI + skills)\n9. Claude query executed with hooks\n10. Messages streamed, logged, tracked (performance, CoT)\n11. Final response sent with files/artifacts\n\n---\n\n## 9. BUILD & DEPLOYMENT WORKFLOW\n\n### Local Development\n```powershell\n# PowerShell ONLY (bash will fail)\nnpm run setup              # First-time setup\nyarn build                 # Build all + Docker image (Docker Desktop required)\nyarn start                 # Start container + test client\nyarn start:compose         # Start via docker-compose (supports scaling)\nyarn reload               # Hot-reload code into running container\nyarn test                 # Run all tests\nyarn lint                 # ESLint check\noagent gen \"prompt\"       # Generate document via CLI\noagent eval ppt.example   # Run single evaluation\n```\n\n### Build Pipeline\n- `lage` coordinates build order across monorepo\n- Each package: clean → copy files → compile TS → dependency check\n- Python modules: editable install + syntax validation\n- Docker build includes node_modules from `docker/package.json` (separate from yarn workspaces)\n\n### Debug Links Setup\n- `gulp setupDebugLinks` creates Node.js debug port mappings\n- Supports remote debugging from IDE\n\n---\n\n## 10. FILE PATHS SUMMARY\n\n| Category | Path |\n|----------|------|\n| Documentation | `/docs/*.md`, `/docs/pptx/`, `/docs/eng_ms/` |\n| Agents | `/agents/create-agent`, `/agents/workspace-agent`, etc. |\n| Modules | `/modules/core`, `/modules/api`, `/modules/grounding`, etc. |\n| CLI | `/.devtools/cli/` |\n| Test Client | `/.devtools/test-client/` |\n| E2E Tests | `/.devtools/e2e-tests/` |\n| Eval Browser | `/.devtools/eval-browser/` |\n| OCV Tool | `/.devtools/ocv/` |\n| Launcher | `/.devtools/launcher/` |\n| Eval Framework | `/eval/` |\n| Docker | `/docker/` |\n| Build Scripts | `/gulp-tasks/` |\n| Root Config | `/package.json`, `/lage.config.js`, `/tsconfig.json`, `/docker-compose.yml` |\n\n---\n\n## 11. KEY INSIGHTS FOR NEW DEVELOPERS\n\n1. **PowerShell requirement**: All build/run commands must use PowerShell on Windows, not bash\n2. **Docker Desktop must be running** for `yarn build` to succeed\n3. **Yarn Berry (v4)** - not v1 commands\n4. **Node >= 24** required\n5. **Workspace linking**: All monorepo dependencies use `workspace:^`, never hardcoded versions\n6. **Flights are static** (override on init); **Filters are dynamic** (depend on request context)\n7. **Registry-first**: Every agent exports a registry configuration controlling its identity, capabilities, and behavior\n8. **Two-phase sub-agents**: Complex agents use Planning (outline/research) + Generation (execution) phases with file-based handoff\n9. **WebSocket-first**: All agent communication is message-routed over WebSocket for streaming and real-time updates\n10. **Evaluation before merge**: PRs require baseline eval comparisons to catch regressions\n11. **No user data in telemetry**: Use `logDebug` for user content, never `logInfo`/`logWarn`/`logError`\n\nThis is a mature, production-grade platform with comprehensive tooling for development, evaluation, debugging, and deployment."}],"totalDurationMs":80232,"totalTokens":75612,"totalToolUseCount":29,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1771,"cache_read_input_tokens":69188,"output_tokens":4651,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1771},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
