{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01MNocAJRYAQpY96Th32HieY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01X7Qgs3UAK8b4t7aKbKAZqy","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"C:/Users/yemishin/.squad/notes/inbox/ripley-2026-03-14.md","content":"# Ripley — OfficeAgent Deep Exploration Findings\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-14\n**Task:** Full codebase architecture exploration of OfficeAgent monorepo\n\n## Area Explored\n\nComplete OfficeAgent monorepo: agents/, modules/, .devtools/, eval/, docs/, docker/, build system configuration.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Overview\nOfficeAgent is an AI-powered document generation platform running in Docker containers. It uses Claude SDK and Azure OpenAI (via GitHub Copilot SDK) to create DOCX, PPTX, XLSX, and PDF files. The system is a Yarn 4.10.3 monorepo with lage task orchestration, TypeScript 5.9, Node 24+, and a Python evaluation framework.\n\n### Message Flow\n```\nClient (WebSocket on :6010)\n  → API Module (app.ts) → WebSocket/HTTP routing\n    → Core (WebSocketManager/Router)\n      → Handler Registry (typed message dispatch)\n        → Orchestrator (Claude SDK or GHCP)\n          → Grounding Pipeline (enterprise search, image, web)\n            → Agent execution (skills, sub-agents, hooks)\n              → Chain-of-Thought tracking\n                → Response streamed back to client\n```\n\n### Three-Tier Agent Architecture\n1. **Full Claude SDK agents** (create-agent): Multi-version, sub-agents, 20+ flights, request interceptors, hooks by agent type. The most complex — `create-agent.ts` is ~84KB.\n2. **Copilot SDK agents** (office-agent, excel-agent): Simpler, use GhcpOrchestrator, import shared services from create-agent.\n3. **Minimal agents** (ppt-creation-agent): No LLM, direct HTML→PPTX conversion, bare registry.\n\n### Orchestrator Abstraction\n`@officeagent/orchestrator` provides a provider-agnostic `IOrchestrator` interface:\n- `ClaudeOrchestrator` — Claude SDK wrapper\n- `GhcpOrchestrator` — GitHub Copilot SDK wrapper\n- Factory pattern: `createOrchestrator()` selects provider at runtime\n- Common types: `OrchestratorRequest`, `OrchestratorMessage`, `OrchestratorResult`\n\n## Patterns\n\n### 1. Registry-First Agent Design\nEvery agent exports `agentRegistry: AgentRegistryConfig` from `src/registry.ts`:\n- Identity: id, name, packageName, description\n- Versions array with model, tools, skills, subagents, scripts\n- Flights (static feature flags) and Filters (dynamic runtime rules)\n- Default version selection + flight-based version overrides\n\n### 2. Versioned Prompt Organization\n```\nsrc/prompts/<version>/\n├── system-prompt.md (EJS templates)\n├── rai.md\n├── skills/<name>/SKILL.md\n├── subagents/<name>.md\n├── scripts/\n├── agent-capabilities/\n├── intent-detection/\n└── overwrites/ (flight-conditional replacements)\n```\n\n### 3. Skills vs Sub-Agents\n- **Skills**: Instructions + scripts the agent follows directly (shared context window)\n- **Sub-agents**: Isolated Claude instances with own system prompt (parallel, focused)\n- Pattern: well-scoped pipeline steps → sub-agent; general capabilities → skill\n\n### 4. Hook System\n- `HookRegistry` with per-agent-type providers (Base, Word, Excel, PowerPoint)\n- Hooks: PreToolUse, PostToolUse, SessionStart, SessionEnd, startTurn\n- Used for performance tracking, CoT streaming, output validation\n\n### 5. Grounding Pipeline (4-Stage)\n`@officeagent/grounding` implements: Preprocessor → Retriever → Postprocessor → Storage\n- Entity-specific extractors: Email, File, Chat, Meeting, People, Calendar, Transcript\n- A2A (Agent-to-Agent) HTTP communication pattern\n\n### 6. Build & Runtime\n- PowerShell required for yarn/oagent/gulp commands on Windows\n- Docker multi-stage build: poppler + LibreOffice + Node 24 + OfficePy base image\n- Ports: 6010 (external API), 6011 (internal), 6020 (debug), 7010 (grounding)\n- Hot reload: `yarn reload` copies dist to running container\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Module Dependency Graph (key paths)\n- **All agents** → `@officeagent/core` (BaseAgent, logging, WebSocket)\n- **All agents** → `@officeagent/message-protocol` (message types)\n- **create-agent** → `@officeagent/grounding`, `@officeagent/rai`, `@officeagent/chain-of-thought`, `@officeagent/excel-headless`\n- **office-agent** → `@officeagent/create-agent` (imports shared services, hooks)\n- **API** → `@officeagent/core`, `@officeagent/message-protocol`, `@officeagent/mcp-proxy`\n- **orchestrator** → no internal deps (provider-agnostic abstraction)\n\n### External Dependencies\n- `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` 0.2.39\n- Express + ws (HTTP/WebSocket)\n- `@augloop-tools/*` (token server, test client)\n- Python: pytest, flask (eval browser), msal, playwright\n\n## Gaps\n\n1. **CLAUDE.md coverage**: Some agents lack CLAUDE.md files (dw-marketer-agent, grounding-agent, excel-js-runner-agent, ppt-agent). These are harder for new agents/developers to understand.\n2. **Documentation freshness**: README.md lists 7 agents but there are 15+ in the agents/ directory. The gap includes newer agents like workspace-agent, excel-agent, ppt-agent, grounding-agent.\n3. **No workspace-agent CLAUDE.md**: workspace-agent has detailed design docs in `docs/WORKSPACE_AGENT_DESIGN.md` but the agent itself has a CLAUDE.md.\n4. **Test coverage visibility**: Coverage only collected in CI (TF_BUILD=true), no easy way to check coverage locally.\n\n## Recommendations\n\n1. **For new agent work**: Always start from registry.ts, read the relevant CLAUDE.md, and follow the create-agent pattern as the canonical reference.\n2. **For prompt changes**: Use the flight-based overwrite system rather than modifying base version files. This allows safe A/B testing.\n3. **For shared module changes**: Run `yarn build` (not just compile) to catch Docker packaging issues early.\n4. **For exploration tasks**: The `oagent` CLI is the fastest way to test changes — `oagent gen \"prompt\" --open` generates and opens the result.\n\n## Key File Locations\n\n| What | Where |\n|------|-------|\n| Agent pattern reference | `agents/create-agent/src/registry.ts` |\n| API entry point | `modules/api/src/app.ts` |\n| Message types | `modules/message-protocol/src/types/` |\n| Orchestrator interface | `modules/orchestrator/src/types.ts` |\n| Grounding pipeline | `modules/grounding/src/orchestrator.ts` |\n| Best practices | `docs/BEST_PRACTICES.md` |\n| WebSocket flow doc | `docs/AgentRequestMessage-WebSocket-Flow.md` |\n| CLI source | `.devtools/cli/` |\n| Eval framework | `eval/` |\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":712,"cache_read_input_tokens":58766,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":712,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"98ef6066-2367-415b-b616-f95ed64be17a","uuid":"e848a306-8d75-42ee-8810-811dd1417b19"}
